(235941,'N+1 Magazine Discussion',cast('2013-03-20 16:30' as date),cast('2013-03-20 16:30' as date),'105 Lawrence',NULL,NULL,'PORT','N+1 Magazine, a literary magazine, will be doing a college campus tour and is coming to Hudson in March. They will lead a reading and discussion about publishing, how to make money as a writer, and other topics pertaining to the literary world. ',500),
(237377,'Ron Paul Lecture: "Liberty Defined: The Future of Freedom"',cast('2013-04-24 16:00' as date),cast('2013-04-24 17:30' as date),'Chapel',NULL,NULL,'CR','Ron Paul will be speaking today in the Hudson Memorial Chapel at 5pm. Doors will open at 4pm so that audience members can get their seats. The event is ticket and you must present your ticket upon entering the venue to be granted admission. 20-30 extra tickets will be available at the door on a first come/ first serve basis for those who were unable to get them during the original ticket sale.'||chr(10)||'Dr. Paul will be speaking for approximately 45 minutes and will then answer any questions presented by the audience. It has been requested that no audio or video recordings be permitted during the lecture. In the event that you do not have a ticket and would still like to see the lecture, a Live Stream will be available in Lawrence 105.This event is sponsored by the College Republicans, the Center for Freedom and Western Civilization, the Institute for Philosophy, Politics, and Economics, The Budget Allocation Committee, Students for a Sensible Drug Policy, and The Hudson Entrepreneurs Club.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'For any additional questions regarding the event, please contact Taylor Hollen (thollen@hudson.edu).',500),
(238994,'Rick Kahlbaurgh Lecture',cast('2013-04-11 17:00' as date),cast('2013-04-11 17:15' as date),'Ho 101',NULL,NULL,'HTC','Rick Kahlbaurgh and Ted Rollins, both CEOs of public companies are coming to campus on April 11th to speak on three main topics: IPOs, MandA deals, and the developing the necessary skills to run a company.',null),
(244415,'The Naked Truth about Homosexuality in the Caribbean',cast('2013-03-28 11:30' as date),cast('2013-03-28 11:15' as date),'Women Studies Lounge',NULL,NULL,'CSA','With the help of WMST and LGBTQ Initiatives, CSA will be hosting a brown bag about the issue of homosexuality in the Caribbean. There will be a panel of students, some speaking from first-hand experience, about the homosexuality surrounding the communities in the Caribbean and the steps being taken to overcome this issue. Come out for a great discussion and invite your friends! Hosted by CSA',440),
(249613,'Gate-Town Connection',cast('2013-04-07 16:00' as date),cast('2013-04-07 18:00' as date),'Whitnall Field',NULL,NULL,'BDS','Please join Hudson faculty and Hamilton residents on Whitnall Field for our third town-gown event, celebrating the strong connection between the Hudson and Hamilton communities. There will be a free BBQ (Frank will be closed), Danger Boy concert, inflatables, and a pie-eating contest!',425),
(252280,'CCF Large Group: Modern Day Slavery',cast('2013-04-09 19:00' as date),cast('2013-04-09 19:00' as date),'Chapel Basement',NULL,NULL,'HCF','Discussion on the facts, causes, and ramifications of modern day slavery and human trafficking. 27 Million people are enslaved today, find out more.',null),
