(306223,'Family Weekend Banquet',cast('2013-10-26 18:00' as date),cast('2013-10-26 19:00' as date),'The Edge Cafe',NULL,NULL,'BSU','The Black Student Union annually hosts the Family Weekend Banquet. This event is open to all parents and students on the Hudson campus as well as the community members of Hamilton. The Family Weekend Banquet is a way for BSU to welcome all parents and students during Family Weekend. There is a keynote speech, usually given by a Professor(s) and/or core members of the Black Student Union, followed by a catered dinner. Lastly alumni speak to parents and students about their experiences at Hudson and the opportunities Hudson has offered them.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Hosted by Black Student Union, ALANA Cultural Center, Alumni of Color, and Sisters of the Round Table.',625),
(306226,'Guest Lecture with Randy Fagundo and Dan Peck, CEO and VP of MinuteKey, Inc.',cast('2013-10-26 16:30' as date),cast('2013-10-26 17:30' as date),'Love Auditorium, Olin Hall',NULL,NULL,'HEC','The Entrepreneurs Club is bringing MinuteKey''s CEO and VP of Operations Randy Fagundo and Dan Peck to Hudson''s Love Auditorium on the Saturday (10/26) of Parents Weekend.'||chr(10)||'Fagundo left his first startup business, American Coin Merchandising, when it was acquired by Coinstar, which he joined as the company''s President of Entertainment Services. After three years as president, Fagundo served as a partner at the consulting firm Automated Retail Solutions, LLC. He joined MinuteKey as its first CEO in 2010.'||chr(10)||'Dan Peck left a supply chain manager position at Proctor and Gamble in 2002 to join Randy at Coinstar as the Vice President of Manufacturing Logistics and was promoted to Vice President and General Manager in 2009. He later filled the position that Randy vacated as the company''s President of Entertainment Services before he accompanied Randy as a partner at Automated Retail Solutions, LLC. Dan joined Randy at MinuteKey as the Vice President of Operations in 2011.'||chr(10)||'The event will begin with a reception and refreshments at 4:30. The speakers will begin at 5:00 and will talk for a about an hour about their experiences running and fundraising for their startup and early stage businesses.'||chr(10)||'The event is sponsored by the Entrepreneurs Club in coordination with the Thought Into Action (TIA) Institute.',350),
(311084,'CWIB Parent''s Weekend Reception',cast('2013-10-26 15:00' as date),cast('2013-10-26 15:30' as date),'13 E Kendrick St Hamilton NY 13346',NULL,NULL,'HWIB','The Hudson Women in Business group will host a reception for students, parents, and other members of the Hudson community during Parent''s Weekend at the home of Dean Nelson. This will be an opportunity to network, mingle, and learn more about CWIB.',null),
