(325089,'Healthy Cuisine: Korean "sushi"? Kimbop Making Workshop',cast('2013-11-05 11:30' as date),cast('2013-11-05 13:30' as date),'COOP Media Lounge',NULL,NULL,'KCA','Join the Korean Student Association for a fun interactive Kimbop (Korean "sushi" roll) workshop and learn about healthy eating, Korean-style!  Don''t worry, no raw fish involved, and you can choose your own ingredients.  Come quick, before the rolls run out! ',360),
(325705,'Black Solidarity Day Speakout',cast('2013-11-04 12:15' as date),cast('2013-11-04 13:15' as date),'Chapel Steps',NULL,NULL,'BSU','"Black Solidarity Day is a day to celebrate solidarity between all Black individuals. On the Hudson campus, the BSU uses this as an opportunity to celebrate solidarity between everyone regardless of race, gender, sexuality etc. Black Solidarity Day consists of a speakout, a traditional candle-lit walk from the HRC to ALANA, and a dinner. The speakout will be held on the Chapel Steps from12:15-1:15. President Herbst will be there to say a few words on diversity at Hudson. The traditional candle-lit walk from the HRC to ALANA will start at 7:45 and the dinner will be from 8-9:30 at ALANA. The dinner is used to discuss the theme for the day while providing a safe, welcoming and uniting environment."',480),
