(338586,'Black History Month Keynote Speaker: Nikki Giovanni',cast('2014-02-06 19:00' as date),cast('2014-02-06 20:30' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,NULL,'BSU','The Black Student Union will host Nikki Giovanni as our Black History Month Keynote Speaker. Nikki Giovanni, a product of the famous 1960s Black Arts Movement, remains one of America''s most distinguished and widely read African-American poets, authors, and essayists. Her outspokenness has spanned a quarter-century, and the human rights activist remains as determined and committed as ever to fighting for civil rights and equality in education. '||chr(10)||'Nikki Giovanni will recite her An Evening of Poetry, Love, and Enlightenment lecture. She will share her eloquent words of wisdom, spanning the civil rights movement, politics, love, art, and more. Discussing the ideals of equality in her dramatic oratory, she shares the experiences and thoughtful poetry that embody her activism and legacy of passion for the arts. After her lecture there will be a 45-minute reception where people are invited to meet her, shake her hand, get a picture, and ask questions in a smaller setting.',550),
