(344263,'Hudson Women in Business Spring Immersion Trip',cast('2014-02-27 15:45' as date),cast('2014-03-01 18:00' as date),'New York City',NULL,NULL,'HWIB','  A trip to New York City to visit and network with Hudson alumni to learn about the different business industries through site visits, an evening receptin, and workshops.',155),
(345507,'Visit from Poet Orlando White',cast('2014-03-24 16:30' as date),cast('2014-03-25 15:30' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center',NULL,NULL,'NAIS','In order to recognize indigenous heritage, literature and art at Hudson University, Native American Student Association would like to invite Orlando White, a Dine (Navajo) poet, to give a lecture on his work and to lead workshops in writing for our student body.',900),
(345510,'Heritage Dinner',cast('2014-02-28 18:00' as date),cast('2014-02-28 20:00' as date),'The Edge Cafe',NULL,NULL,'BSU','The Black Student Union annually hosts the Heritage Dinner on the last day of Black History Month. We host this event because it is open to all students, faculty and staff on Hudson University as well as the community members of Hamilton. The Heritage Dinner is a way for BSU to end Black History Month on a good note by providing good food, good company and good discussion.',700),
(345512,'Black History Month Release Night',cast('2014-02-21 18:00' as date),cast('2014-02-21 20:00' as date),'ALANA Lounge',NULL,NULL,'BSU','Release Night is an opportunity for students on campus to express themselves and speak on social, political, and economic concerns that they have been pondering. It is a welcoming and encouraging space for dialogue to occur on the basis of the type of concerns, questions, and aspirations that Hudson students raise to one another. The Black Student Union takes great pride in celebrating students voices. Through the hosting of Release Nights we provide this platform.'||chr(10)||'Essentially, it is a chance to gain support and recognition through others about the struggles and achievements that Hudson students may be enduring. Students are provided a support structure, which allows them to openly voice their thoughts without fear of being judged.',410),
(345516,'Finals Study Break',cast('2014-05-04 16:00' as date),cast('2014-05-04 17:00' as date),'Academic Quad (rain location: Ho, Cunniff Commons)',NULL,NULL,'SAA','Students will make their own sundaes and enjoy being outdoors.',170),
(345517,'AMTA Regional Tournament',cast('2014-02-07 15:00' as date),cast('2014-02-09 23:00' as date),'Buffalo State University',NULL,NULL,'MT','The Hudson Mock Trial Team will be competing in the annual AMTA Regional tournament in hopes of gaining a bid to ORCS - the first round of national competition. ',290),
(361007,'Princeton Interactive Crisis Simulation 2014',cast('2014-02-20 16:30' as date),cast('2014-02-23 17:30' as date),'Princeton, NJ',NULL,NULL,'MUN','This is a crisis-based Model United Nations conference, meaning that our delegates will be in a much more competitive and immersive environment than at regular conferences. The conference lasts for four days, over the course of which our delegates debate in committee sessions for upwards of 7 hours a day in order to advance the position of their assigned country.',440),
(366322,'Northeast Regionals',cast('2014-02-22 08:00' as date),cast('2014-02-23 20:00' as date),'Western Connecticut College',NULL,NULL,'DS','Western Connecticut College will host the Hat City Debate Tournament, which serves as the regional championship. The tournament is a British Parliamentary style tournament featuring five preliminary rounds of competition and is open to both novice and varsity level debaters. It will take place Saturday, February 22 through Sunday, February 23. Hudson will be competing against many of the best teams in the US. ',590),
(366329,'Africana Women''s Week',cast('2014-02-25 11:30' as date),cast('2014-03-09 02:00' as date),'WMST',NULL,NULL,'SRT','Sisters of the Round Table (SORT) is requesting funding for our annual Africana Womens Week, a week dedicated to highlighting inspirational women of color and identifying with womens issues. Sisters of the Round Table is a support network for women of color that focuses on increasing awareness and addressing issues facing women and women of color within and beyond the Hudson community. This year, SORT is designating the last week of February, leading into Womens History Month as Africana Womens Week (s). This year we are planning to have our events from February 25 to March 8, 2013 in order to space out our events so more people are likely to attend and to reduce stress from CORE members organizing these events.  Africana Womens Week not only raises awareness about the issues talked about in its forum, but also that March is Womens History Month - meant to celebrate the beauty, intellect and accomplishment of the women who came before us, and a guide to the women after us. The purpose of this week is to hold events pertaining to issues concerning women of color and also to pay homage to prominent female figures of color and female figures in general, that deserve recognition, and often go unnoticed. Each event that SORT sponsors this week will be focused on both building a support network and fostering a greater sense of community. All of our events will address basic human issues such as inequality, identity issues and problems with self-expression, which affect a great number of people in the Hudson community. All events will be open to the Hudson community to attend and we hope they foster better relationships among the members of this community as well as enhance peoples understanding of themselves and the relationships that they share with people. ',320),
(366330,'Konosioni Induction',cast('2014-02-14 15:00' as date),cast('2014-02-14 17:00' as date),'Memorial Chapel',NULL,NULL,'THS','New members of Konosioni are traditionally selected in the spring of each academic year. After being selected, new members are inducted into the honor society by current Konosioni members. It is a time to acknowledge their outstanding leadership, and their dedicated service to the community and preservation of tradition.  ',430),
(375368,'Spring Party Weekend 2014',cast('2014-04-25 17:00' as date),cast('2014-04-27 01:00' as date),'Sanford Field House/Broad Street',NULL,NULL,'SAA',NULL,180),
(375550,'Hudson IV Tournament',cast('2014-03-28 12:15' as date),cast('2014-03-30 19:00' as date),'Hudson University',NULL,NULL,'DS','For that past four years the Hudson IV British Parliamentary Debate Tournament has drawn teams from the US, Canada and abroad. Past champions include Sydney University Union, University of Pennsylvania, and University of Otago. At a minimum, come see the Championship Round on 03/30 (tournament schedule below).Selected rounds will be livestreamed and can be viewed live on any internet-connected device.Tournament Schedule:Saturday (March 29)Opening Ceremonies 9:45-11:45 Round 111:45-1:45 Round 22:45-4:45 Round 34:45-6:45 Round 4Sunday (March 30)9:00-11:00 Round 5Break Announcement11:30-1:30 Quarterfinal (Livestreamed)2:30-4:30 Semi-Final (Livestreamed)4:30-6:30 Final (Livestreamed)',580),
(375554,'Mediterranean Model United Nations',cast('2014-03-28 15:30' as date),cast('2014-03-30 15:30' as date),'Menton, France',NULL,NULL,'MUN','MEDMUN is a Model United Nations Conference dedicated to the Middle-East and the Mediterranean region. It is hosted by the Sciences Po College, Middle East and Mediterranean campus in Menton, France, and aims to tackle some of the numerous issues facing this region today. It is a chance to understand the complexity of the United Nations mission in the Middle-East and the Mediterranean region.'||chr(10)||'Normally our club attends Worlds MUN hosted by Harvard, but due to an increase of applicants our team was waitlisted and decided it was not worth waiting to see if we got in to plan our trip.',480),
