(404087,'The Supreme Court and the Future of Money in Politics',cast('2014-04-14 16:15' as date),cast('2014-04-14 16:45' as date),'Persson 06',NULL,NULL,'DM','Professors Johnston and Mandle will discuss the recent Supreme Court decision in McCutcheon vs. Federal Election Commission and what it means for the future of politics in the U.S. - and for members of the Hudson community.',null),
(404756,'Hudson Women in Business Fall 2014 Coffee Hours',cast('2014-09-17 20:00' as date),cast('2014-09-17 20:00' as date),'Batza Room- Case Library',NULL,NULL,'HWIB','Hudson Women in Business Coffee Hours include presentations on a number of topics related to business and professionalism. Most Coffee Hours also feature a short skype session with a different alumna to discuss her experiences after Hudson. Coffee Hours are open to all students interested in learning more about professional skills and/or the business world.',270),
(404760,'Hudson Women in Business Fall 2014 Immersion Trip',cast('2014-10-02 15:00' as date),cast('2014-10-04 15:30' as date),'New York, NY',NULL,NULL,'HWIB','Immersion trip to New York City featuring site visits, a networking reception with alumnae, and alumnae led workshops.',220),
(406027,'Hilarity For Charity Comedy Show',cast('2014-04-10 19:00' as date),cast('2014-04-10 19:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,NULL,'CG','Come join Charred Goosebeak and Theta Chi for our Hilarity for Charity Fundraising event. We''re raising money for Alzheimer''s awarness and research for Seth Rogen''s organization. Please drop by for our comedy show, and we promise you''ll enjoy it.',null),
(406919,'What You Need to Do NOW to Get Into the Best MBA Program',cast('2014-04-13 13:00' as date),cast('2014-04-13 13:30' as date),'Persson 27',NULL,NULL,'HWIB','Hudson Finance Club and Hudson Women in Business will host Shawn O''Connor, author of Forbes'' column "The Launching Pad," MBA from Harvard Business School (Baker Scholar), Founder/CEO of Stratus Prep, and admissions counselor with over ten years of test prep and admissions experience.The presentation and QandA will be held in Persson 27 at 1:00 PM on Sunday, April 13th.Shawn will discuss:- What top business schools are looking for- Leveraging your college experiences- Optimizing your out-of-classroom activities- The importance of admissions essays- The role of the GMAT in today''s admissions game- How to carefully cultivate and groom your recommendersAll students are welcome - please RSVP here so we know how much pizza to get!https://www.eventbrite.com/e/what-you-need-to-do-now-to-get-into-the-best-mba-program-tickets-11184891311We look forward to seeing you!',400),
(411836,'Hudson Women in Business Coffee Hour',cast('2014-04-23 17:45' as date),cast('2014-04-23 18:00' as date),'Batza Room (Case 560)',NULL,NULL,'HWIB','Carrie Keating, Professor of Psychology at Hudson, will be leading our final coffee of the semester. Professor Keating will teach us about body language and how to present yourself in interviews, networking, and in the workplace. This will include information about ''on the job'' body language, such as how to assert yourself as an intern to gain more responsibility. Dinner will be served!',540),
(445088,'Matt the Knife at Donovan''s Pub',cast('2014-08-30 21:00' as date),cast('2014-08-30 21:30' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,NULL,'DP','Come down to Donovan''s Pub for our first show of the year! Illusionist / Comedian Matt the Knife is sure to entertain.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'FREE admission. SUN Cash, Flex, cash and credit accepted for food and drink purchases.',400),
(445802,'BBQ On the Quad',cast('2014-08-28 18:00' as date),cast('2014-08-28 19:00' as date),'Residential Quad',NULL,NULL,'SAA','Come to the residential quad to get free BBQ food from local Holy Smokes BBQ! Food options include pulled pork and BBQ chicken with delicious sides. Come while it''s still hot!',null),
(448863,'SGA Ice Cream Social',cast('2014-09-02 15:00' as date),cast('2014-09-02 15:30' as date),'Outside of the Hudson Memorial Chapel/Academic Quad',NULL,NULL,'SGA','Do you like ice cream? Even better: Do you like FREE ice cream? If so, come to the Chapel steps this Tuesday at 3 pm to learn more about Student Goverment Association initiatives and how you can get involved!',null),
(453226,'Karaoke Night at Donovan''s Pub',cast('2014-09-06 21:00' as date),cast('2014-09-06 22:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,NULL,'SAA','Grab your friends for a fun night of karaoke at Donovan''s Pub! The kitchen will be open for food and drinks, the game room is stocked with air hockey, foosball, pool, and darts if your vocal cords need a break, and it is sure to be a good time!',null),
(454368,'Student Involvement Fair',cast('2014-09-10 16:00' as date),cast('2014-09-10 17:00' as date),'Academic Quad, Rain Location--Huntington Gym',NULL,NULL,'SGA',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'More than 150 organizations from ALANA, CLSI, COVE, the Office of the Chaplains, Alumni Fund, and more are participating in the Student Activities Fair to get you ACTIVE on campus! Try new things, meet new people, explore your interests! Check out all the different booths, and sign up for any groups you may be interested in. If you have any questions, please reach out to the SGA Liaison to Student Organizations, David Kim (sgaliaison@hudson.edu).'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',325),
(458834,'Hudson Marketing Speaker Series - Samantha McDermott',cast('2014-10-05 16:30' as date),cast('2014-10-05 16:30' as date),'Persson 27 Basement Auditorium',NULL,NULL,'HSMC','Hudson Marketing Speaker Series: Samantha McDermott'||chr(10)||'The Hudson Marketing Speaker Series, hosted by the Hudson Marketing Club, aims to connect current students with successful Coglate alums in the marketing field. Speakers will discuss their transition from studying in a liberal arts enviroment to working in a corporate/business setting. These speakers have experience in all types of marketing: advertising, branding, PR, communications, and business.'||chr(10)||'Most of our speakers will give their talks through Skype, but our headlining speaker, Samantha McDermott ''94, plans to fly to campus from California to discuss her career and give advice for like-minded individuals who are curious or passionate about the marketing field. As the current Chief Marketing Officer of a prominent law firm on the West Coast and former owner of her own marketing firm, Samantha McDermott has a wealth of information to share, just two decades out of Hudson. In her approximately 45-minute talk, Samantha will cover many topics, including how she became interested in marketing and communications at Hudson, how she landed her first job, and her vast knowledge about social media networking and corporate law marketing.While Hudson does not offer many classes relevant to marketing, Samantha McDermott''s talk will give students a chance to learn about that industry in a way that the Hudson classroom is not really able to cover. With the growth of social media and rising demand for marketing consultants for just about any established business, a marketing career can be an attractive, interesting, and lucrative option for Hudson students, and Samantha McDermott''s talk will help inspire students to look into marketing jobs and internships, and fine-tune their social media presence to prepare students for success after Hudson.',520),
(458886,'Model United Nations Conferences',cast('2014-10-02 12:00' as date),cast('2014-10-02 12:00' as date),'Boston University, Yale, UPenn, Lima',NULL,NULL,'MUN','MUN conferences for the fall semester',525),
(458889,'North American Debate Championships at HWS',cast('2014-10-24 17:00' as date),cast('2014-10-26 14:30' as date),'Hobart and William Smith Colleges',NULL,NULL,'DS','Hobart Williams and Smith Colleges will be hosting a British Parliamentary Debate Tournament from October 24th, 2014 to October 26th, 2014. The tournament will have six preliminary rounds followed with elimination rounds beginning at quarterfinals. The North American Championships will be at HWS this year. It is very important for institutional rankings. It is also a fairly local tournament which provides both new and experienced debaters the opportunity to compete against some the best debaters in the country. ',650),
(458890,'Yale University Invitational',cast('2014-10-02 17:00' as date),cast('2014-10-05 16:00' as date),'Yale University',NULL,NULL,'DS','The Yale Invitational Touranament brings some of the most prestigious debaters from around the world to the United States. It gives all the members who attend the opportunity to compete against the very best. Featuring six preliminary rounds of debate, the tournament then breaks to quarterfinals. ',600),
(458891,'Bard College Season Opener',cast('2014-09-19 17:00' as date),cast('2014-09-21 16:00' as date),'Bard College',NULL,NULL,'DS','The Season Opener at Bard College is one of the premier tournaments in the Northeast with an opportunity for experienced debaters to prepare for the upcoming season and a welcoming atmosphere for new participants. It will feature five preliminary rounds of debate followed by a break to quarterfinals.',450),
