(474887,'Ebola in Africa: Deadly Threat or Media Hype?',cast('2014-09-18 11:15' as date),cast('2014-09-18 11:15' as date),'Lawrence 105 (Ho Lecture Room)',NULL,NULL,'HGHC','Ebola has been prominently in the news recently, with over 2000 cases this year in western Africa. This outbreak has raised many questions, including: where does Ebola come from; how does it cause disease; and how it is transmitted? Why has the current outbreak has gained such a high level of attention? Is Ebola a threat to a wider region of Africa or even the US? Associate Professor Geoff Holm will answer these questions and more about the biology and epidemiology of Ebola at a Brown Bag Lunch, sponsored by the Hudson Global Health Initiative. Thursday, September 18, at 11:20 in the Ho Lecture Room in Lawrence Hall.',350),
(481364,'SGA Sponsored Bonfire',cast('2014-09-26 16:30' as date),cast('2014-09-26 17:00' as date),'Old Golf Course',NULL,NULL,'SGA','The Bonfire out at the old golf course. Behind Stillman and Andrews at the top of the old golf course aka the field of dreams. It''s from 4:30-6pm on Friday. Grab a marshmallow and hang out with some of the cool kids from SGA by the fire this Friday at the old golf course. Bring your own anything you want!'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',60),
(490454,'Hudson Weekly Athletic Events',cast('2014-10-03 19:00' as date),cast('2014-10-04 18:00' as date),'Reid Building',NULL,NULL,'RDR','Come out and support your Hudson Raiders this weekend, FREE GILLIGANS ICE CREAM at Volleyball on 10.3 for the first 100 fans at 7pm.  GO GATE!',500),
(507941,'The Hudson Hookup Culture Brown Bag',cast('2014-10-23 11:30' as date),cast('2014-10-23 12:00' as date),'O''Conner Campus Center','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'BROS','Brothers and SGA presents its semi-annual brown bag on The Hudson Hookup Culture in the Coop TV on Thursday October 23 at 11:30am. We will have free Royal Indian Food.'||chr(10)||'The goal is of the Brown Bag is to foster meaningful and insightful discussions about taboo conversations regarding sex, gender, sexual orientation, sexual desires, urges, and fears in a safe productive manner.'||chr(10)||'We want to equip students with definitions and the language to talk about "hooking up" and to nuance the perception that people do not date at Hudson and why he/she/ze may choose to engage in this culture or not.'||chr(10)||'We hope everyone leaves the meeting learning the complexities and different factors that create and perpetuate the hook up culture.',null),
