(9280729,'Sex Museum: The Intersections of Our Bodies',cast('2023-09-20 17:00' as date),cast('2023-09-20 18:00' as date),'O''Connor Campus Center - COOP','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'ALANA','Another sex museum opens it''s doors!'||chr(10)||'This chapter of the Sex Museum is focused on intersections of our bodies, its cultural and social representations, as well as our perceptions of the body.'||chr(10)||'Come and learn about:'||chr(10)||'- Healthy relationships;'||chr(10)||'- Body and its spectrum;'||chr(10)||'- How to address and prevent domestic / intimate / dating violence;'||chr(10)||'- Multiple forms of intimacy etc.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'There will be various activities, giveaways, and a lot of fun!',null),
(9408266,'Zoom Interview with Mike Levinger from Hubspot',cast('2023-09-20 19:00' as date),cast('2023-09-20 19:00' as date),'Persson 210','Group Business',NULL,'HSMC','We will be having a zoom interview with alumni Mike Levinger from Hubspot. He will discuss his role in business development / sales and marketing.'||chr(10)||' ',500),
(945052,'Host Your Own Shabbat',cast('2016-11-04 12:00' as date),cast('2016-11-04 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Shabbat: The Hudson Jewish Union is requesting funding for Shabbat dinners hosted individually by Jewish students in order to prepare for and celebrate one of the most important days and oldest traditions in Judaism. Shabbat is the most holy Jewish. Host your own Shabbat draws in other community members to learn about Shabbat in ways that are practices by different people.  For example, some people might do a reform service while other might perform a more conservative service.  This is key to provide a broad perspective regarding Jewish Life. Specifically, all funds will be going to the food costs and dinner associated with the traditional Sabbath meal as well as the traditions we practice such as lighting candles and drinking grape juice (Not wine).',40),
(945056,'Shabbat',cast('2016-09-02 12:00' as date),cast('2016-09-02 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Shabbat: The Hudson Jewish Union is requesting funding for Shabbat dinners in order to prepare for and celebrate one of the most important days and oldest traditions in Judaism. Shabbat is the most holy Jewish holiday and we invite everyone in the surrounding area including the town of Hamilton.  We are the only Synagogue within 40 miles of Hamilton.  Specifically, all funds will be going to the food costs and dinner associated with the traditional Sabbath meal as well as the traditions we practice such as lighting candles and drinking grape juice (Not wine)',70),
(945063,'Community Shabbat',cast('2016-09-09 12:00' as date),cast('2016-09-09 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Shabbat: The Hudson Jewish Union is requesting funding for Shabbat dinners in order to prepare for and celebrate one of the most important days and oldest traditions in Judaism. Shabbat is the most holy Jewish holiday and we invite everyone in the surrounding area including the town of Hamilton.  We are the only Synagogue within 40 miles of Hamilton.  Specifically, all funds will be going to the food costs and dinner associated with the traditional Sabbath meal as well as the traditions we practice such as lighting candles and drinking grape juice (Not wine).  Our community shabbats typically bring in double the normal amount of people thus not having the same people every week.  These shabbats include Shabbat 101, Faculty Shabbat, and BBQ Shabbat.  These are also a great way to get the freshman involved in Jewish life as they are within the first few weeks to month of the semester.',345),
(9580208,'Zoom Discussion Panel - IBM and Pilothouse',cast('2023-11-30 16:30' as date),cast('2023-11-30 18:00' as date),'020 Lawrence Hall - Humanities Auditorium','Group Business',NULL,'HSMC','Join the Sales and Marketing Club as we welcome Dan Norcia and Annie Eadon. Dan is the director of partnerships at Pilothouse, a high-level digital marketing agency. Annie works with sales enablement strategy and experiences at IBM, a global technology innovator. All are welcome!'||chr(10)||' ',340),
