(1033061,'Ghost Hunting with John Zaffis',cast('2016-10-27 20:00' as date),cast('2016-10-27 21:00' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','Join us for a ~spooky~ night. John Zaffis, the self-described Godfather of the Paranormal, has been featured on the SyFy Channel, the Discovery Channel, Ghost Hunters, Ghost Adventures, and Unsolved Mysteries. His research and personal experiences with the supernatural have convinced him that ghost are, in fact, real. Not convinced? Come see him talk live about his experiences! John Zaffis will have a hour talk about ghost hunting in Love Auditorium followed by a tour and ghost hunt of Hudson''s Campus. Love Auditorium, 10/27, 8pm.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' ',470),
(1033139,'Konosioni Field Day',cast('2016-08-24 15:00' as date),cast('2016-08-24 16:00' as date),'Whitnall Field','Social',NULL,'THS','Show your newfound love for Hudson by competing in one of our longest standing traditions. Residence halls will compete against each other for prizes and glory. Featured event includes tug of war and free food. Be sure to wear the right colors  see the posters around campus or your Community Leader for details. Bring your friends and your game face. Sponsored by Konosioni Senior Honor Society. (Whitnall Field).',450),
(1047900,'SORT BACK TO SCHOOL SLEEPOVER',cast('2016-09-30 20:00' as date),cast('2016-09-30 20:00' as date),'wmst','Social',NULL,'SRT','The SORT sleepover is a time to bond and get to know other students on campus. ',120),
(1119382,'Harry Potter Week',cast('2016-11-11 20:00' as date),cast('2016-11-17 23:30' as date),'Hudson University','Arts',NULL,'SAA','This event will take place over the course of the week leading up to CAB Take Two''s advanced premier of Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them. Several campus groups will be coming together to host the week''s events that include a Yule Ball with ''Gate Night Friday 11/11, Tea Reading with Tea Club Monday 11/14, Wizard Chess with TGA Tuesday 11/15, Trivia Night at Donovan''s Pub Wednesday 11/16, Quidditch tournament with Club Sports Thursday 11/17.',null),
(1121876,'ACF Fall Northeast at Columbia',cast('2016-11-04 16:00' as date),cast('2016-11-06 19:00' as date),'Columbia University','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HQB','On November 5th, 2016, there will be a collegiate Quiz Bowl Tournament held by the University of Columbia in NYC. This is a really exciting opportunity for the up and coming Hudson Trivia Club. Members who participate in the tournament would leave Hudson on Friday, November 4th (departure time is pending upon members'' schedules) and would return Sunday, November 6th late afternoon. The tournament is to be held at Columbia University in Hamilton Hall on Saturday, November 5th. The check in for the tournament will be from 8:00-8:30 am and the games will begin between 8:45-9:00 am.  Once the tournament is over, there will be ample time to explore New York City. We will stay at a hotel in NYC courtesy of Hudson and will allocate money for food to members for the weekend.   ',220),
(1136022,'Newman Lunch',cast('2017-01-30 12:15' as date),cast('2017-01-30 13:15' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'NC','The Newman Community hopes to continue putting on a successful weekly lunch series this spring. The series would feature outside speakers, Hudson faculty, and Hudson students leading discussions about the Catholic faith and the Church. Topics would vary each week, but center on central teachings and practices of the Catholic Church. The lunch would be every Monday from 12:15-1:10 and would be catered by local restaurants. About 75 people a week usually come to these lunches.',null),
