(1163418,'Snowshoeing at Stony Pond',cast('2017-02-04 11:00' as date),cast('2017-02-04 17:00' as date),'Stony Pond State Forest','Social',NULL,'HIKE','We will be taking 3 cars (15 people) and going on a snowshoeing excursion at Stony Pond State Forest! ',150),
(1163424,'Snowman Making Outing',cast('2017-02-11 13:00' as date),cast('2017-02-11 14:00' as date),'Harry Lang Cross Country and Fitness Trails','Social',NULL,'HIKE','We will host an event open to all members of the hiking club on the field above the graveyard where we will be making snowmen. We hope to provide hot chocolate and have a competition where the winners get $10 gift cards to a restaurant downtown (limit of 3 people per snowman). Our alternate date if we do not receive funding is March 4th.',300),
(1248463,'QueerFest',cast('2017-04-04 16:30' as date),cast('2017-04-04 18:30' as date),'Golden Auditorium / The Edge','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'LAMBDA','Queerfest Keynote Featuring Kat Blaque and Family Dinner:  Kat Blaque is a transgender African American feminist vlogger and YouTube personality. Blaque has a weekly YouTube series called True Tea where she answers questions that viewers send her about racism, transphobia, black culture and several other topics.Blaque has made guest appearances on several other YouTuber''s videos such as the BuzzFeed video about gender pronouns. She has also collaborated with YouTubers such as Franchesca "Chescaleigh" Ramsey and Ari Fitz. During her visit, Blaque will give a keynote address discussing being a member of the LGBTQ community and being a YouTube personality. This will be followed by a casual Family Dinner with Blaque in the Edge Cafe. Co-Sponsored by Commons Two, Film and Media Studies, Sisters of the Round Table, Black Student Union, and The Center for Womens Studies. '||chr(10)||'Open Safe Zone: An open safezone will be one of the final events of queerfest.  This annual safezone is open to the entire community and is cosponsored by LGBTQ initiatives and queerfest. Co-Sponsored by Haven'||chr(10)||'Drag Ball: The annual culminating event of Queerfest. Each year, Hudson students host and compete in a drag competition, which is then followed by a dance party, as a celebration of Queerfest.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',500),
(1248464,'QueerFest',cast('2017-04-06 18:30' as date),cast('2017-04-06 19:30' as date),'Lathrop 207','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'LAMBDA','Queerfest Keynote Featuring Kat Blaque and Family Dinner:  Kat Blaque is a transgender African American feminist vlogger and YouTube personality. Blaque has a weekly YouTube series called True Tea where she answers questions that viewers send her about racism, transphobia, black culture and several other topics.Blaque has made guest appearances on several other YouTuber''s videos such as the BuzzFeed video about gender pronouns. She has also collaborated with YouTubers such as Franchesca "Chescaleigh" Ramsey and Ari Fitz. During her visit, Blaque will give a keynote address discussing being a member of the LGBTQ community and being a YouTube personality. This will be followed by a casual Family Dinner with Blaque in the Edge Cafe. Co-Sponsored by Commons Two, Film and Media Studies, Sisters of the Round Table, Black Student Union, and The Center for Womens Studies. '||chr(10)||'Open Safe Zone: An open safezone will be one of the final events of queerfest.  This annual safezone is open to the entire community and is cosponsored by LGBTQ initiatives and queerfest. Co-Sponsored by Haven'||chr(10)||'Drag Ball: The annual culminating event of Queerfest. Each year, Hudson students host and compete in a drag competition, which is then followed by a dance party, as a celebration of Queerfest.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',500),
(1248465,'QueerFest',cast('2017-04-14 20:00' as date),cast('2017-04-14 22:00' as date),'The Edge','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'LAMBDA','Queerfest Keynote Featuring Kat Blaque and Family Dinner:  Kat Blaque is a transgender African American feminist vlogger and YouTube personality. Blaque has a weekly YouTube series called True Tea where she answers questions that viewers send her about racism, transphobia, black culture and several other topics.Blaque has made guest appearances on several other YouTuber''s videos such as the BuzzFeed video about gender pronouns. She has also collaborated with YouTubers such as Franchesca "Chescaleigh" Ramsey and Ari Fitz. During her visit, Blaque will give a keynote address discussing being a member of the LGBTQ community and being a YouTube personality. This will be followed by a casual Family Dinner with Blaque in the Edge Cafe. Co-Sponsored by Commons Two, Film and Media Studies, Sisters of the Round Table, Black Student Union, and The Center for Womens Studies. '||chr(10)||'Open Safe Zone: An open safezone will be one of the final events of queerfest.  This annual safezone is open to the entire community and is cosponsored by LGBTQ initiatives and queerfest. Co-Sponsored by Haven'||chr(10)||'Drag Ball: The annual culminating event of Queerfest. Each year, Hudson students host and compete in a drag competition, which is then followed by a dance party, as a celebration of Queerfest.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',500),
(1283483,'Charity Week 2017',cast('2017-04-03 11:00' as date),cast('2017-04-06 18:30' as date),'Hudson University','Fundraising','Concert/Music','BROS','Brothers Charity Week is an annual program composed of several activities placed throughout the week, with the intent of raising money for the surrounding Hamilton community and/or a worthwhile, larger global charitable organization beginning April 3 until April 7, 2017'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'On Monday, April 3, Brothers will start the week with a bake sale in the Coop during the lunch hours. The goods will be homemade in either the ALANA, Drake, or Edge Cafe Kitchens. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'On Tuesday, April 4, Brothers will host a Video Game Night in conjunction with Smash Club in the Coop TV Room at 8pm. There will be 4-5 consoles set up with controllers and monitors, and attendees will be able to play a number of popular multiplayer games including Super Smash Bros. and NBA 2K17. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'On Wednesday April 5, Brothers will host a Night of Live Entertainment in Donovans Pub at 9-10 pm. We will partner with Charred Goosebeak and Broad Street Records to have a range of comic and musical performances. CLSI will contribute pub food.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'On Thursday April 6, Brothers will host a 3v3 Basketball Tournament in Huntington Gymnasium at 5:30pm. Teams and donations will be registered in the Coop the week prior to the event, and funding will go towards a prize for the winner as well as refreshments (Gatorade) for players. '||chr(10)||'These events are suggested/recommended donation.',null),
(173302,'Tacos Con Los Santos',cast('2012-11-01 18:00' as date),cast('2012-11-01 20:00' as date),'COOP',NULL,'Religious/Spiritual','NC','Tacos Con Los Santos will be a campus-wide event hosted by the Newman Community to celebrate All Saints Day. It will bring together students with different beliefs to learn about  extraordinary saints of the Catholic Church while enjoying catered Mexican food. Tacos Con Los Santos will be an engaging experience for everyone who attends. It will offer presentations on what it means to be a saint, how saints are viewed by catholics, and what made the saints extraordinary people. These presentations will be lead in an interactive way by students involved in the Newman Community. There will be a saints trivia game with prizes. ',320),
(200174,'CHOP presents National Hunger and Homelessness Awareness Week',cast('2012-11-12 00:00' as date),cast('2012-11-16 23:00' as date),'Various',NULL,'Volunteer and Community Service ','HHOP','The Hudson Hunger Outreach Program presents National Hunger and Homelessness Awareness Week, November 12th - November 16th'||chr(10)||'Events throughout the week include:'||chr(10)||'Tuesday, November 13th: OxFam''s Hunger Banquet, 6-7:30 PM in ALANA'||chr(10)||'Wednesday, November 14th: Habitat for Humanity''s Gingerbread House Building Competition, 6-8 PM in the HOP'||chr(10)||'Wednesday, November 14th: CHOP''s Scrape the Plate event at Frank Dining Hall'||chr(10)||'Friday, November 16th: COVE Friday sponsored by CHOP, 12:15 in the COVE lounge'||chr(10)||'Come listen to Jodee Osborne from Community Action Partnership speak about local poverty issues in Central New York. Jodee is CAP''s Nutrition Outreach and Education Program Coordinator for Madison County. Lunch will be served!'||chr(10)||'Friday, November 16th: The Wellness Institute''s Family Fun Night, 6:30-8 PM in Sanford Field House'||chr(10)||' ',300),
