(8864138,'Friday Party w/ Friends',cast('2023-02-10 22:00' as date),cast('2023-02-11 02:00' as date),'Beta Theta Pi','Social',NULL,'BTP',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'On Friday, February 10th, the brothers of Beta Theta Pi plan to host a dry event in their basement, main entry area, library, and living room. Attendees will include the brothers of the house and close friends on campus. We will provide a variety of non-alcoholic beverages and snacks in the spaces being used for the event. There is no theme yet for this party, and our dining room setup will include speakers and lighting fixtures. We have one student planned to play music throughout the duration of the event, and attendees will be able to dance and catch up. Two student monitors will be at the door for the duration of the event, in addition to having sober monitors, and we will also provide snacks and water for all guests. Attendance will not exceed 160, and the event will run from 10:00 PM to 2:00 AM. Jason Chapis, Ryan Bush, Ryan Landrigan and Max Parrott will be the social hosts for the event.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',290),
(886427,'Refugee Health Brown Bag',cast('2016-03-24 12:00' as date),cast('2016-03-24 12:00' as date),'Lathrop 207','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HGHC','A representative from the Mohawk Valley Resource Center for Refugees will speak about refugee health, and the issues associated with managing it, in both a local and global context. Lunch will be provided from Hamilton Eatery. ',450),
(8906718,'Charter Day: Afternoon of Service',cast('2023-03-03 12:15' as date),cast('2023-03-03 16:00' as date),'COVE Lounge - 109 Lathrop Hall','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','COVE','In honor of Charter Day, the COVE is sponsoring a campus-wide Afternoon of Service on Friday, March 3rd, 2023. All Hudson community members including students, alumni, as well as faculty and staff are invited to volunteer with our local community partners. Transportation and lunch will be provided. Please wear clothing you are comfortable getting dirty. Registration ends on Wednesday, March 1st, 2023 at 5:00pm.',null),
(8959086,'Tach Taproom',cast('2023-03-08 10:00' as date),cast('2023-03-09 01:00' as date),'Good Nature Brewery','Social',NULL,'TC','An event a the Good Nature Brewery with a few of our friends',375),
(8962263,'The Stevenson Prize for Expository Speaking (Hosted by Hudson Debate Society)',cast('2023-04-28 16:30' as date),cast('2023-04-28 17:30' as date),'Lawrence 020','Social',NULL,'DS',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'The Stevenson Prize for Expository Speaking is open to all currently enrolled'||chr(10)||'Hudson students. Each contestant will present a research paper:'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'That is not co-authored'||chr(10)||'That is not the result of collaborative research'||chr(10)||'That is based on independent research conducted by the contestant at Hudson University in connection with coursework'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'The presentation will be expository. The speech should be audience centered, anticipating as much as possible the interests and abilities of the assembled audience.'||chr(10)||'The audience should not be addressed as expert bearers of technical knowledge in the particular discipline where in the research is grounded (e.g. Biology, History, Philosophy, etc.).'||chr(10)||'Presentations will be evaluated by a panel of several faculty members, and the top several presentations for each class year will receive monetary prizes. '||chr(10)||'For further details or to sign up, please contact debatesociety@hudson.edu'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' ',350),
(8962266,'The Kingsford Speaking Competition (Hosted by Hudson Debate Society)',cast('2023-03-20 16:30' as date),cast('2023-03-20 17:30' as date),'Lathrop 207','Social',NULL,'DS','Each contestant will deliver a speech that intends to persuade the immediate audience to take action as a step toward the solution of a problem made salient by the speech. The action step must be generally within the means of the audience (i.e. possible), clearly linked to affecting the problems solution, motivated by needs/desires apparently aroused by the speech, and perceived as good (expedient, and appropriate) by virtue of its consistency with the audiences operative hierarchy of values. Speeches will be evaluated by a panel of several faculty members, and the top several speeches for each class year will receive monetary prizes. '||chr(10)||'For further details or to sign up, please contact debatesociety@hudson.edu',380),
(8962267,'The Lewis Orator Prize (Hosted by Hudson Debate Society)',cast('2023-04-05 16:30' as date),cast('2023-04-05 17:30' as date),'Lathrop 207','Social',NULL,'DS','Each contestant will deliver an original speech that is centered on a one-word prompt (this year''s prompt is TIME) published by the competitions organizers prior to the competition.  The prompt must be used in the speech as a vehicle to elucidate some aspect of social reality in a new and memorable way. Speeches will be evaluated by a panel of several faculty members, and the top several speeches for each class year will receive monetary prizes. '||chr(10)||'More Information:https://docs.google.com/document/d/15SOIww8VkN5ehdmPOYlUsNM_6H4mkdK5/edit?usp=sharingandouid=108829104633921500605andrtpof=trueandsd=true'||chr(10)||'Sign-up Here:https://forms.gle/8ApRJ6bVyp7vDAVf7'||chr(10)||'For any questions, please contact debatesociety@hudson.edu. ',550),
