(9540662,'Fall on the Farm and Pumpkin Smash',cast('2023-10-21 14:00' as date),cast('2023-10-21 15:30' as date),'Donovan Pub','Social',NULL,'SAA','Looking for something to do this weekend away from campus?  Introduce the Fall on the Farm event! SAA is happy to sponsor students on a trip to Sugar Hill Farm. Admission covers tractor drawn hayrides, corn maze, access to the u-pick patch and pumpkin smash, lots of free barnyard games (hay bale tower, gravity wagon basketball, and candy corn ring toss), and one u-pick pumpkin (for you to smash or take home)!There is no sign up. Please show up to Donovan before 2pm this Saturday and bus will return to Hudson around 4:30pm.',300),
(9542329,'Origami Lucky Stars Making Event',cast('2023-10-27 15:00' as date),cast('2023-10-27 15:00' as date),'Lawrence Room 107 - Japanese Studies Center','Social',NULL,'TTC','On Friday, October 27, we are hosting an Origami Lucky Stars Making event from 3 - 4 p.m. in Lawrence Room 107 Japanese Center (new location!) These origami lucky stars represent a special gift of love and good luck (more information here).'||chr(10)||'As always, everyone is welcome! We will have tea, snacks, origami papers, and jars for you to make these lovely star jars for yourself or gifts to friends and family members!',55),
