(9990821,'2024 Milmoe Workshop in Investigative Journalism and Journalist Ethics',cast('2024-02-29 18:30' as date),cast('2024-02-29 20:00' as date),'Ho 101 Lecture Room','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HMN','Rebekah F. Ward, a multimedia journalist specializing in Climate and Environment at the Houston Chronicle and member of the Class of 2013 of Hudson University, will be visiting Hudson to share her extensive experience and knowledge in journalism. With a rich background in fact-checking, investigative reporting, and freelance writing for distinguished outlets such as France 24, Reuters, and the Overseas Crime and Corruption Reporting Project, Ward brings invaluable insights into investigative journalism''s ethics and integrity. Her session promises to enlighten Hudson''s current students, aspiring writers, and journalists with lessons from her extensive career. This event is sponsored by the Cornelius (Laddie) Milmoe ''30 endowment and the Office of Student Involvement and hosted by the Hudson Maroon-News. ',460),
(1025799,'MSA Brown Bag Series',cast('2016-09-09 12:00' as date),cast('2016-12-09 13:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'HMSA','A series of Brown Bag Talks on Topics related to Islam designed to educate Hudson students about Islam and it''s impact it has on our society today. ',420),
(1025805,'Eid',cast('2016-04-29 18:00' as date),cast('2016-04-29 20:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Spirituality',NULL,'HMSA','The Eid Al-Fitr is yearly an Islamic Festival celebrated throughout the Islamic communities and is the epitome of Islamic Festival',null),
(1089744,'Islam and Homosexuality',cast('2016-10-21 12:00' as date),cast('2016-10-21 12:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'HMSA','Columbia University Chaplain Mouhamadou Diagne will talk about Islam and Homosexuality. He will also lead the Friday Prayer for the Muslim Students.',null),
(1157515,'MSA Brown Bag Series',cast('2017-01-27 12:00' as date),cast('2017-04-28 12:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'HMSA','A series of Brown Bag Talks on Topics related to Islam designed to educate Hudson students about Islam and it''s impact it has on our society today. The Brown Bags will focus on the topics of Sunni Shia Split, What Trump Presidency Means for Muslims, Sharia Law, Islam and other Abrahamic Religions. The topics are subjected to change based on speaker availability. ',500),
(1157533,'Mehdi Hasan Talk',cast('2017-03-16 12:00' as date),cast('2017-03-16 12:00' as date),'Chapel','Spirituality',NULL,'HMSA','Mehdi Hasan is a renown British scholar. A graduate of Oxford, Mehdi Hasan moved on to become a political journalist, broadcaster, and author. He has two shows on Al Jazeera English, UpFront and Head to Head. Mehdi specializes in issues regarding Islam and Muslims and has a very strong fan base online.',760),
