(945040,'Spoken Word Artist Micah Bournes',cast('2016-09-18 18:30' as date),cast('2016-09-18 18:30' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Spirituality',NULL,'UC','Acclaimed spoken word poet Micah Bournes will guest-lead University Churchs Sunday night worship, providing students and Hudson community members with the unique opportunity to worship God through a relatively newer medium. Micah will also lead a Monday lunch, during which he will perform some of his work and will discuss how being a Christian impacts his role as poet, as well as how he seeks to provide fellowship through his work.',445),
(945041,'Spoken Word Artist Micah Bournes',cast('2016-09-19 12:15' as date),cast('2016-09-19 12:15' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'UC','Acclaimed spoken word poet Micah Bournes will guest-lead University Churchs Sunday night worship, providing students and Hudson community members with the unique opportunity to worship God through a relatively newer medium. Micah will also lead a Monday lunch, during which he will perform some of his work and will discuss how being a Christian impacts his role as poet, as well as how he seeks to provide fellowship through his work.',445),
(945049,'Hanukkah',cast('2016-12-16 12:00' as date),cast('2016-12-16 13:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Hanukkah is the 8 day festival of lights.  For these eight nights, we are requesting funding for celebratory food for menorah lighting ceremonies (which would also serve as study breaks). Here, we plan to have a pre-hanukkah event because hanukkah this year will fall during winter break.  This will include a catered party from Albany (to keep it kosher) and will be co-sponsored with BDS.',225),
(945050,'CJU Fall Speaker',cast('2016-09-30 12:00' as date),cast('2016-09-30 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','We are bringing two speakers to campus: David Makovsky and Ghaith al-Omari.  David is the Ziegler distinguished fellow and director of the Washington Institute for Near East Policy Project on the Middle East Peace Process and an adjunct professor at John Hopkins Universitys school of Advanced International Studies in the Middle Eastern Program.  He is the coauthor of Myths, Illusions, and Peace and appears on the PBS news hour with Jim Lehrer.  Ghaith is a senior fellow at The Washington Institute, is the former executive director of the American Task Force on Palestine. Previously, he served in various positions within the Palestinian Authority, including advisor to the negotiating team during the 1999-2001 permanent-status talks.'||chr(10)||'We are bringing in both experts to have a panel discussion about Israel and Palestine.  We hope that this will bring the campus together not just to have a great discussion but to promote positive dialogue about this issue post event.',570),
(945051,'High Holidays 2016',cast('2016-10-02 12:00' as date),cast('2016-10-02 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Rosh Hashanah: Rosh Hashanah is the Jewish New Year. In most Jewish families, the meal is an integral part of the celebration. The Hudson Jewish Union is requesting funding for Rosh Hashanah dinner in order to honor this tradition following religious services.'||chr(10)||'Yom Kippur: Yom Kippur is part of the High Holidays along with Rosh Hashanah. This is a 25 hour fast marking the most solemn day of the Jewish Calendar.  This full fast (no food or water) is traditionally bracketed by two celebratory meals: one before the fast and a break-fast afterwards.'||chr(10)||'These two holidays are the most holy ones in the Jewish Calendar except for Shabbat. ',260),
(945064,'Sukkot',cast('2016-10-16 12:00' as date),cast('2016-10-16 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Sukkot: Sukkot is the fall harvest festival.  We erect a large temporary structure on the quad and invite other groups to joins us for activities and dinner in it. We are requesting funding for these dinners and other events. We anticipate our BBQ to feed over 100 people as we are coordinating with the Muslims and Newman.',300),
(954490,'CJU Fall Other Misc. Events and Items',cast('2016-09-01 12:00' as date),cast('2016-09-01 12:00' as date),'SAP','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Bagel Brunch: This event is community bonding at the Saperstein Center.  Surprisingly, attendance can top 100 and we unfortunately do run out of bagels some days.  Additionally, we serve a large number of non-Jews thus including the whole Hudson community.  In addition to Hudson students, we also serve a large number of the Hamilton community.'||chr(10)||'Havdalah: Havdalah is celebrating the end of the Sabbath (Shabbat).  We host a great group of community members to have a quick service with light food afterward.  '||chr(10)||'Advertising: Costs to provide supplies to get the word out for the whole semesters events.'||chr(10)||'Morning Minyon: Every week, we have a morning service.  This service needs to have at least 10 Jewish adults to happen.  During this service to attract people, we provide coffee and donuts.'||chr(10)||'Knife Sharpening/BBQ Brushes: In order to continue providing low-cost dinners at Shabbat and low-cost meals at our other events, we need to keep our knives sharp.  Due to the frugality of the CJU, we have neglected to sharpen our knives for many years.  We are requesting a small sum of money to sharpen them instead of buying new ones.  Additionally, we are requesting $10 to buy BBQ brushes.'||chr(10)||'Blender: We need a blender to continue providing low-cost dinners at Shabbat and other events.  This will increase the food quality and the speed at which we can operate.',200),
(1025662,'NYC Immersion Trip',cast('2016-10-20 12:00' as date),cast('2016-10-22 13:45' as date),'New York City','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HWIB','This immersion trip will be an educational and networking opportunity for members of Hudson Women in Business, Hudson Consulting Club, and Hudson Finance Club.  Each club will take select, highly motivated members to visit companies in their specific industry and network with alumni.',150),
(1025745,'Fall 2016 Model UN Conferences',cast('2016-10-13 12:00' as date),cast('2016-10-16 12:00' as date),'Boston, MA / Philadelphia, PA / Montreal, Quebec','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'MUN','Hudson Model United Nations would like to attend three competitive conferences this fall: Boston Area Model United Nations (BarMUN) in Boston, run by Boston University, University of Pennsylvania Model UN Conference (UPMUNC) in Philadelphia, and McGill Model United Nations Assembly (McMUN) hosted by McGill University.',390),
(1032777,'Mexico Public Health Immersion Trip',cast('2017-01-08 12:00' as date),cast('2017-01-19 13:00' as date),'Hudson University','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HGHC','The Hudson Global Health Initiative is sponsoring a trip from January 8-January 19 of 2017 where 8 students will be chosen to travel to Northern Mexico. While in Mexico the students will focus on issues of border health, indigenous health, foreign medical school requirements, rural healthcare and the non profit industry. The trip will travel to Juarez, Chihuahua City, the Sierra Tarahumara region, and a variety of other locations. ',210),
