(1241490,'OASIS Family Dinners 2017 Spring',cast('2017-01-29 12:00' as date),cast('2017-05-11 19:00' as date),'WMST','Cultural',NULL,'OASIS','OASIS Family Dinners aim to build a safe space and community within Asian students on campus. We invite all Asian-identifying students to join our Family Dinners. The Family Dinner allows students to share an Asian meal together, connect with other Asian students on campus, and engage in conversations about Asian identities in a relaxed atmosphere.',340),
(1241491,'OASIS Brown Bag Series 2017 Spring',cast('2017-01-29 12:00' as date),cast('2017-05-07 16:00' as date),'WMST','Cultural',NULL,'OASIS','The Brown Bag Series consist of a speech by an invited speaker and discussion with attendees. It opens to all students and professors. The series will touch upon the topics involving gender, sexuality, Asian cultures, culture differences, activism, human rights, etc.. It aims to provide students with novel perspectives and create a safe space for free-talking.',500),
(4892544,'Fraternity Recruitment Information Session',cast('2019-09-10 19:00' as date),cast('2019-09-10 19:00' as date),'Love Auditorium, Olin Hall','Cultural',NULL,'IFC','This will be the information session for all sophomore students interested in Fraternity life. We will inform them of the recruitment week schedule as well as give information about each of the houses that they could potentially join.',null),
(4970072,'Hudson Vietnamese Society Family Dinner',cast('2019-09-28 18:00' as date),cast('2019-09-28 20:00' as date),'OISS kitchen','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Hudson Vietnam Society Catered Dinner aims to present Vietnamese culture, particularly cuisine, in the cross-cultural context of different countries all over the world. Through this family dinner, we hope to engage Hudson students of diverse backgrounds in a relaxing environment to enhance their understanding and appreciation of a different and foreign culture. We also offer an opportunity for Hudson students to exchange stories about their own unique identities.'||chr(10)||'With the introduction of distinctly Vietnamese food, Hudson Vietnam Society invites people from different parts around the world to experience the story of our country through the exquisite signature dishes that have gained much love and admiration.',510),
(5164824,'Vietnamese Traditional Games',cast('2019-11-16 19:00' as date),cast('2019-11-16 21:00' as date),'Jane Pinchin Common Space','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Vietnamese Traditional Games Event introduces members of Hudson University to traditional Vietnamese games including figurine painting and rope skipping. By introducing these traditional games, we aim not only to deepen Hudson students understanding of the Vietnamese culture and traditions that have shaped Vietnamese culture today but also to establish an emotional connection with fellow Hudson students through exciting and engaging activities. ',290),
(525929,'Release Night',cast('2015-02-20 18:45' as date),cast('2015-02-20 20:30' as date),'ALANA Lounge','Cultural',NULL,'BSU','Release Night is an opportunity for students on campus to express themselves and speak on so-cial, political, and economic concerns that they have been pondering. It is a welcoming and en-couraging space for dialogue to occur on the basis of the type of concerns, questions, and aspira-tions that Hudson students raise to one another. The Black Student Union takes great pride in celebrating students voices. Through the hosting of Release Nights we provide this platform.Essentially, it is a chance to gain support and recognition through others about the struggles and achievements that Hudson students may be enduring. Students are provided a support structure, which allows them to openly voice their thoughts without fear of being judged.',300),
(525930,'Joy De Gruy',cast('2015-02-11 18:00' as date),cast('2015-02-11 19:15' as date),'Love Auditorium','Cultural',NULL,'BSU',NULL,null),
(573293,'Anime Boston 2015 trip',cast('2015-04-03 19:00' as date),cast('2015-04-05 17:00' as date),'Hynes Convention Center','Cultural',NULL,'HAS','We will be travelling to Boston and spend two nights and two days at Anime Boston, the Northeast largest anime convention held annually in Massachusetts, USA. The event aims to promote an educational appreciation for Japanese animation, comics, and pop-culture.'||chr(10)||'Members will have the opportunities to explore their areas of interests through nearly 300 industry panels, hands-on workshops, informative interviews, all the while enjoying themselves with their favorite activities, such as drawing, cosplaying and writing.'||chr(10)||'Our event is open to all Hudson students, and we plan to provide transportation for a maximum of 20 people (the capacity of two Hudson vans) through an application form sent to all students in our mailing list and also available to the general student body.',400),
(582660,'Brown Bag: The Indian Ocean World',cast('2015-04-09 12:00' as date),cast('2015-04-09 12:30' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'SACC','The brown bag by Professor Balachandran is meant to spread awareness about South Asian Culture and the interconnectedness of this region in general. Professor Balachandran will talk about The Indian Ocean World which will specifically talk about how the Ocean connects the lives of the many different people living in South Asia and the relationship between these diverse cultures.',440),
(593964,'Africana Women''s Week(s) Keynote: "Redefining Realness: Janet Mock"',cast('2015-03-02 19:00' as date),cast('2015-03-02 20:30' as date),'Love Auditorium','Cultural',NULL,'SRT','Join Sisters of the Round Table as we present Janet Mock. Mock is a writer, speaker, cultural commentator, prominent advocate for trans women''s rights and the New York Times bestselling author of Redefining Realness: My Path to Womanhood, Identity, Love and So Much More. This event will be an interactive discussion exploring womanhood, identity, and solidarity. All are welcome!'||chr(10)||' ',340),
(6426553,'ALANAPalooza',cast('2020-09-11 18:00' as date),cast('2020-09-11 19:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'ALANA','Join ALANA virtually for their signature ALANAPalooza event.  Hear from alumni as well.  This will be a livestream event!',400),
(6508045,'Dolores Huerta Keynote Speaker',cast('2020-10-14 21:00' as date),cast('2020-10-14 21:30' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','Join the Latin American Student Organization in welcoming their Fall 2020 Keynote Speaker, Dolores Huerta.'||chr(10)||'Dolores Huerta will speak on her Journey into Activism during the Civil Rights Movement as a Hispanic/Latina woman, her activism today, and her advice to current organizers and activists.'||chr(10)||'Biography'||chr(10)||'Dolores Huerta is a civil rights activist and community organizer. She has worked for labor rights and social justice for over 50 years. In 1962, she and Cesar Chavez founded the United Farm Workers union. She served as Vice President and played a critical role in many of the unions accomplishments for four decades. In 2002, she received the Puffin/Nation $100,000 prize for Creative Citizenship which she used to establish the Dolores Huerta Foundation (DHF). DHF is connecting groundbreaking community-based organizing to state and national movements to register and educate voters; advocate for education reform; bring about infrastructure improvements in low-income communities; advocate for greater equality for the LGBT community, and create strong leadership development. She has received numerous awards: among them The Eleanor Roosevelt Humans Rights Award from President Clinton in 1998. In 2012 President Obama bestowed Dolores with The Presidential Medal of Freedom, the highest civilian honor in the United States.',875),
(6764831,'ALANA and Mosaic Present: Vietnamese Lantern Making',cast('2021-02-10 17:00' as date),cast('2021-02-10 18:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Join student leaders Alex Tran 22 and Flora Zhang 22 to learn how to make Vietnamese lanterns.  '||chr(10)||'Made possible by a generous gift to the Presidents Discretionary Fund from Gio 94 and Maree Cutaia in support of Mosaic programs.'||chr(10)||'Register for the event here.',450),
(6764840,'ALANA and Mosaic Present: Chinese Calligraphy',cast('2021-02-10 18:00' as date),cast('2021-02-10 19:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Chinese Language Intern, Abby Hsu  (Hsu) , leads a Chinese Calligraphy lesson in honor of the Lunar New Year. During this session you will learn how to write Chinese Characters. Alumni are invited to purchase their own materials and follow along. '||chr(10)||'There will be an opportunity for a limited number of participants to receive immediate feedback, but all are still welcome to join in the lesson.'||chr(10)||'Register for the event here.'||chr(10)||'Please note: 15 calligraphy kits available by ALANA Cultural Center will be made available for current students only. Please sign up using the Google Form to reserve your kit.'||chr(10)||'Chinese Calligraphy Kit Reservation Form: https://forms.gle/nDH2gGcxNkyFv2XA6'||chr(10)||'Made possible by a generous gift to the Presidents Discretionary Fund from Gio 94 and Maree Cutaia in support of Mosaic programs.',185),
(6764902,'ALANA and Mosaic Present: Dumpling Making',cast('2021-02-10 19:00' as date),cast('2021-02-10 20:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Prof. Song will teach us how to make two types of dumplings for Lunar New Year. Participants are invited to purchase items in advance to make alongside Prof. Song, who has provided non-vegetarian and vegetarian recipes. Organization of Asian Sisters in Solidarity (OASIS+) will share live commentary.'||chr(10)||'Register for the event here. All are welcome!',320),
(6776672,'Lantern Release',cast('2021-02-12 17:00' as date),cast('2021-02-12 18:00' as date),'Taylor Lake','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Celebrate the start of the Lunar New Year with us as we release the Vietnamese lanterns we make over Taylor Lake. '||chr(10)||'Please note: Space is limited to 10 people. Please register here. '||chr(10)||'If you are not able to join us in person, please click on the link to the Hudson Vietnamese Society Instagram page to view the release.'||chr(10)||'https://www.instagram.com/hudsonvietnamesesociety/',240),
(6776680,'Happy Lunar New Year! Moving forward into the new year with diligence, persistence, and honesty.',cast('2021-02-12 19:00' as date),cast('2021-02-12 20:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Students from the various regions that celebrate this holiday will share the traditions that are specific to their culture.'||chr(10)||'Register for the event here.',null),
(6776682,'ALANA and Mosaic Present: Japanese Calligraphy',cast('2021-02-12 16:00' as date),cast('2021-02-12 17:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Prof. Yukari Hirata   will lead a Japanese Calligraphy lesson in honor of Lunar New Year.  During this session you will learn how to write Japanese Characters.  Alumni are invited to purchase their own materials and follow along.   If you do not have materials, you can still participate in the lesson. '||chr(10)||'There will be an opportunity for only a limited number of participants to receive immediate feedback, but all are still welcome to join in the lesson.'||chr(10)||'Register for the event here.'||chr(10)||'Please note: 15 calligraphy kits will be made available for current students on campus only.  Please sign up using the Google Form to reserve your kit. '||chr(10)||'Japanese Calligraphy Kit Reservation Form: https://forms.gle/UfGwzPmLjjhs5QBg7'||chr(10)||'Made possible by a generous gift to the Presidents Discretionary Fund from Gio 94 and Maree Cutaia in support of Mosaic programs.',400),
(6944391,'Friday Fun at ALANA',cast('2021-02-26 20:00' as date),cast('2021-02-26 21:30' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center Lounge','Cultural',NULL,'ALANA','Come to ALANA on Friday nights and make crafts, play games or watch movies',null),
(6944392,'Friday Fun at ALANA',cast('2021-03-05 20:00' as date),cast('2021-03-05 21:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center Lounge','Cultural',NULL,'ALANA','Come to ALANA on Friday nights and make crafts, play games or watch movies',null),
(6944393,'Friday Fun at ALANA',cast('2021-03-12 20:00' as date),cast('2021-03-12 21:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center Lounge','Cultural',NULL,'ALANA','Come to ALANA on Friday nights and make crafts, play games or watch movies',null),
(6945095,'Black History Month Everyone is a Scientist',cast('2021-02-24 19:00' as date),cast('2021-02-24 20:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'ALANA','Join ASU and ALANA for a Black History Month dialogue about college social and academic navigation. ',230),
(7065150,'Tea Club Boba Night',cast('2021-04-10 12:00' as date),cast('2021-04-10 12:00' as date),'Alana Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'TTC','Tea Club is having a boba event where we will be distributing boba-making kits to our members. Each person will come and pick up their pre-packaged boba and snacks, which they will be making and eating in their own homes. We will encourage our members to come to the corresponding event which will be held on zoom. Distribution of the boba and snacks will occur at ALANA and people will have to sign up for a time. ',250),
(7072415,'Djali Brown-Cepeda Speaking Event',cast('2021-04-20 18:00' as date),cast('2021-04-20 18:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','LASO invites you to come to speak with and meet Djali Brown Cepeda about unlearning colorism, racism, and machismo with the Latinx context and more! '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'About Djali Brown Cepeda: Dominican-American filmmaker/archivist and racial justice advocate. Djali Brown Cepeda is the founder of Nueva Yorkinos which is an organization that aims to preserve Latinx history and culture in New York city through photography and storytelling.',420),
(722896,'First Meeting',cast('2015-09-17 18:00' as date),cast('2015-09-17 17:30' as date),'Ho 238','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HTT','Come to our first meeting to learn what we''re all about and be introduced to our first project of the year',null),
(751382,'African Appreciation week (Keynote and fashion show)',cast('2015-11-14 12:00' as date),cast('2015-11-14 13:00' as date),'HOP','Cultural',NULL,'AS','The ASU fashion show and the Keynote lecture are two very important events for the African Student Union. This year ASU  will be bringing Taiye Selasi author of Ghana Must go.  The ASU fashions is an annual event with fashions representative of many parts of the continent. There will be food and music. ',620),
(7538875,'Anime Club x Tea Club: Tea Study Break',cast('2021-10-29 17:00' as date),cast('2021-10-29 18:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center Multipurpose Room','Cultural',NULL,'HAS','Before Halloween weekend kicks in, why not come, have a study break, and hang out with us in ALANA Cultural Center? We invited everyone to join us for a tea break, with snacks, and watch some videos!',null),
(7598677,'Masala Chai Night',cast('2021-11-14 18:00' as date),cast('2021-11-14 19:00' as date),'ALANA MPR Room','Cultural',NULL,'TTC','Our Officer Sam Fleming will demonstrate the Art of making Masala Chai. All are welcomed to join!',null),
(761684,'Alf Jacques (Onondaga): Lacrosse: The Creator''s Game',cast('2015-11-05 12:00' as date),cast('2015-11-05 13:00' as date),'Alana Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'NAIS','The Native American Student Association (NASA) is proposing an event to bring attention to Native American culture during November, which is Native American Heritage Month.  NASA wishes to bring Onondaga lacrosse stick maker, hall of fame player, and educator Alfred Jacques to campus to discuss the cultural significance of lacrosse for the Haudenosaunee (Iroquois) people.  This event is in keeping with NASAs mission to educate the campus and the public about Native American culture.  Alf is a charismatic person and excellent speaker whose presentation will enhance the spirit of NASA and enrich the experience of the Native American Studies Program at Hudson.  Alf, a master craftsman of lacrosse sticks, will demonstrate his craft and his creations, while explaining the history and cultural importance of lacrosse.',620),
(7623635,'Board Game and Karaoke Night',cast('2021-12-03 18:00' as date),cast('2021-12-03 20:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'HIC','Come to the study break event co-hosted by Hudson International Community (CIC) and Go+! Fetch some snacksanddrinks, play cards, and sing with your friends at this event to shake off your stress! Everyone is welcome!',null),
(7623636,'Board Game and Karaoke Night',cast('2021-12-03 18:00' as date),cast('2021-12-03 20:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'HIC','Come to the study break event co-hosted by Hudson International Community (CIC) and Go+! Fetch some snacksanddrinks, play cards, and sing with your friends at this event to shake off your stress! Everyone is welcome!',null),
(7637305,'Dancefest After-Gathering',cast('2021-12-04 22:30' as date),cast('2021-12-05 01:30' as date),'CAH/ADH','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','Come join BSU, LASO and LAD in collaboration to celebrate the After-party for Dancefest! ',350),
(7933330,'Black History Month End of Month Celebration at La Casa',cast('2022-02-26 22:30' as date),cast('2022-02-27 01:00' as date),'La Casa','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','Come join La Casa, LASO and BSU to close out Black History Month with a big celebration and a night full of DanceHall, Reggaeton, and AfroBeat dancing! '||chr(10)||' ',320),
(8088562,'Loteria Night',cast('2022-09-17 20:00' as date),cast('2022-09-17 21:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'LASO',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'Loteria is a game of chance similar to the American game Bingo, but using a deck of cards with images that relate to Mexican culture. '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',300),
(8088565,'Posole Mixteco',cast('2022-09-30 18:00' as date),cast('2022-09-30 18:00' as date),'94 Broad St','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','Our event will help LASO accomplish our mission statement by centering indigenity and indigenous identities in conversations through traditional native food.',null),
(8088566,'Tostoneo',cast('2022-10-06 17:00' as date),cast('2022-10-06 17:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'LASO',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'For our event, we want to have a tostones eating contest. Tostones are plantain slices that have been fried twice and are popular in Latin American and Caribbean cuisines. They are a food that is popular among Latinx communities and would be a great way to represent Latinx identities on campus while commemorating Hispanic Heritage month through a commonly enjoyed food.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',400),
(8088571,'Fogata y Historias de Terror',cast('2022-09-16 19:00' as date),cast('2022-09-16 20:00' as date),'La Casa','Cultural',NULL,'LASO',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'For our event, we want to have a campfire and scary storytelling night. There are enough terrible mythological monsters and horror legends to scare us for a lifetime all over Latin America. Almost every country has its own ghosts and stories about them.'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',150),
(821024,'Women in Ethnic and civil war in Sri Lanka',cast('2015-03-12 12:30' as date),cast('2015-03-12 12:30' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'SACC','The idea of South Asia usually revolves around India. In the South Asian Cultural Club, we are trying to deconstruct this view, by expanding the definition of South Asia. To do this, we wish to have a brown bag by Professor Rajasingham to discuss the ongoing ethnic and civil war in Sri Lanka, primarily how it affects women. Professor Rajasingham is a peace activist and works closely with those affected in Sri Lanka. The aim is to inform and start a conversation about the conflict in Sri Lanka, as it has not been spoken about in the West but affects the lives of many in the East.',670),
(8407998,'Keynote Speaker',cast('2022-10-13 18:00' as date),cast('2022-10-13 18:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','For this event, we hope to have a dinner and conversation event with Vanessa Pezo - a Latinx Trauma Therapist. Our goal is to help destigmatize mental health topics and bring students together to engage in these important conversations.',null),
(841835,'Anime Boston 2016 Trip',cast('2016-03-25 19:00' as date),cast('2016-03-27 18:00' as date),'Hynes Convention Center','Cultural',NULL,'HAS','Anime Boston 2016 is the Northeast largest anime convention held annually in Massachusetts. The event aims to promote an educational appreciation for Japanese animation, comics, and pop-culture.'||chr(10)||'Hudson Anime Society is organizing this trip to give attendees opportunities to explore their areas of interests through a wide variety of industry panels, hands-on workshops, informative interviews, all the while enjoying themselves with drawing, cosplaying and writing. The trip is open to all Hudson students (up to 12 people).',240),
(841840,'LASO features Keynote Speaker Junot Diaz',cast('2016-01-26 19:00' as date),cast('2016-01-26 21:00' as date),'Love Auditorium, Olin','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','The Latin American Student Organization (LASO) and other sponsors have invited Professor Junot Diaz to talk about his novels, social justice advocacy, and international human right violations in the Dominican Republic on Tuesday January 26, after MLK week and before Black History Month , at 7pm at the Chapel.  '||chr(10)||'Junot Diaz was born in the Dominican Republic and raised in New Jersey. He is the author of the critically acclaimed Drown; The Brief Wondrous Life of Oscar Wao, which won the 2008 Pulitzer Prize and the National Book Critics Circle Award; and This Is How You Lose Her, a New York Times bestseller and National Book Award finalist. He is the recipient of a MacArthur Genius Fellowship, PEN/Malamud Award, Dayton Literary Peace Prize, Guggenheim Fellowship, and PEN/O. Henry Award.  A graduate of Rutgers College, Diaz is currently the fiction editor at Boston Review and the Rudge and Nancy Allen Professor of Writing at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.'||chr(10)||' ',800),
(8513721,'Queering Hudson',cast('2022-10-18 19:00' as date),cast('2022-10-18 19:00' as date),'Rainbow Room','Cultural',NULL,'QTPC','Come play a game and have a conversation surrounding the theme of celebrating queerness, embracing our intersectionalities, and coming out with guest speakers Professor Justin Helepololei and Professor Taryn Jordan! Donuts will be provided!',null),
(8543690,'Haloween Party',cast('2022-10-28 22:00' as date),cast('2022-10-29 00:00' as date),'La Casa','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','Come join LASO, QTPOC, SORT, KCA, and Brothers to enjoy a spooktacular party at La Casa! All are welcome. ',250),
(858993,'Wii Tournament',cast('2016-01-30 19:00' as date),cast('2016-01-30 23:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Cultural',NULL,'HMSA','The Muslim Student Association will be hosting a Wii Tournament at the Chapel basement. The event is open to everyone. Food and refreshments will be served.',null),
(866637,'Classics Coffee Hour',cast('2016-03-25 13:30' as date),cast('2016-03-25 14:00' as date),'Lawrence 114','Social',NULL,'HCS','Come hang out with the Hudson Classics Society and meet others interested in the ancient civilizations of ancient Greece and Rome!  Chat over coffee, tea, and sweets with other student and department faculty.  A great way to meet new people and make connections!',null),
(883312,'OASIS Family Dinners',cast('2016-02-20 17:00' as date),cast('2016-02-20 19:00' as date),'Center for International Programs Kitchen','Cultural',NULL,'OASIS','OASIS Family Dinners aim to build a safe space and community within Asian students on campus. We invite all Asian-identifying students to join our Family Dinners. The Family Dinner allows students to share an Asian meal together, connect with other Asian students on campus, and engage in conversations about Asian identities in a relaxed atmosphere.',340),
(883313,'OASIS Family Dinners',cast('2016-03-05 17:00' as date),cast('2016-03-05 19:00' as date),'Center for International Programs Kitchen','Cultural',NULL,'OASIS','OASIS Family Dinners aim to build a safe space and community within Asian students on campus. We invite all Asian-identifying students to join our Family Dinners. The Family Dinner allows students to share an Asian meal together, connect with other Asian students on campus, and engage in conversations about Asian identities in a relaxed atmosphere.',340),
(883314,'OASIS Family Dinners',cast('2016-03-26 17:00' as date),cast('2016-03-26 18:00' as date),'Center for International Programs Kitchen','Cultural',NULL,'OASIS','OASIS Family Dinners aim to build a safe space and community within Asian students on campus. We invite all Asian-identifying students to join our Family Dinners. The Family Dinner allows students to share an Asian meal together, connect with other Asian students on campus, and engage in conversations about Asian identities in a relaxed atmosphere.',340),
(9025286,'German Cooking Night',cast('2023-04-17 18:00' as date),cast('2023-04-17 19:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'GC','Come to the German Clubs cooking night to make and taste Flammkuchen, a pizza-like regional German specialty with all kinds of sweet and savory variations!',null),
(9025288,'German Mug Painting',cast('2023-04-03 18:00' as date),cast('2023-04-03 19:00' as date),'Max Kade German Center, 115 Lawrence Hall','Cultural',NULL,'GC','Attendees to our mug painting night will be able to paint classic beer stein mugs and enjoy handmade German pretzels that we will be baking. Snacks and refreshments are included, and no knowledge of the German language is necessary!',null),
(903179,'Challenges of Reading Quranic Arabic',cast('2016-02-26 16:00' as date),cast('2016-02-26 17:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Cultural',NULL,'HMSA','As part of the Hudson''s Muslim Student Association Brown Bag Series, Professor Musa will be giving a talk on the challenges of reading Quranic Arabic at the Chapel Basement. Halal food from Taj Mahal will be served.',null),
(9034125,'Lewis Orator Prize',cast('2023-04-05 16:30' as date),cast('2023-04-05 17:30' as date),'Lathrop 207','Cultural',NULL,'DS','Each contestant will deliver an original speech that is centered on a one-word prompt published by the competitions organizers prior to the competition.  The prompt must be used in the speech as a vehicle to elucidate some aspect of social reality in a new and memorable way.'||chr(10)||'Speeches will be evaluated by a panel of several faculty members, and the top several speeches for each class year will receive monetary prizes. '||chr(10)||'For further details or to sign up, please contact debatesociety@hudson.edu',360),
(9075118,'Stevenson Prize for Expository Speaking',cast('2023-04-28 16:30' as date),cast('2023-04-28 17:30' as date),'Lawrence Auditorium 020','Cultural',NULL,'DS','The Stevenson Prize for Expository Speaking is open to all currently enrolled'||chr(10)||'Hudson students. Each contestant will present a research paper:'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'That is not co-authored'||chr(10)||'That is not the result of collaborative research'||chr(10)||'That is based on independent research conducted by the contestant at Hudson University in connection with coursework'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'The presentation will be expository. The speech should be audience centered, anticipating as much as possible the interests and abilities of the assembled audience. The audience should not be addressed as expert bearers of technical knowledge in the particular discipline wherein the research is grounded (e.g. Biology, History, Philosophy, etc.).'||chr(10)||'Presentations will be evaluated by a panel of several faculty members, and the top several presentations for each class year will receive monetary prizes. For further details or to sign up, please contact debatesociety@hudson.edu',410),
(9394927,'Mid-Autumn Festival 2023',cast('2023-09-30 18:00' as date),cast('2023-09-30 19:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','LETS CELEBRATE THE MID-AUTUMN FESTIVAL WITH US on Saturday, September 30 from 6-8 PM  A collaboration between HVS, CIA, and OASIS+. Join us for a night of food, moon cakes, lanterns, calligraphy, special performance arts, and more. Everyone is welcome!  ',300),
(9467318,'German Music and Game Night',cast('2023-10-02 18:00' as date),cast('2023-10-02 18:30' as date),'Max Kade German Center','Cultural',NULL,'GC','Hudson students from any background are invited to come together and have fun around the German language and culture. Attendees to our game night will be able to participate in some super fun German board games like German Taboo, Mensch Argere Dich Nicht, Wizard, and Quartett, while listening to a playlist of German music. Snacks and refreshments are included, and no knowledge of the German language is necessary!',295),
(9523444,'The CAS Gundam Building Event',cast('2023-10-21 16:00' as date),cast('2023-10-21 18:00' as date),'The Japan Room','Cultural',NULL,'HAS','Gundam, short for "Mobile Suit Gundam," created by Yoshiyuki Tomino is a multimedia franchise that originated in Japan and has become an iconic part of global pop culture. The original "Mobile Suit Gundam'''' consisted of a story set in a distant future, depicting a war and political drama between Earth and its colonies using giant humanoid robots called "mobile suits.". The series was a huge success from the start and in the 1990s marked a turning point as the franchise gained international recognition. Gundam models (Gunpla), which are DIY model kits based on the many Gundams featured in the shows and films, became highly popular collectibles, quickly becoming highly popular collectables even for those outside of the Gundam fan base and a main staple of Japanese Otaku culture. Throughout its history, Gundam has not only been a popular entertainment franchise but also a significant cultural phenomenon that has influenced other media, fashion, and even real-world robotics research. Its themes of war, technology, ethics, and identity have resonated with audiences worldwide, making it a lasting and iconic part of Japanese and global pop culture. We want to share this important staple in Japanese pop culture by allowing students and staff around campus, whether they are a Gundam expert or a fresh beginner, to explore and nurture their interests. Participants will be able to build their own Gundam sets during the workshop and their final products can either be reused or used as decoration in future events. The hands-on experience of creating an original set, alongside the chance to go see that work in future events will spark deeper interest in Japanese culture amongst students. We are expecting new fans of Gundam and Japanese culture and media to emerge from this event.',400),
(9587386,'Bracelet-Making Extravaganza',cast('2023-11-04 16:30' as date),cast('2023-11-04 17:00' as date),'ALANA''s Multipurpose Room','Cultural',NULL,'HIC',NULL||chr(10)||'Join us in making bracelets with beads sourced from various nations in Africa and Asia! This event is open to all Hudson community members, regardless of their background. Let''s celebrate cross-cultural friendship by making bracelets together! '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'*We will also have traditional friendship bracelet beads, charms, and bangles!*'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Here''s a video of Ghanaian artisans making glass beads from recycled glass: '||chr(10)||'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jddwxwn6bFM'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',110),
