(3184818,'Kappa Kisses',cast('2019-02-08 10:00' as date),cast('2019-02-14 16:00' as date),'O''Connor Campus Center','Fundraising',NULL,'KKG','Kappa Kisses is a Philanthropy event that Kappa Kappa Gamma hosts each year. The sorority sells bags of Hershey kisses in the Coop for four days and delivers the Kisses on Valentine''s Day. The kisses will be sold for $5 one bunch of kisses and $9 two bunches of kisses. The proceeds will go both to Reading is Fundamental and the Kappa Foundation. 75% of total donations go to RIF and 25% go to the Kappa foundation. We will be setting up a table in the coop. Students can come write a message and send bags of kisses to friends. We will be using a HUES Card machine, supplied by CLSI, for donations. We are excited to host this event again! We will be selling on Friday (the 8th) and Monday the 11th- Wednesday the 13th from 10am-4pm in the coop. Kisses will be delivered on the 14th. ',240),
(319946,'Reformation Day Celebration',cast('2013-11-06 18:00' as date),cast('2013-11-06 19:00' as date),'Chapel Garden Level',NULL,'Religious/Spiritual','UC','A dinner and discussion will take place in the Chapel Garden Level regarding the Reformation, the differences between various Protestant denominations, and their influence today. Catered by Royal India Grill.',null),
