(513435,'Haunted House and Halloween Party',cast('2014-10-31 18:00' as date),cast('2014-11-01 19:00' as date),'La Casa, 6pm-8pm PAC House, 110 Broad, 10-1am','Fundraising',NULL,'LASO',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'LASO (Latin American Student Organization), BDS (Blue Diamond Society), KCA (Korean Cultural Association) are sponsporing its annual Haunted House and Halloween Party. The Haunted House will be in LA CASA from 6pm-8pm.Take a guided Scare Tour through the 3 stories of La Casa. Open to the public. Come at your own risk! Halloween Party will be in PAC HOUSE (110 Broad) from 10pm to 1am. It is: A Halloween themed party and philanthropic event to raise money for BDS charity of the year Innovation Africa. Suggested donations of $5 are happily accepted.TICKETS AVAILABLE AT COOP and FRANK THIS WEEK ONLY FROM 11:15AM-2:15PM! ONE TICKET for ADMISSION INTO BOTH EVENTSSuggested Donation of $5! Come, celebrate festivities, and bring friends! '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' ',340),
(528981,'Konosioni Senior Honor Society Induction Ceremony for the Class of 2016',cast('2015-02-13 15:00' as date),cast('2015-02-13 16:30' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Community Service',NULL,'THS','The Konosioni Senior Honor Society Class of 2015 is proud to present the Konosioni Senior Honor Society Class of 2016.  We invite the Hudson and Hamilton community to join us as we celebrate the achievement of these 26 leaders on campus.  There will be a short torchlight parade on the academic quad with the current and new members, followed by a ceremony and reception in the Chapel.  This event will be livestreamed and available to watch through the Hudson webpage.'||chr(10)||'Watch on Livestream',375),
(528982,'Konosioni Senior Honor Society Brown Bag - Madison County Gives',cast('2015-04-07 12:00' as date),cast('2015-04-07 12:00' as date),'ALANA Multipurpose Room','Community Service',NULL,'THS','The Konosioni Senior Honor Society is hosting a brown bag discussion which will have short presentations by the eight not-for-profit organizations featured on the Madison County Gives website.  Each of these organizations received funding from the donations raised in Konosionis auction last year and have put the money towards meaningful projects.  This brown bag is designed to highlight the need for philanthropic giving in Madison County and to engage student and community interest in the 19th Annual Konosioni Charity Auction the following week.',140),
(636773,'Global Health Initiative Parents Weekend Silent Auction and Raffle',cast('2015-10-30 20:00' as date),cast('2015-10-30 21:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub, Hudson University','Fundraising',NULL,'HGHC','We will be fundraising for Bwindi Community Hospital Friday evening of parents weekend with a silent auction and raffle.  Prizes will be made up of donations from local businesses such as La Iguana, the Hudson Inn, and Hamilton Eatery.  Small deserts and non-alcoholic drinks will be provided, and other food and drinks will be available for purchase from Donovan''s Pub.',200),
(6539653,'Hudson Caretakers Card Making',cast('2020-10-19 16:00' as date),cast('2020-10-19 16:00' as date),'Alumni 207','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','HC','Hudson Caretakers is a service group that normally visits the Crouse Community Center and volunteers there. Since we cannot volunteer in person this semester, we will be making cards for the residents at the day center located closer to Hudson. Come join us!',200),
(6945936,'Positive Post-its',cast('2021-02-23 15:30' as date),cast('2021-02-23 16:30' as date),'Shaw Wellness Center Lounge','Community Service',NULL,'RAK','Today DoRAK will be creating positive messages on post-it notes to spread around campus!',null),
(6969659,'Digitize and Reeducate: Surveillance, Detention and Unfree Labor in Northwest China',cast('2021-03-16 16:00' as date),cast('2021-03-16 16:00' as date),'Online','Thoughtful Learning','Religious/Spiritual','HMSA','This short talk considers the economic factors that have produced protest and violence in Northwest China (Xinjiang). Because Uyghurs have been framed by state authorities as threatening, yet detainable, subject population, their existence offers technology companies space and funding that is unavailable in other parts of China to develop new data-intensive surveillance technologies. These new technologies can then be used to assist in the legal theft of their labor when they are assigned to work in unfree conditions. Building on analysis of labor exploitation in Eastern China and forms of development in other spaces in China, the talk describes the way state power is channeled through infrastructure and institutions to intensify ethno-racialization and produce a mass detention and a "reeducation labor regime" at a frontier of global capitalism. These systems impose a deprivation of liberty" or unfreedom that is systematic and targets individuals based on their ethnicity and faith thereby producing a contemporary and ongoing crime against humanity.',400),
(698910,'Spy',cast('2015-09-04 19:00' as date),cast('2015-09-04 20:00' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','Take Two presents a free screening of the 2015 hit comedy, Spy! '||chr(10)||'Susan Cooper is an unassuming, deskbound CIA analyst, and the unsung hero behind the Agency''s most dangerous missions. But when her partner falls off the grid and another top agent is compromised, she volunteers to go deep undercover to infiltrate the world of a deadly arms dealer, and prevent a global crisis.',null),
(7006843,'5K in A Day!',cast('2021-03-21 19:30' as date),cast('2021-03-22 18:30' as date),'Online','Fundraising',NULL,'DDD','This is a National Event hosted by Tri Delta''s throughout the country. It is a little boost to our fundraising efforts in which 100% of all proceeds raised go to benefit our philanthropic organization, St.Jude. It is a 24 hour event in which we reach out to our sisters, the community, friends, family, and alumni for donations totaling at least $5,000. It is an easy and low commitment way to get involved with local Greek Life and donate to a fantastic cause. ',425),
(7043822,'Tri Hop!',cast('2021-04-10 12:00' as date),cast('2021-04-10 15:00' as date),'HUDSON UNIVERSITY','Fundraising',NULL,'BDS','On Saturday April 10th from 12-4pm Tri Delta will be hosting its annual Tri Hop pancake fundraiser in order to support our philanthropy, St. Jude Children''s Hospital. Due to the ongoing status of the pandemic this event has been switched to a more COVID friendly method. In order to still allow the fundraiser to occur, a delivery method will be employed in which sisters from Tri Delta will deliver pancakes to those who order them within hour time slots. All proceeds from this event go directly to St. Jude Children''s Hospital. All food will be individually packaged and made with silverware and tableware being individually packaged as well. All food will be to-go orders and there will be no consumption of food as a group or in group settings. Tickets for the pancakes are only $5 and must be purchased by 11:59 on April 5th. The ticket is bought in the form of a $5 donation directly to St. Jude Children''s Hospital through our link ( https://fundraising.stjude.org/site/Donation2?idb=467189759anddf_id=4880andFR_ID=130126andmfc_pref=TandPROXY_ID=130126andPROXY_TYPE=21and4880.donation=form1 ) Once you have bought a ticket it will be delivered to you within your selected time slot!',150),
(7070241,'Poster Making, Take Back the Night March, Survivor Speakout',cast('2021-04-14 17:30' as date),cast('2021-04-14 20:00' as date),'Little 207','Community Service',NULL,'TN','Come join the Take Back the Night march at 6 pm on Wednesday, April 14th starting at the top of Willow Path by the library. Poster making will take place from 5:30 - 6:00 pm in Little 207 with materials provided. Following the march will be the Survivor Speakout from 7 pm to 9 pm in Little 207. This is a closed space and healing session for survivors and those they choose to bring in support. A counselor will be present. ',570),
