(908725,'SGA Engagement Series: Social Hosting Policy Forum',cast('2016-03-02 11:45' as date),cast('2016-03-02 13:15' as date),'COOP TV Room','Community Service',NULL,'SGA','Come discuss Hudson''s social hosting policy with partying''s best friend, pizza. Director of Sorority and Fraternity affairs Kathryn Wojcik and Director of Residential Programs Kerra Hunter will be there to answer questions and explain how to host parties at Hudson for both greek and non-greek organizations. The event will be held on Wednesday, March 2nd from 11:45 A.M. to 1:20 P.M. in the COOP TV Room',50),
(1227636,'Brownbag Lecture Series Spring 2017',cast('2017-04-18 12:15' as date),cast('2017-04-18 12:15' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality','Religious/Spiritual','HBC','CBC will be organizing three brownbags this semester. We are inviting two professors from campus and one guest speaker from a monastery we visited last semester. We are expecting 30-40 people for each event and will need to order (vegetarian) food.',null),
(175282,'Diwali',cast('2012-11-09 16:00' as date),cast('2012-11-09 22:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents',NULL,'Religious/Spiritual','HINDU','The Hindu Student Association (HSA) is requesting funding for the celebration of one of the most important Hindu festivals: Diwali, The "Festival of Lights". We plan to hold Diwali at The Hall of Presidents on Nov 9, 2012. The celebration of Diwali at Hudson will involve an Indian buffet, a presentation on Diwali, and a fireworks show meant to highlight the spirit and symbolism of Diwali. This is an annual event and is enthusiastically attended by a diverse Hudson population.',500),
(245753,'Shine a Light on Slavery',cast('2013-04-08 15:00' as date),cast('2013-04-12 15:00' as date),'Coop, Lawrence, Chapel garden level',NULL,'Religious/Spiritual','HCF','A week of events (Brown Bag, film screening, coop tables) to raise awareness about modern day slavery and human trafficking in conjunction with the "End It" movement and to raise funds for non-profit organizations such as IJM, Love 146, and Not for Sale, which work to end trafficking and exploitation and help survivors.',450),
