(384884,'Interfaith Lecture: Father George V. Coyne, SJ, on How Science Meets Religious Faith',cast('2014-03-06 19:00' as date),cast('2014-03-06 20:00' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,'Religious/Spiritual','NC','Our 2014 Baccalaureate speaker, astronomer and former director of the Vatican Observatory, Father George V. Coyne, SJ, will be giving a lecture on the space where science and religion meet. Fr. Coyne is a Jesuit priest and the McDevitt Chair of Religious Philosophy at Le Moyne College in Syracuse. Before the lecture, dinner will be served with Fr. Coyne at the Chapel Garden Level at 5:30. ',475),
(458919,'GateTown Connection',cast('2014-09-21 13:30' as date),cast('2014-09-21 16:00' as date),'Whitnall Field',NULL,'Club Sports','BDS','Come down to Whitnall field and join Hudson students, faculty, and Hamilton residents on for BDS''s 4th annual GateTown Connection, a tradition that celebrates the strong connection between the Hudson and Hamilton communities.'||chr(10)||'At 1:30 p.m.  join us for:  FREE FOOD and ICE CREAM  INFLATABLES  LIVE MUSIC  KICKBALL and RELAY RACES with Hudsons athletes  PIE EATING CONTEST',380),
