(8549628,'Phi Delta Theta and Gamma Phi Beta Philanthropy Pumpkin Carving',cast('2022-10-28 16:00' as date),cast('2022-10-28 17:00' as date),'Phi Delta Theta Front Lawn','Fundraising','Philanthropy','PDT','We are planning on hosting a philanthropy pumpkin carving event on the front lawn of 114 Broad street. There will be pumpkins and refreshments for sale to benefit the Madison County Children''s Camp. There will be a pumpkin carving station with small pumpkin carving knives and other decorating supplies on a few tables that will be sectored off and monitored. ',280),
(874168,'MSA Brown Bag: The Golden Age of Islam with Professor Aaron Spevack',cast('2016-02-05 12:30' as date),cast('2016-02-05 13:30' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HMSA','The MSA has been holding Brown Bags to raise awareness in the Hudson community about contemporary issues in the Islamic world. Professors at Hudson from different departments and with a wide range of expertise will share their insights on Islamic society, culture, spirituality or politics. Students will have the opportunity to engage in discussions on these important topics, while they enjoy delicious halal South Asian dishes.   ',450),
(930154,'One Love Club Meeting',cast('2016-03-24 16:30' as date),cast('2016-03-24 16:30' as date),'Alumni 110','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'ONE','Learn about One Love and how you can be involved in ending relationship violence at Hudson!',null),
(181443,'NYC Russian Immersion Trip',cast('2012-11-17 15:15' as date),cast('2012-11-18 14:15' as date),'New York City',NULL,'Concert/Music','REC','This trip will provide Russian students with a unique opportunity to immerse themselves within Russian Culture. Upon arrival, students will attend a special exhibit at the Guggenheim, where many works of Kandinsky, a world famous Russian emigre artist, are currently being displayed. Students will then enjoy a dinner at The Russian Samovar, an authentic Russian restaurant run and frequented by real Russians. Afterwards, students will have the chance to see Ivanov, one of Anton Chekhov''s most famous and renowned plays. Upon finishing the play, exhausted students will return to the hotel room. We will leave the next morning, after a "Russian" Breakfast.',400),
(209019,'Mardi Gras Dinner',cast('2013-02-12 18:00' as date),cast('2013-02-12 20:00' as date),'HOP',NULL,'Concert/Music','UC','This event is a Mardi Gras themed dinner and dance. The dinner will take place in the HOP and will be catered by Michaels Fine Food and Spirits, Inc. There will be Mardi Gras themed decorations scattered around the tables and handed out to the guests. At a certain time, the band will start to play and dancing will commence within the Clark Room.',300),
(220235,'Collin McLoughlin Concert',cast('2013-01-25 19:30' as date),cast('2013-01-25 21:30' as date),'The Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','Collin McLoughlin, Hudson Class of 2010, is coming back to Hudson to perform in an exclusive show for the Hamilton Community! Many of you might know him from THE VOICE, where he was loved by all the judges in his blind audition! Come down to The Palace on Friday, January 25th! Doors open at 7:30 and concert stars at 8. '||chr(10)||'FREE ADMISSION!',500),
(321134,'Murder Mystery Dinner Party',cast('2013-10-23 18:45' as date),cast('2013-10-23 20:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Theater','SAA','Come down to Donovan''s Pub this Wednesday for a night of mystery, intrigue and crime-solving fun for all! Dinner will be served free of charge during this interactive performance.'||chr(10)||'The Acme Mystery Company provides interactive comedies in a mystery format, usually in conjunction with a dinner. Our shows play on two levels: they are extremely funny and fun to watch but there also is a very real mystery which each audience member gets the chance to solve. At every seat is a program telling you where you are, when you are, and who you are. It also tells you about the characters you will be meeting. Additionally, each table is given a Clue and encouraged to exchange this information with other tables in an effort to put together the most comprehensive list so as to better solve the mystery.',430),
(357765,'Welcome Back Concert by Jeff LeBlanc',cast('2014-01-24 21:00' as date),cast('2014-01-24 22:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Concert/Music','DP','Kick off the spring semester with an awesome concert in Donovan''s Pub featuring musician Jeff LeBlanc!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Jeff has performed at over 80 colleges across the US and has toured with Gavin DeGraw, Colbie Caillat, Goo Goo Dolls, Ingrid Michaelson, Lifehouse, Matt Nathanson, Brett Dennen and many more. His music has been featured on several MTV shows, E!, and Sirius/XM.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Facebook - www.facebook.com/jeffleblancmusic'||chr(10)||'Twitter - @jleblancmusic'||chr(10)||'Instagram - @jeffleblancmusic '||chr(10)||'Website - www.jeffleblancmusic.com '||chr(10)||'Soundcloud - www.soundcloud.com/jeffleblancmusic',520),
(361006,'Spring 2014 Cabaret',cast('2014-02-28 19:00' as date),cast('2014-03-01 19:00' as date),'The Palace Theatre',NULL,'Concert/Music','MAT','The Hudson Cabaret is an inherent part of musical theater at Hudson. The Cabaret has been a consistent production every semester for years now and is the main, and sometimes only musical theater event every semester. The cast of Cabaret is made up of a diverse crowd of people from different activities and grades all around campus. The cast is brought together through a love of singing, acting, and love of musical theater. The show is compiled of different musical theater songs that fall under a given theme. Our show will include songs from musicals, glee, and general popular pop songs as well. The cast members are dedicated to making theatre at Hudson in a fun, relaxing environment. ',150),
(403621,'The 4th Annual Fringe Festival',cast('2014-04-12 16:30' as date),cast('2014-04-12 17:30' as date),'Parker Commons',NULL,'Concert/Music','MAT','Come and see Masque and Triangle''s 4th Annual Fringe Festival! Featuring performances by all your favorite Hudson Performing Arts groups! Featuring performances by: MandT, The Mantiphondrakes, Fuse, Ballroom Dance, and Charred Goosebeak!This amazing revue will be ONE NIGHT ONLY on April 12th 2014, from 4:30-6:30 PM @ Parker Commons! Come watch your friends perform for an amazing two hours of singing, dancing, acting, and improv. All while enjoying delicious FREE FOOD from the Hamilton Eatery!',400),
(524607,'Plutus',cast('2014-11-18 19:30' as date),cast('2014-11-18 22:00' as date),'Ryan 209','Arts','Theater','MAT','Come down to Ryan 209 to see Aristophanes'' classic comedy come to life in the 21st Century. Watch the struggles of a citizen of Athens as she copes with the burdens of a poor life and stumbles upon Plutus, the God of Wealth. Performances are on:Tuesday, Nov. 18 and Wednesday, Nov. 19 at 7:30.With universal themes of the human struggle, the political controversy of economic inequality, literary irony, slapstick comedy and crude flatulent humor, PLUTUS is as thought-provoking and enjoyable as it was thousands of years ago. With the blessings of Zeus the Deliverer, we gladly invite you to this performance.'||chr(10)||'Directed by Karl Uywith Technical Manager, Jason Alexander,and Assistant Manager, Isabella Crowley.',440),
(7601569,'Women''s Club Ice Hockey Game v. SUNY Cortland',cast('2021-11-14 16:00' as date),cast('2021-11-14 17:30' as date),'Cortland Ice Rink','Athletics','Club Sports','IH','We will be playing SUNY Cortland at Cortland''s rink at 4 PM. We will be leaving from the class of 1965 arena at 2:20 PM.',null),
(9083280,'CRAWFISH BOIL',cast('2023-05-05 15:30' as date),cast('2023-05-05 18:30' as date),'Theta Chi','Fundraising','Concert/Music','TC','Put that on a cracka doooooode!!!,'||chr(10)||'It''s Theta Chi''s annual Crawfish Boil! On a lovely early May evening, the brothers of Theta Chi will host an all-you-can-eat Crawfish Boil boiled by our well-experienced crawfish enthusiasts. Don''t like crawdads? No worries (we take it very personally), we will also have a grill full of burgers and hot dogs. We will have shirts available for purchase as well. This is an event for the Hudson community to come together and support our local fire department while embracing your inner Cajun! It''s gonna be platinum!'||chr(10)||'Best,'||chr(10)||'Brothers of Theta Chi',140),
(9424846,'Fall Concert',cast('2023-11-11 19:00' as date),cast('2023-11-11 21:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts','Concert/Music','MANTI','Annual Hudson Resolutions Fall Concert with the Hudson Dischords and Hudson Mantiphondrakes.',null),
(173299,'Hudson Wind Ensemble Fall 2012 Concert',cast('2012-11-12 19:00' as date),cast('2012-11-12 22:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel',NULL,'Concert/Music','SB','Performance of our fall 2012 repertoire',null),
(178333,'24 Hour Burn',cast('2012-10-19 20:00' as date),cast('2012-10-20 20:00' as date),'Hamilton Center for the Arts',NULL,'Theater','MAT','The 24 Hour Burn is when a show is written, directed, and acted in 24 hours. The writers meet at 8 pm on Friday night and each write their own show. They write until 8 am the next morning and where the scenes are then given to the directors and actors. The scenes are rehearsed all day on Saturday and then the performances go up at 8 pm on Saturday and are open for anyone and everyone. ',370),
(244425,'Carnival',cast('2013-03-18 19:00' as date),cast('2013-03-18 19:30' as date),'COOP TV Room',NULL,'Concert/Music','CSA','Since we couldn''t all go to Trinidad and Tobago for Carnival, we decided to bring Carnival to Hudson. We will have a limbo competition, domino tournament, spades, Caribbean karaoke and much more. As always, we will be playing all the tunes from the Caribbean and we will have food. :) Hosted by Caribbean Student Association',330),
(270380,'PM Open Mic Night',cast('2013-09-13 19:00' as date),cast('2013-09-13 20:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Theater','DPS','Open Mic Night is a venue designed for all of those who love spoken word. The event is open to all students, and various types of performances are welcome. From personal poems, to those of favored poets to musical performances, all are welcome to perform! ',240),
(2903743,'Kikwetu: The After Party',cast('2018-11-10 23:00' as date),cast('2018-11-11 02:00' as date),'Creative Arts House','Social','Concert/Music','AS','Kikwetu will be an after party for Hudson students and ASU members to culminate Africa Appreciation Month. Once more, this event will be a great opportunity for students to celebrate African culture through music from the continent and diaspora.',null),
(321135,'Ghost Hunter John Zaffis',cast('2013-11-01 20:00' as date),cast('2013-11-01 20:30' as date),'Ho Auditorium 101',NULL,'Theater','SAA','Come to Ho Auditorium to watch John Zaffis present on his experiences as a ghost hunter, and then join as he leads a ghost hunt up to the Hudson Cemetery. '||chr(10)||'With over 35 years of experience in the field, John Zaffis is a veteran Ghost Hunter and Demonologist. John has encountered possessions, performed exorcisms, come face-to-face with ghosts and poltergeists, and experienced multiple hauntings and near-death experiences first hand. From all he has seen and survived, John Zaffis has come to firmly believe that the paranormal is real, and his research and understanding place him as one of the leading authorities in the field today.',550),
(338820,'Bad Things Happen: MandT Performance',cast('2013-12-06 18:00' as date),cast('2013-12-06 20:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT','One of two fall productions. Bad Things Happen is about six college freshmen coming to college and dealing with the baggage of their past when meeting new people. Bad Things Happen will be performed in Brehmer Theater at these times:'||chr(10)||'6:30pm, December 4th6pm, December 6th3pm, December 7th',500),
(338823,'Bad Things Happen: MandT Performance',cast('2013-12-04 18:30' as date),cast('2013-12-04 20:30' as date),'Brehmer Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT','One of two fall productions. Bad Things Happen is about six college freshmen coming to college and dealing with the baggage of their past when meeting new people. Bad Things Happen will be performed in Brehmer Theater at these times:'||chr(10)||'6:30pm, December 4th6pm, December 6th3pm, December 7th',500),
(338828,'Summer Brave: MandT Performance',cast('2013-12-05 18:30' as date),cast('2013-12-05 20:30' as date),'Brehmer Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Summer Brave a play written by Pulitzer Prize winning playwright William Inge. It is one of two Masque and Triangle Fall Productions. The play will be performed in Brehmer Theater, at these times:'||chr(10)||'6:30pm, December 5th8pm, December 6th1pm, December 7th '||chr(10)||' ',200),
(376248,'Cash Cash @ Hudson',cast('2014-02-20 20:00' as date),cast('2014-02-20 23:45' as date),'Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','We are proud to announce the largest EDM show since Avicii came to campus!! Cash Cash will be coming to Hudson on Feb 20th (next Thursday)!This show is brought to you by Chegg, Monster Energy, Hudson University, and Campus DJ!Check out Cash Cash''s hit single Take Me Home: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wvzfOyW0ZMoABOUT CAMPUS DJ:As the only nationwide search for the top collegiate DJs, Campus DJ is an authentic platform for students and universities to participate in an exciting national competition with huge prizing. Come see the best college DJs battle it out for their chance of being crowned the best college DJ in the country!To participate in the Hudson Battle, sign up at www.campusdj.com, and get your friends to vote! The winner of the Hudson battle will move on to our regional battle on 4/4 in New York City to perform live on a yacht! The regional winner will move on to compete in the national finale in at Avalon Hollywood in June!',500),
(400885,'Senegal St. Joseph Gospel Choir Performance',cast('2014-10-16 18:30' as date),cast('2014-10-16 19:30' as date),'Hall Of Presidents','Arts','Concert/Music','AS','This event will involve a two-hour choral performance by the Senegalese St Joseph Gospel Choir which is composed of 15 singers and 4 traditional drummers from Dakar, Senegal. With over six decades of experience, the choir is famed for its passionate and diverse performances which range from traditional African songs to Negro spirituals to contemporary songs that they have composed in different languages such as Oulof, Portuguese Creole, Diola, French and Serere. This performance will be part of the choirs inaugural North American tour.  ',450),
(410210,'Taming of the Shrew',cast('2014-04-19 18:00' as date),cast('2014-04-19 19:00' as date),'Merrill House Lawn',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Performances of Shakespeare''s comedy, Taming of the Shrew, will be held on Merrill House Lawn.'||chr(10)||'In the case of rain, the show will be held in the HOP.'||chr(10)||'The show runs approximately 1:45 with an additional 5 minute intermission.',null),
(456441,'CAB Club Series: DENLO',cast('2014-09-05 22:30' as date),cast('2014-09-05 23:30' as date),'Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','Continued from last year, the CAB Club Series is a series of concerts held at the Palace Theater and other locations. They provide a great opportunity for students of all ages to attend a free concert in a local venue. '||chr(10)||'This week we welcome DJ Denlo!  A Buffalo man who started DJing at St. Lawrence University during college, Denlo is now a resident DJ at the New York City venue 205 Club!',425),
(458938,'GateTown Connection',cast('2014-09-21 13:30' as date),cast('2014-09-21 16:00' as date),'Whitnall Field',NULL,'Club Sports','BDS','Come down to Whitnall field and join Hudson students, faculty, and Hamilton residents on for BDS''s 4th annual GateTown Connection, a tradition that celebrates the strong connection between the Hudson and Hamilton communities.'||chr(10)||'At 1:30 p.m.  join us for:  FREE FOOD and ICE CREAM  INFLATABLES  LIVE MUSIC  KICKBALL and RELAY RACES with Hudsons athletes  PIE EATING CONTEST',380),
(477967,'Karaoke Night at Donovan''s Pub',cast('2014-11-08 21:00' as date),cast('2014-11-08 23:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social','Concert/Music','SAA','Grab your friends for a fun night of karaoke at Donovan''s Pub! The kitchen will be open for food and drinks, the game room is stocked with air hockey, foosball, pool, and darts if your vocal cords need a break, and it is sure to be a good time!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',380),
(5160729,'Symphonic Band Concert',cast('2019-11-18 20:15' as date),cast('2019-11-18 21:30' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts','Concert/Music','SB','Winter concert of the Hudson Symphonic Band under the direction of Laura Campbell. Music including Holst''s First Suite, Themes from King Kong, and holiday music. Free and Open to the Public',null),
(7390909,'First-Year and Sophomore Theater Community Program',cast('2021-09-22 16:15' as date),cast('2021-09-22 16:15' as date),'Ryan 209','Arts','Theater','MAT','This is an opportunity for first-year and sophomore students to find a theater community at Hudson. Come for games, fun, a potential performance opportunity, and so much more!',null),
(7924818,'W Club Lacrosse Game vs. Syracuse (Home)',cast('2022-02-19 16:00' as date),cast('2022-02-19 18:00' as date),'Sanford Field House','Athletics','Club Sports','LCW','W Club Lacrosse Vs. Syracuse University '||chr(10)||'Sanford Field House',null),
(9025285,'Hudson Resolutions Akfest Concert',cast('2023-04-15 19:00' as date),cast('2023-04-15 20:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts','Concert/Music','HR','The Hudson Resolutions'' annual Akfest Concert is on April 15th at 7pm in Hudson Memorial Chapel. Come enjoy an evening of a cappella, featuring some of your favorite songs across all genres! ',440),
(194143,'Upright Citizens Brigade Workshop and Show',cast('2012-12-01 20:00' as date),cast('2012-12-01 22:00' as date),'Donovans Pub',NULL,'Theater','CG','Workshop'||chr(10)||'The UCB Theatre Training Center bases their curriculum around the idea that all quality individual comedic scenes focus in on one central comedic idea  this idea is referred to as The Game of the scene.'||chr(10)||'The workshops focus on teaching students how to use the idea of The Game to create their improvised scenes. Concepts addressed will include how to identify games within scenes, and how to use the concept of heightening to properly play out scenes once games have been discovered. '||chr(10)||'Show'||chr(10)||'The UCB TourCo shows always start with the cast asking for a volunteer from the audience to come up on stage for a quick interview. The cast will ask the volunteer questions about their life (school, work, family, friends, relationships, etc.) and then take the cool, weird, or funny information they learn and use it to inspire their scenes. It''s almost like watching an entire episode of SNL made up on the spot about one person from the crowd. It''s pretty amazing to see!'||chr(10)||'',440),
(249618,'BSR/PM Open Mic',cast('2013-04-03 19:00' as date),cast('2013-04-03 19:30' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Concert/Music','DPS','Come enjoy a smattering of live acoustic tunes and original poetry. Want to perform? Email us!'||chr(10)||'Refreshments provide',null),
(293730,'Club Series: dBerrie',cast('2013-10-04 22:00' as date),cast('2013-10-05 00:30' as date),'Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','Doors: 10:00pmEntry: Entry is free. HUES Card is required for entry. Each student may bring up to one guest. Additional Info: Alcohol will be served free of charge for students 21+. Friday, Oct. 4th come to the Palace Theater for the first installment of CAB''s Club Series, featuring dBerrie. Between dBerrie''s DJ set, the special effects, and alcohol served to students 21+, this is guaranteed to be one of the best EDM parties to ever come to Hudson. dBerrie has performed at many of the world''s best clubs, as well as recently headlining Sensation Brazil 2013 alongside Deniz Koyu. Check out some of his music below: Radioactive (dBerrie remix): https://soundcloud.com/dberrie/imagine-dragons-radioactive-1Somebody I Used To Know (dBerrie remix): http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7GW5r80uA5MThe Lights (dBerrie Remix): https://soundcloud.com/dberrie/ellie-goulding-the-lightWebsite: http://www.dberrie.com/Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/dBerrieofficialSoundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/dberrie',500),
(3294451,'TriHOP',cast('2019-04-06 16:00' as date),cast('2019-04-06 19:00' as date),'Delta Delta Delta House','Fundraising','Volunteer and Community Service ','BDS','The annual TriHOP event will be hosted by Delta Delta Delta on Saturday, April 6th, 2019 from 4-8pm. All-You-Can-Eat pancakes and bacon will be served at the Tri Delta house located at 84 Broad Street. Pre-sale tickets will be sold at Coop and online for $5, and tickets may also be purchased on the day of the event for $7. If you buy a ticket online ahead of time, please pick up your wristband for the event at the Coop the week before TriHOP. There will be a raffle during the event with prizes donated from local businesses in Hamilton. TriHOP t-shirts are also available for purchase online. All proceeds from this event will benefit the St. Jude Childrens Research Hospital, which focuses on treating childhood cancer and other life-threatening diseases with no cost to the families themselves. Please join us to enjoy plenty of pancakes and to support the children of St. Jude!'||chr(10)||'',325),
(3319402,'SPW Concert: Dreezy',cast('2019-04-13 21:00' as date),cast('2019-04-13 22:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Social','Concert/Music','BSU','Join us at the Hall of Presidents on Saturday, April 13th at 9pm. Opening DJ is YungKee. Music starts at 9:15pm with Dreezy taking the stage at 10pm.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'HUES Cards are required for all Hudson students, staff, and faculty. Guests must be registered during SPW registration hours in Donovan''s Pub.',400),
(345016,'Battle of the Bands',cast('2013-12-06 19:00' as date),cast('2013-12-06 22:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','Come watch student and faculty bands compete in CAB Music''s Battle of the Bands! The winning band will receive a CASH prize! There will also be FREE DONOVAN''S PUB food for all!Sponsored by CAB and the Class Affairs Committee',null),
(379676,'Caribbean Appreciation Week',cast('2014-03-24 17:00' as date),cast('2014-03-29 01:00' as date),'ALANA, HOP, Lathrop 207, Gymnasium, Frank Dining Hall',NULL,'Concert/Music','CSA','The Caribbean Students'' Association annual Caribbean Appreciation Week is aimed at celebrating Caribbean culture on campus and making the general Hudson population aware of some aspects of the rich culture of the islands. It is truly the culmination of the group''s work over the entire school year in terms of giving recognition to Caribbean culture.',600),
(399025,'Island Vibez - Party Tun Up with Mr. Vegas',cast('2014-03-28 22:00' as date),cast('2014-03-29 01:00' as date),'HOP',NULL,'Concert/Music','CSA','A Caribbean concert and party with renowned Jamaican artiste, Mr. Vegas!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'(Katie Kammerdiener suggested I added Island Vibez as a separate event so it gets pushed on the calendar even though it is already corporated in Caribbean Week)',510),
(410211,'Taming of the Shrew',cast('2014-04-17 18:00' as date),cast('2014-04-17 19:00' as date),'Merrill House Lawn',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Performances of Shakespeare''s comedy, Taming of the Shrew, will be held on Merrill House Lawn. Come out and see Hudson students perform!'||chr(10)||'In the case of rain, the show will be held in the HOP.'||chr(10)||'The show runs approximately 1:45, with an additional 5 minute intermission.',245),
(448796,'Club Series III Featuring DJ SLIINK',cast('2014-12-05 22:30' as date),cast('2014-12-06 01:00' as date),'Palace Theater','Arts','Concert/Music','SAA','Continued from last year, the Club Series is a series of concerts held at the Palace Theater. They provide a great opportunity for students of all ages to attend a free concert in a local venue!'||chr(10)||'DJ Sliink will be headlining this event!',null),
(508056,'CAB Club Series II',cast('2014-11-07 22:30' as date),cast('2014-11-08 01:00' as date),'Parker Commons','Arts','Concert/Music','SAA','Continued from last year, the CAB Club Series is a series of concerts held at the Palace Theater and other locations. They provide a great opportunity for students of all ages to attend a free concert in a local venue. '||chr(10)||'Hudson''s Protoculture DJ Group will be DJing this event!'||chr(10)||' ',575),
(526883,'Hudson Ballet Nutcracker',cast('2014-11-20 19:00' as date),cast('2014-11-20 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater, Dana Arts Center','Arts','Concert/Music','BALLET','Please join the Hudson Ballet Company for their annual production of The Nutcracker.  This holiday favorite is student-directed, student-choreographed, and student-performed, with guest appearances by children from the Hamilton community. ',500),
(7022973,'Lego Building Contest',cast('2021-04-01 16:00' as date),cast('2021-04-01 16:30' as date),'Batza Room','Fundraising','Volunteer and Community Service ','HFH','On Thursday, April 1st, Habitat for Humanity is having a Lego building competition! Sign up in teams of 2 to build a creation of your choosing for the chance to win a gift card to the Hamilton Eatery. Please show a proof of donation, minimum $3, to Syracuse Habitat at this link: https://www.habitat.org/donate/?affiliate=0072-1963andlink=6'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'The contest will be held in the Batza Room from 4:00-5:30. Teams can sign up for a thirty-minute slot at 4:00, 4:30, or 5:00.',300),
(7056470,'Random Act of Kindness',cast('2021-04-08 11:00' as date),cast('2021-04-08 11:00' as date),'Outside Lathrop Hall','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','RAK','DoRAK will be doing a random act of kindness!!!',null),
(781367,'Charred Goosebeak Family Weekend Show',cast('2015-10-30 19:00' as date),cast('2015-10-30 19:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Spirituality',NULL,'CG','Charred Goosbeak, Hudson''s only performing improv group, is at it again with a celebration you won''t soon forget.  What''s the occassion?  Why the 280th birthday of John Adams of course!  Bring your friends, your families, your friends'' families and see Charred Goosebeak perform their unqiue brand of improv comedy which may or may not be at all relevent to everyone''s favorite lawyer-president.',null),
(8552383,'Fall Fest Concert',cast('2022-10-29 21:30' as date),cast('2022-10-29 22:00' as date),'Cotterell Court','Arts','Concert/Music','BROS','SAA is excited to host the first ever Fall Fest Concert, featuring Sean Kingston and the Hudson Thirteen on Saturday, October 29th! The Hudson Thirteen will perform at 9:30pm, and Sean Kingston''s performance will begin at 10:00pm. We hope to see everyone in Cotterell Court for this amazing night!'||chr(10)||'This concert was done in collaboration with SGA, and co-sponsored by the Afrikan Diaspora House, Blue Diamond Society, Brothers, Black Student Union, Creative Arts Society, Delta Delta Delta, Delta Upsilon, Lambda, Latin American Student Organization, and Phi Delta Theta. ',450),
(196130,'Poetry Open Mic Featuring Advocate',cast('2012-11-16 18:00' as date),cast('2012-11-16 21:00' as date),'Coop TV room',NULL,'Theater','DPS','We will be having guest poet from NYC Advocate host a student open mic, followed by a performance of his own work.  In addition to a public performance, he will be teaching a private workshop with Hudson students.',700),
(244414,'Hudson Resolutions Akfest',cast('2013-04-06 20:00' as date),cast('2013-04-06 20:30' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel',NULL,'Concert/Music','HR','Join Hudson''s premier co-ed a cappella group, The Resolutions, for their 21st annual Spring concert, Akfest. Tickets are $5 and can be purchased at the Coop or at the door. Doors will open at 7:30 pm for an 8:00 pm show.',null),
(270375,'Word On the Street',cast('2013-08-29 15:00' as date),cast('2013-08-29 15:30' as date),'Academic and Freshman Quad',NULL,'Theater','DPS','Help us welcome new first year students by writing couplets and short poems on the sidewalk of the Academic and Freshman Quad. Ice cream will be provided to all who choose to attend! ',210),
(300911,'CABARET: Fall 2013',cast('2013-11-02 19:00' as date),cast('2013-11-02 19:30' as date),'The Palace Theatre',NULL,'Concert/Music','MAT','The Hudson Cabaret is an inherent part of musical theater at Hudson. The Cabaret has been a consistent production every semester for years now and is the main, and sometimes only musical theater event every semester. The cast of Cabaret is made up of a diverse crowd of people from different activities and grades all around campus. The cast is brought together through a love of singing, acting, and love of musical theater. The show is compiled of different musical theater songs that fall under a given theme. This semester we want everyone to have a say in what we sing and are opening up suggestions to the cast members and to the public.  Our show will include songs from musicals, glee, and general popular pop songs as well. The cast members are dedicated to making theatre at Hudson in a fun, relaxing environment. ',260),
(325085,'The North Korean Refugee Problem and the NGOs- What is True and What is being done? Brown Bag',cast('2013-11-14 11:30' as date),cast('2013-11-14 13:00' as date),'ALANA Multipurpose Room',NULL,'Volunteer and Community Service ','KCA','Join us for a brown bag discussion on the North Korean refugee issues and prospect, ans well as the role of NGOs and the government. Following the film screening of Danny from North Korea, further discussion of the topic will be led by a panel of students who have interned at North Korean refugee-related organizations as well as Prof. Palmer, who has been actively involved in North Korean refugee education issues in Korea.'||chr(10)||' ',500),
(371763,'Mantiphondrakes Valentine''s Day Concert',cast('2014-02-14 19:00' as date),cast('2014-02-14 20:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Concert/Music','MANTI','What better way is there to enjoy the day of roses, hearts and sweets with a night of song?Whether you want a romantic evening performance with your special someone, or you''re looking for someone to hold in your heart, or you just want to enjoy some good music, come down to DONOVAN''S PUB on ST. VALENTINE''S DAY at 7:00 PM.Let the Mantiphondrakes sing the night away for you ',380),
(468706,'Native American Arts and Culture Festival',cast('2014-10-18 09:30' as date),cast('2014-10-18 16:00' as date),'Sanford Field House, Hudson University',NULL,'Concert/Music','NAIS','The Native American Arts and Culture Festival is a free event open to the public and the Native American Student Association''s biggest event all year. The festival will feature a craft market, live music and dancing, traditional food, children''s activities, and demonstrations. ',260),
