(8088639,'Goodbye La Casa Party',cast('2022-04-29 00:00' as date),cast('2022-04-30 01:00' as date),'La Casa','Cultural','Dance','LASO','Come say good bye to La Casa!',null),
(9059070,'ASU Fashion Show After Party: Africa After Dark',cast('2023-04-15 22:00' as date),cast('2023-04-15 23:00' as date),'La Casa','Social','Concert/Music','LASO','African Student Union presents the ASU Fashion Show After Party with collaboration from Black Student Union, Latin American Student Association, and the Caribbean Students Association. Join us as we finish off the night with a fun celebration. We will be hosting DJ Mike Cook who will be playing music that will make you want to dance, sing, or simply appreciate the atmosphere. With the theme of a Night in Africa, be ready for good vibes and even better moves! Join us in this celebration of culture at La Casa on Saturday, April 15th at 10 pm.  ',450),
(9750013,'Ballroom Waltz Auditions',cast('2024-02-11 19:00' as date),cast('2024-02-11 20:00' as date),'Ballroom Waltz Auditions','Arts','Concert/Music','HBD','Ballroom is doing a small group waltz this semester for DanceFest! This is an audition-based dance, but no experience or partner is necessary. We will teach you everything you need to know during the audition!',null),
(1062693,'Hudson Vietnamese Society Family Dinner',cast('2016-11-11 18:00' as date),cast('2016-11-11 20:30' as date),'ALANA Center','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Come join the Hudson Vietnamese Society for some delicious and authentic Vietnamese pho! '||chr(10)||'Having a meal together is an essential part of life in the Vietnamese culture. We hope our classic HVS tradition, Family Dinners, can help foster new bonds, strengthen personal connections, and provide an opportunity for others to learn and expand their understanding on the country, culture, and people of Vietnam through food and intimate conversations. ',null),
(1265409,'Super Smash Bros Tournament',cast('2017-03-23 20:00' as date),cast('2017-03-23 22:30' as date),'Hamilton Theater','Athletics',NULL,'SAA','Compete in a Super Smash Bros tournament hosted by CAB Take Two and the Smash Bros Club at the Hamilton Theater and enjoy some food from Royal India Grill.',455),
(165842,'Auditions: The Marriage of Bette and Boo',cast('2012-09-12 18:00' as date),cast('2012-09-13 19:00' as date),'Little 207',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Do you like wedding cake? Can you vacuum gravy? Ever play the kazoo? AUDITION FOR OUR SHOW! THE MARRIAGE OF BETTE AND BOO is a dark, hilarious comedy by Christopher Durang. It features a big cast, and we cannot wait to have you on board! AUDITIONS WILL BE HELD IN LITTLE 207 Wednesday, September 12 6-8pm Thursday, September 13 6-8pm Please prepare a short monologue. Interested in crew/tech work? Email dvonnegut! More information will be available at the Student Activities Fair on Sept. 5, or feel free to ask questions here! Directed by Coco Vonnegut Asst. Directed by Mary Rose Devine',420),
(170933,'One Night Stand: Back to School',cast('2012-09-21 20:00' as date),cast('2012-09-21 20:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Join us for the first One Night Stand of the school year! What''s a One Night Stand? It''s an afternoon of relaxed theater - actors and directors meet for the first time together at 5:30 to rehearse a short scene, and then at 8:00pm we put on a show with scripts in hand - no memorization necessary! If you''d like to act or direct (no theaterical experience needed!), email hgoldman or llaiks by 6pm Wednesday 9/19. Then you''ll come to the HOP on Friday 9/21 at 5:30pm. Don''t forget theater needs an audience too! Come watch the One Night Stand, with opening act Mantiphondrakes at: 8pm in the HOP!',255),
(181433,'Hudson Ballet Company Holiday Showcase',cast('2012-11-26 17:00' as date),cast('2012-11-30 22:00' as date),'Palace Theater',NULL,'Dance','BALLET','This semester the Hudson Ballet Company will be holding a Holiday Showcase.  This event involves participation from Hudson students in addition to children from the Hamilton community.  Throughout the semester, classes are held for both Hudson students and Hamilton children that focus on teaching timeless choreography from The Nutcracker.'||chr(10)||'The Showcase will be advertised and open to both Hudson and Hamilton, and will hopefully take place at the Palace Theater.  ',null),
(209025,'Vagina Monologues',cast('2013-02-14 19:00' as date),cast('2013-02-16 20:30' as date),'Palace Theater',NULL,'Theater','SRT','A performance of Eve Ensler''s play Vagina Monologues as part of the annual VDAY campaign to end violence against women and girls.'||chr(10)||'All members of the cast are members of the Hudson community including students, faculty, and staff.'||chr(10)||'Tickets will be $5 and all proceeds will benefit national (VDAY campaign) and local (Vera House and Victims of Violence) campaigns aimed at ending violence and assault.',330),
(229604,'CABARET ROCKS! Spring 2013 Cabaret',cast('2013-02-28 19:00' as date),cast('2013-03-01 19:00' as date),'The Palace Theatre',NULL,'Concert/Music','MAT','The Hudson Cabaret is an inherent part of musical theater at Hudson. The Cabaret has been a consistent production every semester for years now and is the main, and sometimes only musical theater event every semester. The cast of Cabaret is made up of a diverse crowd of people from different activities and grades all around campus. The cast is brought together through a love of singing, acting, and love of musical theater. The show is compiled of different musical theater songs that fall under a given theme. This years theme is Cabaret Rocks. Our concept includes songs from rock musicals, glee, and general popular pop songs as well. ',300),
(256176,'DANCEFEST',cast('2013-04-26 18:30' as date),cast('2013-04-26 20:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel',NULL,'Dance','GDT','Come to Dancefest on Friday, April 26 to watch the Hudson dance groups perform!  Doors open at 6:00 and show begins at 6:30 in the Chapel.  You won''t want to miss it!'||chr(10)||'Free admission.  Donations are greatly appreciated and will be collected at the Coop and Frank the week leading up to Dancefest.  All proceeds benefit Hamilton Center for the Arts.'||chr(10)||' ',null),
(320643,'Dirt! the Movie',cast('2013-11-11 19:00' as date),cast('2013-11-11 21:00' as date),'Ho 101',NULL,'Sustainability','SEA',NULL,180),
(338824,'Summer Brave: MandT Performance',cast('2013-12-07 13:00' as date),cast('2013-12-07 15:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Summer Brave a play written by Pulitzer Prize winning playwright William Inge. It is one of two Masque and Triangle Fall Productions. The play will be performed in Brehmer Theater, at these times:'||chr(10)||'6:30pm, December 5th8pm, December 6th1pm, December 7th '||chr(10)||' ',200),
(345506,'CAB Presents: Comedy Magician Joel Meyers',cast('2014-02-14 20:00' as date),cast('2014-02-14 21:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub',NULL,'Theater','SAA','Joel Meyers is a young interactive comedy illusionist who has already taken the world by storm, performing a progressive brand of magic for audiences worldwide. Newsweek magazine says Joel quite simply "will capture your imagination.Joels varied and impressive resume includes star performances off Broadway, countless shows for corporations, charities, and universities, and a tour in China. He was named 2013 Best Rising Star and was nominated for two Campus Magazine awards for 2013.'||chr(10)||'Come see Joel''s fascinating performance this Friday night (Valentine''s Day!) in Donovan''s Pub, right after the Mantiphondrakes concert!',430),
(398881,'A capella and Draughts for CURE',cast('2014-03-27 20:00' as date),cast('2014-03-27 22:00' as date),'Good Nature Brewing',NULL,'Concert/Music','HGHC','This will be a charity concert at Good Nature Brewing to benefit CURE International!! The Hudson 13 will be performing and the Global Health Initiative will be raising funds all night. CURE International is an organization that works to provide surgeries for children in multiple developing countries throughout the world.',275),
(4871134,'Equestrian Team @ Hartwick',cast('2019-10-26 04:30' as date),cast('2019-10-26 18:00' as date),'Hartwick College','Athletics','Club Sports','EC','Equestrian Team at Hartwick for IHSA Hunt Seat Competition',460),
(4943475,'Pre-Veterinary Club''s First Meeting',cast('2019-09-19 16:30' as date),cast('2019-09-19 16:00' as date),'Ho 326','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'PVC','The Pre-Veterinary Club is hosting it''s first meeting of the year on Thursday, September 19 in Ho 326. The meeting serves as an introduction to the club and leadership. We also hold ice breakers and are keen to learn about the areas within the field of veterinary medicine that members are interested in to guide our planning for the semester. We hope you can make it!',370),
(524608,'Plutus',cast('2014-11-19 19:30' as date),cast('2014-11-19 22:00' as date),'Ryan 209','Arts','Theater','MAT','Come down to Ryan 209 to see Aristophanes'' classic comedy come to life in the 21st Century. Watch the struggles of a citizen of Athens as she copes with the burdens of a poor life and stumbles upon Plutus, the God of Wealth. Performances are on:Tuesday, Nov. 18 and Wednesday, Nov. 19 at 7:30.With universal themes of the human struggle, the political controversy of economic inequality, literary irony, slapstick comedy and crude flatulent humor, PLUTUS is as thought-provoking and enjoyable as it was thousands of years ago. With the blessings of Zeus the Deliverer, we gladly invite you to this performance.'||chr(10)||'Directed by Karl Uywith Technical Manager, Jason Alexander,and Assistant Manager, Isabella Crowley.',440),
(537098,'Barinholtz and Belushi Improv Comedy Show with Charred Goosebeak',cast('2015-01-31 12:00' as date),cast('2015-01-31 22:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater','Arts','Theater','CG','Rob Belushi and Jon Barinholtz are a highly successful improv comedy duo. They have performed at Hudson every year for at least the past three years. Rob and Jon will do a full day of workshopping and performing. During the afternoon, they will run an improv workshop with the members of Charred Goosebeak. Members almost unanimously name the annual workshop as the most valuable coaching they receive, and one of the most fun things they get to do all year. In the evening, Charred Goosebeak and Rob and Jon will perform at the Brehmer Theater. We have received very good crowds in the past. Rob and Jon also plan to bring a third performer, at no additional cost, as they have in past years. That performer will run an improv workshop for any Hudson students interested in improv comedy. Rob Belushi and Jon Barinholtz are successful professional comedians. Rob had a recurring character on the sitcom "How I Met Your Mother", and has recently acted on "The Mentalist" and in a series of Gatorade commercials with Peyton Manning. In the last year, Jon has had roles on the TV shows "New Girl" and "The McCarthys". The two also have a web series on Comedy Central called "Pie Guys". The chance to receive coaching from, perform with, and enjoy watching two such successful performers is truly unique.',1400),
(5504802,'Women''s Club Water Polo Tournament @ Columbia',cast('2020-02-08 13:00' as date),cast('2020-02-09 18:30' as date),'Columbia University','Athletics','Club Sports','WPCW','Women''s Club Water Polo will compete in the NY State Division of the Collegiate Water Polo Association in this two-day tournament.',235),
(582764,'But All My Friends Are: Black, Asian, Latino, Gay, Multiracial',cast('2015-02-20 19:00' as date),cast('2015-02-20 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater','Arts',NULL,'BROS','Brothers wants to bring the hereandnow theater company to present their famous show But All of my friends areBlack, Asian, Latino/a, Gay, Multi-Racial on Friday March 6, 2015 to perform at Brehmer Auditorium at 7pm.'||chr(10)||' But All of my friends areBlack, Asian, Latino/a, Gay, Multi-Racial is a collection of 10 plays performed in 90 minutes.  Each short play deals with an aspect of being a person of color in the US and is presented through comedy, poetry, and dance, as well as often true to life performances.  The show offers one of the most innovative means of examining diversity and tolerance from this critically acclaimed theatre of color.',550),
(595351,'Figure Skating Spring Exhibition',cast('2015-03-01 17:30' as date),cast('2015-03-01 19:30' as date),'Starr Rink','Athletics',NULL,'FCS','Performances by Soloists, Speed Skaters and Synchronized Skating Team.  Followed by open skate until 7:30pm',590),
(6494968,'Sunset Photography Workshop',cast('2020-10-01 17:30' as date),cast('2020-10-01 18:00' as date),'Willow Path','Arts',NULL,'PC','The Photography Club will be having our first hands-on workshop on Sunset Photography. We will provide all the professional cameras and gear needed to capture the beautiful outdoors by Taylor Lake. Members will have a brief introduction on how to handle and use the cameras, so we welcome all experience levels. We will meet near Willow Path which is right by Taylor Lake. In compliance with Hudson''s event safety guidelines, masks will always have to be worn and we will only be accepting the first eight people to rsvp/show up. Make sure you secure a spot asap and join our GroupMe for updates.',230),
(7027811,'Caribbean Week LASO Family Dinner',cast('2021-04-03 18:00' as date),cast('2021-04-03 18:00' as date),'Online','Cultural',NULL,'LASO','LASO will be hosting a conversation about Caribbean Latinx culture and the erasure of Caribbean identities within Latinidad. We are hoping to be catering individually packaged Dominican food from Mi Casa that we will distribute to participants. ',null),
(709532,'Take Two Movies: Pitch Perfect',cast('2015-09-11 19:00' as date),cast('2015-09-11 20:00' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','Come see a free screening of the 2012 hit, Pitch Perfect! '||chr(10)||'Synopsis: The Barden Bellas are a collegiate, all-girls a cappella singing group thriving on female pop songs and their perfect looks. After a disastrous failing at last year''s finals, they are forced to regroup. Among the new recruits is freshman Beca, an independent, aspiring DJ with no interest in the college life. But after she meets Jesse, from the rival all-male a cappella group, Beca has a new outlook and takes it upon herself to help the Bellas find their new look and sound and get back into the competition.',null),
(722326,'Barinholtz and Belushi Improv Comedy Show',cast('2015-10-03 20:00' as date),cast('2015-10-03 20:30' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts',NULL,'CG','Charred Goosebeak presents two of the best improvisational comedians around today: Rob Belushi and Jon Barinholtz. In the afternoon they will be doing an improvisation workshop with the members of Charred Goosebeak and perform with them in the evening. This has been an annual event for the past four years at least and one much cherished by the members of Charred Goosebeak and thoroughly enjoyed by the community. Rob Belushi and Jon Barinholtz are successful professional comedians. Rob had a recurring character on the sitcom "How I Met Your Mother", and has recently acted on "The Mentalist" and in a series of Gatorade commercials with Peyton Manning. In the last year, Jon has had roles on the TV shows "New Girl" and "The McCarthys". The two also have a web series on Comedy Central called "Pie Guys". The chance to receive coaching from, perform with, and see perform two such successful performers is a great opportunity for anyone.',450),
(747659,'Hudson Portfolio Literary Magazine Submissions Due',cast('2015-12-01 08:00' as date),cast('2015-12-01 23:45' as date),'Hudson University','Arts',NULL,'PORT','The Hudson Portfolio, Hudsons official literary magazine, is looking for any art, non-fiction, poetry, or fiction pieces to display in our 28th annual publication. This is a great way to showcase the literary and artistic talent of Hudson. Submit to hudsonportfolio@hudson.edu by December 1, 2015!',220),
(7508863,'LASO/La Casa Carne Asada After-Gathering',cast('2021-10-29 21:30' as date),cast('2021-10-29 22:45' as date),'La Casa','Cultural','Dance','LASO','Join LASO for an After-Gathering at La Casa after a successful Carne Asada! ',null),
(7515309,'Night at La Casa',cast('2021-10-16 22:30' as date),cast('2021-10-17 01:00' as date),'La Casa','Cultural','Dance','LASO','Come enjoy a fancy night at La Casa! Come dressed in your finest most luxurious outfits! ',null),
(7525907,'Social Justice Peer Education Brown Bag: Understanding Imposter Syndrome',cast('2021-10-21 12:00' as date),cast('2021-10-21 12:15' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center''s MPR Room','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'ALANA','Join a conversation about ways and strategies to cope with and address imposter syndrome on Thursday from noon-1:15 pm. The dialogue will be facilitated by the ALANA Social Justice Peer Educators and Shaw Ambassador, and Royal Indian Grill will cater the lunch. This event is PE Credit hour eligible.'||chr(10)||'https://calendar.hudson.edu/event/thrive_lunch_imposter_syndrome#.YW2nbmZKhbV',400),
(7531975,'Chili Cook-Off',cast('2021-10-22 15:00' as date),cast('2021-10-22 16:00' as date),'Gamma Phi Beta','Fundraising','Philanthropy','GPB','This event is such a fun way for everyone in the community and even our parents to get involved in Gamma Phi philanthropy. Anyone can form a team and cook chili to see who wins best chili! The fundraising will come from a tasting free for the chili. It will be next week on Family Weekend at 72 Broad, in the backyard of Gamma Phi Beta from 3:00-5:00pm. This year 100% of proceeds will go to Madison County Children''s camp in Eaton, NY.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' ',240),
(7636543,'Kappa Kickball',cast('2021-12-05 16:00' as date),cast('2021-12-05 20:00' as date),'Hudson Sanford Field House','Fundraising','Philanthropy','KKG','A kickball tournament to raise money for the mental health organizations Active Minds and National Eating Disorders Associations. ',500),
(7933156,'La Casa Celebration',cast('2022-02-25 22:00' as date),cast('2022-02-25 23:30' as date),'La Casa','Cultural','Dance','LASO','Come celebrate La Casa on Friday for BHM!! ',null),
(800505,'Passover 2016',cast('2016-04-22 17:00' as date),cast('2016-04-22 18:00' as date),'Parker Commons','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Join the Hudson Jewish Union for the celebration of Passover, commemorating our liberation from slavery in ancient Egypt.  '||chr(10)||'If you would like to attend the first night seder, please RSVP to Rabbi Dena Bodian by April 8 if you''d like to join us!',null),
(8035440,'Tach 3''s hockey tournament',cast('2022-04-05 19:30' as date),cast('2022-04-05 21:30' as date),'class of 1965 arena','Fundraising','Philanthropy','TC','Philanthropy hockey tournament at the class of 9165 arena raising money for Ukraine and the local Hamilton ice rink!',530),
(821023,'Club Series Events, Spring Semester 2015',cast('2015-02-13 22:30' as date),cast('2015-02-14 01:00' as date),'Palace Theater','Arts','Concert/Music','SAA',NULL||chr(10)||'Continued from last year, the Club Series is a series of concerts held at the Palace Theater. They provide a great opportunity for students of all ages to attend a free concert in a local venue. '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' ',470),
(821029,'Interfaith Dinners',cast('2015-03-12 18:00' as date),cast('2015-03-12 18:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. Each dinner has a theme and there are discussions or presentations that are related to that theme for students to participate in during the dinner. These dinners have been extremely successful in the past.',null),
(821045,'Dr. Strangelove or: How I Learned to Stop Worrying and Love the Atomic Bomb',cast('2015-09-05 17:00' as date),cast('2015-09-05 18:00' as date),'Golden Auditorium','Arts',NULL,'HFS','Come join the Hudson Film Society in Little Hall for our first screening of the semester! Stanley Kubrick''s 1964 comedy, set during the Cold War, seeks to permeate the tension by asking, "what if the wrong person pushed the wrong button?" Running time is 1 hr and 43 minutes.'||chr(10)||'Trailer',500),
(8296880,'A Cappella Welcome Concert',cast('2022-09-02 19:00' as date),cast('2022-09-02 20:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts','Concert/Music','MANTI','Enjoy a night of music featuring Hudson''s five a cappella groups: Hudson Dischords, Hudson Resolutions, Hudson Thirteen, Mantiphondrakes, and Swinging ''Gates! Livestream link below: '||chr(10)||'https://livestream.com/hudsonuniversity/hudsonwelcomeconcert2022',440),
(8383315,'Homecoming Concert',cast('2022-09-24 21:00' as date),cast('2022-09-24 21:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Arts','Concert/Music','SAA','Hello everyone! SAA, Delta Delta Delta, Gamma Phi Beta, and Kappa Kappa Gamma are excited to announce that Echosmith will be performing on September 24th, 2022 for our Homecoming Concert! The concert will be at 9:00pm at the Hall of Presidents, with doors opening at 8:30pm. We hope to see you there!'||chr(10)||' ',500),
(8562282,'Open Party',cast('2022-11-05 22:00' as date),cast('2022-11-05 23:00' as date),'The Creative Arts Society (CAS)','Arts','Concert/Music','BSU','The Creative Arts Society, Afrikan Diaspora House, Black Student Union, and Student Activities Sound have decided to throw an open party at 80 Broad.',370),
(8618656,'DanceFest AfterParty',cast('2022-12-03 22:00' as date),cast('2022-12-04 01:00' as date),'LaCasa','Social','Dance','BROS','Continue the party after DanceFest at LaCasa celebrating the performances and members of the multicultural dance groups on campus!',null),
(881912,'Darwin''s Living Legacy',cast('2016-02-12 14:30' as date),cast('2016-02-12 15:30' as date),'HO 101','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'SASS','Celebrate Charles Darwin''s Birthday with SASS (the Secular Association of Skeptical Students)! '||chr(10)||'Professor Soja will be giving brief talk on "Darwin''s Living Legacy", then we will eat CAKE!'||chr(10)||'Did we mention, there will be cake?',360),
(8920343,'Pie a Phi',cast('2023-03-03 15:00' as date),cast('2023-03-03 17:00' as date),'Phi Delta Theta - Inside House','Fundraising','Philanthropy','PDT','Fundraising event for the Live Like Lou Foundation, which works towards raising money for ALS research, assists families with a member diagnosed with ALS, and funding towards medical expenses. Pie a Phi allows Hudson students to hear a live band and select a brother to pie at a cost that would go towards the Live Like Lou foundation. There will also be optional hotdogs and other grilled foods to purchase, along with an optional t-shirt!',155),
(8946573,'TriHOP  Tri Delta Fundraiser for St.Jude Children''s Research Hospital',cast('2023-04-15 14:00' as date),cast('2023-04-15 17:00' as date),'Tri Delta House','Fundraising','Philanthropy','DDD','An amazing fundraising event for St.Jude Children''s Research Hospital which provides support for families and ensures they never have to pay for pediatric cancer treatment. The $5 tickets for TriHOP can be purchased in advance or at the event to try our all-you-can-eat pancake buffet hosted on our front lawn with all of our proceeds going to St.Jude!',280),
(9824408,'Baking Against Bigotry',cast('2024-03-01 16:00' as date),cast('2024-03-01 18:00' as date),'Pink Haus','Social',NULL,'LAMBDA','Come decorate cupcakes and discuss marriage in LGBTQ+ and Disabled communities with us! All are welcome <3'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Please fill out this form if you interested in decorating pride cupcakes at Pink Haus in collaboration with Hudson Disability Activists, Hudson LAMBDA, and the Baking Club on March 1st!',null),
(1032793,'Undocupoets series: Sonia Guinanseca',cast('2016-10-14 20:00' as date),cast('2016-10-14 22:00' as date),'Bunche House','Arts',NULL,'LASO','The Latin American Student Organization (LASO), in conjunction with Lounge, has invited Sonia Guinansaca to come and perform during the 2016 Fall semester for Hispanic Heritage Month celebration.'||chr(10)||' Sonia is a Queer Migrant Feminist Poet , Cultural Organizer, and Activist from Harlem by way of Ecuador. Born in Ecuador, at the age of 5 migrated to the United States to reunite with her parents in NY. Since 2007, Guinansaca has been public about her status as an undocumented immigrant. She is the co-founder of some of the largest undocumented organizations in the country, coordinating and participating in groundbreaking civic actions in the immigrant rights movement. She has also founded some of the first creative artistic projects by and for undocumented writers/artists. She has emerged as a national leader in the undocumented migrant artistic and political communities.  She seeks to look into deconstructing borders, and blowing up migration discourse so that tiny radical seeds can grow from that gravel.',350),
(1048019,'Blair Witch Project',cast('2016-10-15 17:00' as date),cast('2016-10-15 18:00' as date),'Golden Auditorium','Arts',NULL,'HFS','Come to Hudson Film Society''s spooky screening of this 1999 cult classic! Pizza and good times included',240),
(173303,'Hudson University Sponsors Student Bus Transportation to the Tiesto/Dada Life Concert at the Syracuse Oncenter',cast('2012-10-02 19:30' as date),cast('2012-10-03 13:30' as date),'Oncenter, Syracuse, NY',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','Hudson will provide bus transport for up to 55 students to the Tiesto/Dada Life concert at the Syracuse Oncenter on Tuesday, October 2.'||chr(10)||' ',425),
(285662,'Men''s Rugby Home Opener',cast('2013-09-07 13:00' as date),cast('2013-09-07 15:00' as date),'Academy Field (Below Oak DR)',NULL,'Club Sports','RFCM','Come support Hudson Rugby as the Men start the season against Rival Hamilton College.  Kickoff is at 1PM',420),
(300906,'MandT Fall Production, Bad Things Happen',cast('2013-12-05 17:00' as date),cast('2013-12-07 18:00' as date),'Brehmer Theatre',NULL,'Theater','MAT','One of two fall productions. Bad Things Happen is about six college freshmen coming to college and dealing with the baggage of their past when meeting new people.',300),
(325725,'MandT: One Night Stand',cast('2013-10-26 20:00' as date),cast('2013-10-26 20:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater, Dana Arts Center',NULL,'Theater','MAT','This ONS is scheduled for Saturday, October 26th, starting at 5pm.  The performance will go on at 8pm.  This event is over Family Weekend and is a great opportunity to introduce your family to the Masque and Triangle community, or just to have a great time!  We will be performing front of curtain in Brehmer Theater, so there will be plenty of seats and all are welcome.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'This time around, participants can sign up to act or direct.  You will then be divided into scenes, and will have approximately three hours to learn as much as possible.  Don''t worry if that seems stressful or downright impossible it''s all in good fun, andperfection is boring anyway!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'If you are looking for an easy way to stay connected or get involved in student theater here on campus, this event is for you!  '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'To sign up, email Caitlyn Hartigan at chartigan@hudson.edu with your name and whether you want to act or direct.  You can also include a note on the preferred size of the scene you would like to be placed in, and we will try to take that into account.  Feel free to email as well with any questions.',380),
(328221,'Hudson Winter Olympics',cast('2013-11-16 14:00' as date),cast('2013-11-16 16:00' as date),'Sanford Field House',NULL,'Club Sports','SAA','We''re bringing back one of Hudson''s favorite traditions for the first time in years! Sign up with this form in groups of 8-10 to compete in a good old-fashioned field day, complete with dodgeball, tug-of-war, capture the flag and many more. T-shirts will be provided for participating teams and pizza will be served after the games are done. Sign-ups due by November 12th.'||chr(10)||'Sponsered by the Hudson Activities Board and the Athletics Department',325),
(329703,'Hudson''s Got Talent',cast('2013-11-08 18:30' as date),cast('2013-11-08 20:30' as date),'The Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','SAA','Come see Hudson''s most talented performers at the second annual Hudson''s Got Talent! Catering from Rusch''s will be provided. Doors open at 6:30 for dinner, show begins at 7:00. ',400),
(338826,'Summer Brave: MandT Performance',cast('2013-12-06 20:00' as date),cast('2013-12-06 22:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Summer Brave a play written by Pulitzer Prize winning playwright William Inge. It is one of two Masque and Triangle Fall Productions. The play will be performed in Brehmer Theater, at these times:'||chr(10)||'6:30pm, December 5th8pm, December 6th1pm, December 7th '||chr(10)||' ',200),
(366327,'Taming of The Shrew Auditions',cast('2014-01-28 18:00' as date),cast('2014-01-29 20:30' as date),'Little 207',NULL,'Theater','MAT','This semester MandT is putting on a production of the Shakespearean comedy Taming of the Shrew directed by Allison Spanyer! '||chr(10)||'Auditions will be held Tuesday January 28 and Wednesday January 29 from 6-8:30 PM in Little 207. '||chr(10)||'Please prepare 10-15 lines of Shakespearean text, not from Taming of the Shrew. '||chr(10)||'If you cannot find a monologue, some wil be provided. '||chr(10)||'Please contact aspanyer@hudson.edu with any questions or concerns. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Don''t miss out on this amazing opportunity to be involved in a Shakespearean production at Hudson!!',280),
(383933,'Brothers 15th Anniversary Charity Week',cast('2014-04-07 12:00' as date),cast('2014-04-12 16:00' as date),'Various locations',NULL,'Volunteer and Community Service ','BROS','Brothers Charity Week is an event composed of several activities throughout the week in order to raise money for the surrounding Hamilton community and other worthwhile global charitable organizations.Starting on Monday, we hold a bake sale in the Coop, giving away homemade goods for a suggested donation and there will be a poker tournament held that evening in collaboration with Games Afoot.On Tuesday, we will run a BBQ on the academic quad during lunchtime.On Wednesday, we are cooperating with BDS and Games Afoot for our 5th annual Super Smash Bros. Tournament, for which there will be a suggested donation for entry.On Thursday, we will hold a bachelors auction, usually our highest grossing event of the week.And concluding on Saturday, we will hold a 3 on 3 basketball tournament in Huntington Gym.Throughout the week, we will be accepting donations at every event and at our Coop table in order to maximize our fund generation.',300),
(468684,'Hudson Ballet Nutcracker',cast('2014-11-19 19:00' as date),cast('2014-11-19 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater, Dana Arts Center','Arts','Dance','BALLET','Please join the Hudson Ballet Company for their annual production of The Nutcracker.  This holiday favorite is student-directed, student-choreographed, and student-performed, with guest appearances by children from the Hamilton community.  '||chr(10)||' ',450),
(484770,'Hudson''s Got Talent',cast('2014-11-13 18:00' as date),cast('2014-11-13 21:00' as date),'PALACE THEATER','Arts',NULL,'SAA','Hudson students will display their array of talents in a competition-style show hosted by CAB Special Events.  Three celebrity judges will be selected to offer critiques and applause for each act, and there will be three audience-voted winners at the end of the show!  Food will be provided by Rusch''s and will be available before and during the show in the space just outside the theater.',590),
(525925,'Mardi Gras Dinner and Dance',cast('2015-02-17 18:00' as date),cast('2015-02-17 20:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents and Clark Room','Spirituality','Concert/Music','UC','University Church, along with the other Religious Life communities, will once again be hosting the Mardi Gras Dinner and Dance! This event aims to bring together the Hudson and Hamilton communities and bring awareness to the history of Fat Tuesday, Mardi Gras and the season of Lent in the Christian faith.'||chr(10)||'This event will take place on Fat Tuesday (February 17th) at 6:00 pm in the Hall of Presidents.  Food will be catered by Michael''s and a live jazz band will be playing music through dinner and while we dance!'||chr(10)||'Student tickets can be reserved in the Chapel Basement or at the COOP for a suggested donation of $5.  Hamilton community members can reserve their tickets for a suggested donation of $15 by calling 315-228-7682 or e-mailing chaplainsoffice@hudson.edu',410),
