(308067,'CABARET',cast('2013-11-01 19:00' as date),cast('2013-11-01 19:30' as date),'Palace Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT','The Hudson Cabaret is an inherent part of musical theater at Hudson. The Cabaret has been a consistent production every semester for years now and is the main, and sometimes only musical theater event every semester. The cast of Cabaret is made up of a diverse crowd of people from different activities and grades all around campus. The cast is brought together through a love of singing, acting, and love of musical theater. The show is compiled of different musical theater songs that fall under a given theme. This semester we want everyone to have a say in what we sing and are opening up suggestions to the cast members and to the public.  Our show will include songs from musicals, glee, and general popular pop songs as well. The cast members are dedicated to making theatre at Hudson in a fun, relaxing environment. ',260),
(325729,'Musical One Night Stand',cast('2013-09-27 20:00' as date),cast('2013-09-27 20:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents',NULL,'Theater','MAT',' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'This is the FIRST EVER MUSICAL ONE NIGHT STAND! A One Night Stand is a fun, low-commitment theater event in which actors and directors rehearse for three hours, immediately followed by a script-in-hand performance. This ONS, however, will feature exclusively musical numbers! The ONS will take place on Friday, September 27th 8pmin the Hall of Presidents in James C. Hudson'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',245),
