(372946,'Mardi Gras Dinner and Dance',cast('2014-03-04 18:00' as date),cast('2014-03-04 20:30' as date),'The HOP',NULL,'Concert/Music','UC','University Church, along with the other Religious Life communities, will once again be hosting the Mardi Gras Dinner and Dance! This event aims to bring together the Hudson and Hamilton communities and bring awareness to the history of Fat Tuesday, Mardi Gras and the season of Lent in the Christian faith. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'This event will take place on Fat Tuesday (March 4th) at 6:00 pm in the Hall of Presidents.  Food will be catered by Michael''s and a live student jazz band will be playing music through dinner and while we dance!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Student tickets can be reserved in the Chapel Basement or at the COOP for a suggested donation of $5.  Hamilton community members can reserve their tickets for a suggested donation of $10 by calling 315-228-7682 or e-mailing chaplainsoffice@hudson.edu'||chr(10)||' ',190),
