(6603856,'Hudson Caretakers Card Making',cast('2020-11-16 16:00' as date),cast('2020-11-16 17:00' as date),'Alumni 207','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','HC','Hudson Caretakers is a service group that normally visits the Crouse Community Center and volunteers there. Since we cannot volunteer in person this semester, we will be making cards (holiday-themed!) for the residents at the day center located closer to Hudson. Come join us!',225),
(7624532,'Dancefest - Fall 2021',cast('2021-12-04 18:30' as date),cast('2021-12-04 20:30' as date),'The Chapel','Arts','Dance','HDT','It''s your favorite high-energy Hudson tradition! Now in our 24th year, we invite you to get ready for celebrating a "higher love" through dance. '||chr(10)||'Doors open at 6pm, show starts at 6:30pm.'||chr(10)||'Warning: Some songs in the show may contain explicit language that may be perceived as inappropriate or offensive. Dancefests mission is to create a space for dancers to express themselves freely and exercise creative freedom in their choice of music. If you have any other further questions, please contact saa@hudson.edu',550),
(7628850,'SAA Holiday Concert',cast('2021-12-10 22:30' as date),cast('2021-12-10 23:45' as date),'The Mat- Parker Commons','Arts',NULL,'SAA','Smallpools and Social House for the last general SAA concert of the semester',275),
(8552384,'Fall Fest Concert',cast('2022-10-29 21:30' as date),cast('2022-10-29 22:00' as date),'Cotterell Court','Arts','Concert/Music','BROS','SAA is excited to host the first ever Fall Fest Concert, featuring Sean Kingston and the Hudson Thirteen on Saturday, October 29th! The Hudson Thirteen will perform at 9:30pm, and Sean Kingston''s performance will begin at 10:00pm. We hope to see everyone in Cotterell Court for this amazing night!'||chr(10)||'This concert was done in collaboration with SGA, and co-sponsored by the Afrikan Diaspora House, Blue Diamond Society, Brothers, Black Student Union, Creative Arts Society, Delta Delta Delta, Delta Upsilon, Lambda, Latin American Student Organization, and Phi Delta Theta. ',450),
(8552387,'The Nutcracker',cast('2022-11-13 14:00' as date),cast('2022-11-13 15:30' as date),'Palace Theater','Arts','Dance','BALLET','This November, the Hudson Ballet Company will be performing the Nutcracker. The story centers around a young girl named Clara who befriends her Uncle Drosselmeyer''s nephew at a Christmas Eve party. Later that night the Nutcracker she receives as a present from her Drosselmeyer comes to life, battling the evil Mouse, and saving her. The victorious Nutcracker transforms into the nephew, who then walks with her through the Land of Snow and introduces her to the Land of Sweets, where the Sugar Plum Fairy and her court celebrate by performing a series of dances for them.'||chr(10)||'Admission is free but tickets are required. ',325),
(8992319,'Self Care Event: Nail Painting and Coloring!!!',cast('2023-03-24 15:00' as date),cast('2023-03-24 15:00' as date),'COVE Lounge (109 Lathrop Hall)','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','RAK','We will be taking time to take care of ourselves by painting nails and coloring!',75),
