(1025748,'Ballet Class',cast('2016-09-13 19:30' as date),cast('2016-09-13 20:00' as date),'Huntington 303','Arts',NULL,'BALLET','The Hudson Ballet Company provides classes taught by Paris Wilcox, a former principal dancer with the Kansas City Ballet, for students of all levels of experience. The classes help develop students'' technique, flexibility, strength, and artistic expression. Classes take place Tuesdays and Thursdays.',260),
(1025754,'The Nutcracker',cast('2016-11-16 19:00' as date),cast('2016-11-16 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater','Arts',NULL,'BALLET','The Hudson Ballet Company presents its 10th Annual Performance of the Nutcracker, a perfect way to get into the holiday spirit.',650),
(1157519,'KCA, OASIS, and Hudson Stand-Up Present: A Night of Comedy with Eliot Chang!',cast('2017-02-09 18:00' as date),cast('2017-02-09 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater','Arts',NULL,'KCA','The Hudson Korean Culture Association, OASIS, and the Hudson Stand-Up Comedy Club have invited comedian Eliot Chang to host a Night of Comedy followed by a workshop discussing the marginalization and generalizations that affect Asians and Asian Americans in the media and many social situations. This event will take place in Brehmer Theater on Thursday, February 9 at 6:00 PM. The event will open with a set done by the Stand-Up Club, lead into Eliots 1 hour show, and conclude with the aforementioned discussion of the Asian experience in America.'||chr(10)||'Boasting over 80,000 subscribers and over 10 Million views on YouTube, Eliot Chang''s "Comedy Central Presents" half hour special was voted #2 in the Comedy Central Stand Up Showdown 2011. His other TV appearance include E!''s "Chelsea Lately" and Showtime''s "Minority Report." Also an actor and an improviser, Eliot studied improv in NY at the Upright Citizens Brigade (UCB) and then with Armando Diaz at the Magnet Theater, where he was on the house team "Jungle! Jungle!"'||chr(10)||'Writing about Chang, the VP of Talent for Comedy Central Joann Grigioni notes," In a comedic landscape that is often wrought with sarcasm, self deprecation, and cynicism, I have to say that Eliot Chang is a welcome relief! His point of view is honest and real yet Eliot''s approach is marked by a fun positive energy that is genuine and refreshing. (That is something that sets him apart - the fact that he is still funny with this attitude and energy that other people try to put forth and it comes off as an act). He''s simply fun to watch and makes me laugh. "',325),
(194153,'Hudson Fall Cabaret 2012',cast('2012-11-09 19:00' as date),cast('2012-11-10 22:30' as date),'The Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','MAT','The Hudson Cabaret is an inherent part of musical theater at Hudson. The Cabaret has been a consistent production every semester for years now and is the main, and sometimes only musical theater event every semester. The cast of Cabaret is made up of a diverse crowd of people from different activities and grades all around campus. The cast is brought together through a love of singing, acting, and love of musical theater. The show is compiled of different musical theater songs that fall under a given theme. This years theme is Time Warp. Our concept includes a rich history of musical theater in that it showcases songs beginning in the 1900s and ending with modern musical theater songs. ',360),
(204211,'United States Institute for Theatre Technology (USITT) 2013 Annual Conference and Stage Expo',cast('2013-03-18 11:30' as date),cast('2013-03-24 11:30' as date),'Frontier Airlines Center; Milwaukee, Wisconsin',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Trip planned by Masque and Triangle in conjunction with Hudson University Theater to the United States Institute for Theater Technology (USITT) conference in 2013. The conference will be held in Milwaukee, Wisconsin from March 20-23. This trip would be open to students, faculty, and members of local professional theater groups.',250),
(236378,'Habitat For Humanity Home Run',cast('2013-04-13 09:00' as date),cast('2013-04-13 12:00' as date),'Village Green',NULL,'Concert/Music','HFH','The Hudson Habitat for Humanity chapter will be having its annual HomeRun 5k and half-marathon fundraiser on Saturday, April 13, 2013 on the Hamilton Village Green.  Pre-registration will cost $20 per person for the 5k and $30 per person for the half-marathon. Registering on the day of the event will cost $25 per person for the 5k and $35 for the half-marathon. '||chr(10)||'Registration begins at 9am, the half marathon starts at 10am, the 5K starts at 11am and the award ceremony is at noon. The largest group registered will receive a free pizza party and the first 100 runners registered will also get FREE T-SHIRTS!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'All proceeds will benefit the Madison County Habitat for Humanity Affiliate.  '||chr(10)||'For more information please go to our website: https://sites.google.com/a/hudson.edu/homerun/ '||chr(10)||' ',425),
(325720,'One Night Stand',cast('2013-10-26 20:00' as date),cast('2013-10-26 20:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater',NULL,'Theater','MAT',' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'This ONS is scheduled for Saturday, October 26th, starting at 5pm. The performance will go on at 8pm. This event is over Family Weekend and is a great opportunity to introduce your family to the Masque and Triangle community, or just to have a great time! We will be performing front of curtain in Brehmer Theater, so there will be plenty of seats and all are welcome.This time around, participants can sign up to act or direct. You will then be divided into scenes, and will have approximately three hours to learn as much as possible. Don''t worry if that seems stressful or downright impossible it''s all in good fun, and perfection is boring anyway!If you are looking for an easy way to stay connected or get involved in student theater here on campus, this event is for you! To sign up, email Caitlyn Hartigan at chartigan@hudson.edu with your name and whether you want to act or direct .'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',540),
(335223,'24 Hour Burn!',cast('2013-11-16 20:00' as date),cast('2013-11-16 21:00' as date),'27 Persson Hall',NULL,'Theater','MAT','Hey MandT Community!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Want to write your own scene, act or direct? Sign up for our first 24 hour burn of the year!!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Here''s how it works: '||chr(10)||'At 8 PM on November 15th, writers gather and write their own scenes until 8 AM the following morning'||chr(10)||'THEN from 8 AM to 8 PM November 16th, actors and directors work together to put together a show that goes on the same night!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'The Burn is a great opportunity to try your hand at writing, acting or directing, and is always a lot of fun! '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'To sign up, email chartigan@hudson.edu and see the attached poster for more information!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'We always need audience members if you think a whole day of acting, directing, or writing would be just too much!'||chr(10)||'',535),
(361008,'Konosioni Auction',cast('2014-04-12 19:00' as date),cast('2014-04-12 20:00' as date),'The Palace Theater',NULL,'Concert/Music','THS','The Konosioni Auction is an annual event hosted to raise funds for local not-for-profit organizations. Last year, Konosioni was able to award more than $20,000 to local groups to develop new projects and increase their capacity to do good work. This aligns with our mission, which is to promote charitable and philanthropic efforts as stewards of the greater Hudson community. This year, we plan on hosting the auction during Spring Family Weekend, which will bring a significant number of alumni, parents and friends of Hudson to campus, and increase the event''s traction. There will be a two silent auction periods during which guests can bid on items and a live auction period done by a local auctioneer. The event will be cocktail reception styled with entertainment by several Hudson groups.',600),
(486985,'Jeff LeBlanc Concert at Donovan''s Pub',cast('2014-11-07 21:00' as date),cast('2014-11-07 22:30' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts','Concert/Music','SAA','Come down to Donovan''s Pub for an awesome concert with singer Jeff LeBlanc, an independent American singer and songwriter. Known for being in tune with his audience, LeBlanc often tells witty jokes or anecdotes onstage, takes requests or surprises fans with a Rihanna or Crowded House cover. Having played with everyone from Ingrid Michaelson, Matt Nathanson and David Archuleta, to the Goo Goo Dolls and Augustana, who would LeBlanc most like to tour with next?',650),
(491840,'African Fashion Show',cast('2014-11-15 19:00' as date),cast('2014-11-15 21:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Cultural','Concert/Music','AS','The African Fashion Show will be a colorful and significant celebration of African fashion organized by the African Students Union in collaboration with other cultural groups. Creative designers with styles ranging from traditional African dresses to modern Afropolitan clothes will clothe models who will grace the runway in this event that we hope to make an annual event. To showcase and share more aspects of African culture, we will have an intermission which will include African dances by a dance group organized by ASU members and will also offer African refreshments like sambusa and mandazi.',400),
(5066681,'Round Robin',cast('2019-10-26 14:30' as date),cast('2019-10-26 14:45' as date),'Fordham University','Athletics','Club Sports','SCW','We will be playing in a round robin against Fordham and NYU on Saturday, October 26 at 2:30. ',290),
(5096374,'Night of Comedy',cast('2019-11-07 20:00' as date),cast('2019-11-07 21:00' as date),'The Mat','Arts','Theater','CG','Sponsored by The Mat and Ciccone Commons, this semester''s Night of Comedy is the first-ever collaboration between Hudson Stand Up, Charred Goosebeak, and ETC. The show will feature a lineup packed with comedy of all kinds, and it will hopefully establish a tradition of collaboration between comedic performing arts groups.',550),
