(594068,'Finesse of Tress',cast('2015-03-07 17:00' as date),cast('2015-03-07 19:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts',NULL,'SRT','Finesse of Tress is a part of Sisters of the Round Table''s Africana Women''s Week(s). This event is an open mic centered on hair and how it connects to a persons identity. Individuals perform monologues, poems, songs, etc. about hair and how its meaningful to them. There will be a raffle with baskets containing hair products at the COOP throughout the week and during the event. All proceeds from the raffle will go directly to Vera House and Victims of Violence. Food will be provided, all are welcome!',370),
(6536357,'Photography Portrait Workshop',cast('2020-10-16 16:30' as date),cast('2020-10-16 17:00' as date),'Willow Path, Near the Library','Arts',NULL,'PC','Is your LinkedIn profile photo looking a bit drab and out of focus? Is your Instagram profile still using a pic from when you were in high school? Then the Photography Club has the answer for you with our outdoor portrait workshop! We will provide all the professional cameras and gear needed to capture all your beautiful faces and extravagant poses! We encourage you to bring any fun props or cool outfits to make those photos just that much more special.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Members will have a brief introduction on how to handle and use the cameras, so we welcome all experience levels. We will meet near Willow Path which is right by Taylor Lake. In compliance with Hudson''s event safety guidelines, masks will have to be worn and we will only be accepting the first eight people to RSVP/show up. Make sure you secure a spot ASAP and join our GroupMe for updates.',110),
