(287423,'HWS Fall Classic',cast('2013-10-26 10:00' as date),cast('2013-10-27 19:00' as date),'Hobart and William Smith Colleges',NULL,'Volunteer and Community Service ','DS','The HWS Fall Classic is a regional debate tournament that is held in the World Universities Debating Championship (WUDC) style which will take place at Hobart and William Smith Colleges in Geneva, New York on Saturday, October 26 and Sunday, October 27. The tournament will consist of five preliminary rounds, followed by a varsity semifinals break and a novice final round. ',535),
(594020,'Art As Resistance: Faviana Rodriguez',cast('2015-03-03 16:30' as date),cast('2015-03-03 18:00' as date),'ALANA','Arts',NULL,'SRT','This event is a part of Sisters of the Round Table''s Africana Women''s Week(s). Favianna Rodriguez is an Afro-Peruvian American artist from Oakland, California. She uses her perspective as a child of migrant workers growing up  in a high crime area to forge her identity as a feminist and activist. Growing  up she did not witness positive images of women of color in the media which inspired her to work around issues of equality, race, interdependence, youth activism, and sexuality. Rodriguez will be giving a lecture followed by a QandA on her work and process. ',500),
(6531476,'DoRAK Outreach Project',cast('2020-10-14 17:00' as date),cast('2020-10-14 17:00' as date),'415 Case Geyer Library','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','RAK','On Wednesday, October 14th, we will be hosting one of our most loved activities of the year... making DoRAK buttons. This activity will spread kindness to both club members and Hudson''s broader community alike! This activity is a perfect way to unwind and destress during the midterm season!',350),
(6581911,'Kindness Stickers',cast('2020-11-04 17:00' as date),cast('2020-11-04 18:00' as date),'Outside Case Geyer Library','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','RAK','We will be placing kindness stickers inside and outside around campus!',120),
(6611638,'Writing Holiday Cards!',cast('2020-11-18 17:00' as date),cast('2020-11-18 18:00' as date),'415 Case Geyer Library','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','RAK','Today we will be writing holiday cards for friends, family, and members of our Hudson Community!!!',160),
(722314,'Birdman: Or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance)',cast('2015-09-26 17:00' as date),cast('2015-09-26 18:00' as date),'Golden Auditorium, Little Hall','Arts',NULL,'HFS','Join the Hudson Film Society for an evening of humor and excitement as we watch Birdman: Or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance). The film follows Michael Keaton as an aging action film star as he attempts to make his debut on the stage. Keaton''s, Emma Stone''s, and Edward Norton''s performances all earned them Oscar nominations and Alejandro Gonzalez Inarritu was awarded Best Achievement in Directing. Running time is 1hr and 59 minutes.  ',400),
(735264,'Ballet Classes',cast('2015-09-15 19:30' as date),cast('2015-09-15 20:00' as date),'Huntington 303','Arts',NULL,'BALLET','The Hudson Ballet Company provides classes taught by Paris Wilcox, a former principal dancer with the Kansas City Ballet, for students of all levels of experience. The classes help develop students'' technique, flexibility, strength, and artistic expression. Classes take place Tuesdays and Thursdays.',260),
(8084444,'Open Mic Night',cast('2022-04-28 19:00' as date),cast('2022-04-28 19:00' as date),'Donovans Pub','Arts',NULL,'HSU','2-minute standup comedy performances by Club Members to entertain diners at Donovan''s Pub.',550),
(9584435,'The Nutcracker',cast('2023-11-11 18:30' as date),cast('2023-11-11 20:00' as date),'Arts at the Palace','Arts','Dance','BALLET','The Nutcracker is a widely-known holiday performance and tradition for people all across the world, enjoyed by both the audiences and the performers. This ballet shares the story of a young girl who is gifted a Nutcracker that transforms into a prince and together they travel to a land of fantasy and sweets. The production is performed by Hudson students and dancers from the Hamilton community. Tickets are free and available through this link: https://www.hamiltoncreates.com/registration ',430),
