(633010,'Dancefest: Behind the Scenes',cast('2015-04-18 13:00' as date),cast('2015-04-18 16:00' as date),'Ryan Studios','Arts',NULL,'ALANA','Wanna try dance, but afraid of performing? Are you amazed by the choreography you see at Dancefest? Want to know how it feels to be part of the group? NOW YOU CAN LEARN YOUR FAVORITE DANCE GROUPS''S CHOREOGRAPHY!!! - Dancefest: Behind the Scenes Pick and choose your favorite dance groups to attend. Check the schedule in the poster.FREE FOOD!!!!!NO EXPERIENCE IS NEEDED!!!!',null),
(636774,'Brown Bag',cast('2015-10-15 11:30' as date),cast('2015-10-15 12:00' as date),'Lawrence Hall, Hudson University','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HGHC','The new epidemiology professor for the Biology department, professor Taye, has agreed to do a brown bag with us next semester to discuss his work and research. It would give students the opportunity to meet a new professor as well as hear about opportunities for involvment in epidemiology research on campus and abroad.',null),
(7057288,'Bengali New Year Celebrations',cast('2021-04-14 16:00' as date),cast('2021-04-14 18:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'SACC','In celebration of the Bengali New Year, the South Asian Cultural club is planning to hold a small, in-person celebration at the ALANA Cultural Center courtyard on April 14 from 4-7 pm. It will be a casual, casual-socially distance block-printing event where participants can come and decorate bandanas or T-shirts with traditional south Asian block printing patterns as they enjoy the New Year festivities at Bangladesh on a projector screen. There will also be RIG to-go for people who sign up early for the event. People can also opt to bring their own T-shirt or piece of clothing to decorate with block-printing.'||chr(10)||'The Bengali New Year, or Pahela Baisakh is a celebration of a new year of harvest and prosperity in Bangladesh and by people of Bengali heritage in the Indian States of West Bengal, and Assam, irrespective of religious faith. It is generally celebrated on April 14 and 15 of every year and marks the beginning of the seasons in the Bengali Lunar Calendar. It is a celebration where people come together to appreciate the colors and prosperity that spring brings with it, irrespective of their religious or cultural background.',null),
(7389925,'Homecoming Comedian Adam Conover',cast('2021-09-25 21:30' as date),cast('2021-09-26 21:30' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts',NULL,'SAA','Adam Conover, comedian and star of Adam Ruins Everything, will be performing in the Hudson Memorial Chapel! Doors open at 8:30pm and Adam will go live on stage at 9:30pm. This is an event you don''t want to miss!'||chr(10)||'HUES Card or wristband are required for entry!',null),
(7527176,'Parents Weekend Brunch!',cast('2021-10-23 10:00' as date),cast('2021-10-23 12:00' as date),'Tri Delta House','Fundraising','Philanthropy','DDD','Tri Delta is back and better than ever with hosting their annual event for family weekend, the Family Weekend Brunch! Join us for a morning of delicious food crafted by our skillful chef, Eric Thomas and plentiful socialization with other members and their families. Tickets will be $5 per person at the door with donations welcome as 100% of proceeds raised will go to supporting our wonderful philanthropy St.Jude Children''s Research Hospital. This event will be held etirely outside underneath a tent in the backyard. We can''t wait to welcome you!!',null),
(756642,'Hudson Dischords and Hudson Resolutions Family Weekend Concert',cast('2015-10-31 19:00' as date),cast('2015-10-31 20:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts',NULL,'HD','Come join the Hudson Dischords and Hudson Resolutions for a night of singing, tyring to dance, and more! Bring your family and friends for a fun night you won''t want to miss! ',null),
(756668,'CVS Cooking Night',cast('2015-10-23 19:00' as date),cast('2015-10-23 20:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','HVS Cooking Night will be a night of bonding and good food: attendees will be taught to make two popular Vietnamese snacks: com suon and cha trung (Vietnamese grilled pork, served with Tam rice and egg meatloaf). The event will be in the ALANA Center and is open to public.',null),
(7629382,'First Club Meeting!',cast('2021-12-03 14:00' as date),cast('2021-12-03 15:30' as date),'Whitnall Field','Social',NULL,'HGC','Hello,'||chr(10)||'Join us for the first ever meeting of the Hudson Grilling Club!'||chr(10)||'There will be burgers, impossible burgers, and vegetables so we have something for everyone.'||chr(10)||'Please RSVP so we know how much food to buy in advance. Thank you.',null),
(7847469,'Caffeiene',cast('2022-02-05 18:30' as date),cast('2022-02-05 21:30' as date),'Coop TV Room','Social','Concert/Music','SAA','Caffeine is an open mic and game night where students can get to know each other through hearing stories and poems from classmates. In addition, in the main room in the Coop there will be a coffee cup decorating competition where the top three cups will be awarded a prize. Games will be spread out around the Coop and snacks and drinks will be provided. Feel free to come in your PJs!',null),
(7847493,'Iceless Ice Skating',cast('2022-02-05 21:00' as date),cast('2022-02-06 00:00' as date),'Huntington Gym','Social',NULL,'SAA','Come skate with us at Huntington Gym and make your own photo snow globe!! '||chr(10)||'Wear your masks :)',null),
(7866698,'CWiB Coffee Hour #1',cast('2022-02-07 19:00' as date),cast('2022-02-07 20:00' as date),'Case Geyer 560 Batza room','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HWIB','For our first Coffee Hour of the semester we will be doing a resume + LinkedIn + Handshake workshop. We suggest bringing in a copy of your resume and/or profile draft, so that we can give you feedback from the different stations. We will also be available to answer any general questions about resumes, interviews, networking, internships, anything!'||chr(10)||' ',null),
(7967134,'7th-Day Study Break',cast('2022-03-20 12:00' as date),cast('2022-03-20 12:00' as date),'Michael Saperstein Jewish Center','Social','Religious/Spiritual','SASS','It''s said that the world was made in six days and the seventh was a day of rest. Join us in resting for six days over break and doing all of your homework on the seventh, or just enjoy a chill environment before classes start back up. And we''ll have food!',null),
(7973274,'First Meeting of Spring Semester',cast('2022-04-02 14:00' as date),cast('2022-04-02 14:00' as date),'Whitnall Field','Social',NULL,'HGC','Join us for our first meeting of the spring semester!',null),
(821022,'Fall Fest',cast('2014-10-22 19:00' as date),cast('2014-10-22 19:00' as date),'Chapel Garden Level','Social','Religious/Spiritual','UC','Join University Church as we celebrate fall with various Fall themed treats, carving of a pumpkin, socializing, and fellowship!',null),
(8552386,'The Nutcracker',cast('2022-11-11 19:00' as date),cast('2022-11-11 20:30' as date),'Palace Theater','Arts','Dance','BALLET','This November, the Hudson Ballet Company will be performing the Nutcracker. The story centers around a young girl named Clara who befriends her Uncle Drosselmeyer''s nephew at a Christmas Eve party. Later that night the Nutcracker she receives as a present from her Drosselmeyer comes to life, battling the evil Mouse, and saving her. The victorious Nutcracker transforms into the nephew, who then walks with her through the Land of Snow and introduces her to the Land of Sweets, where the Sugar Plum Fairy and her court celebrate by performing a series of dances for them.'||chr(10)||'Admission is free but tickets are required. ',null),
(8931162,'German Music and Game Night',cast('2023-02-27 18:00' as date),cast('2023-02-27 19:30' as date),'Max Kade German Center, 115 Lawrence Hall','Cultural',NULL,'GC','This event allows Hudson students from any background to come together and have fun around the German language and culture. Attendees to our game night will be able to participate in numerous German board games, such as German Taboo, Mensch Argere Dich Nicht, Wizard, and Quartett, while listening to a playlist of German music. Snacks and refreshments are included, and no knowledge of the German language is necessary!  ',null),
(926462,'University Church Good Friday Dinner',cast('2016-03-25 17:00' as date),cast('2016-03-25 17:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'UC','Join University Church for a meatless, fast-breaking dinner on Good Friday before students share their faith in personal testimonies on the chapel stage.'||chr(10)||'All are welcome!'||chr(10)||'Co-sponsored by the Hudson Newman Community. ',null),
(927702,'Latke Hamentashen Debate',cast('2016-03-27 12:00' as date),cast('2016-03-27 12:00' as date),'Saperstein Jewish Center','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU','Participate in the revival of the age old debate: "Which is better, Latke or Hamentashen?"'||chr(10)||'Hudson Jewish Union Presidents Chelsea Mohr ''17 and Jack Polikoff ''17 will go head to head in debate, but everyone can cast their vote as you sample both traditional treats. '||chr(10)||'Bagels and lox will be served as well.',null),
(927737,'Purim',cast('2016-03-23 19:00' as date),cast('2016-03-23 20:00' as date),'Saperstein Jewish Center','Spirituality',NULL,'HJU',' '||chr(10)||'It''s time for our annual town-gown celebration of Purim, a joyous commemeration of the story of Esther''s defeat of Haman''s plot to eliminate the Jewish people in Persia. Purim is typically observed with an interactive reading of the Book of Esther, plays with fun costumes, and a delicious feast. We will serve up a spectacular BBQ. '||chr(10)||'Costumes are encouraged but optional. '||chr(10)||' ',null),
(9342593,'Pink Haus Study Night',cast('2023-09-11 19:00' as date),cast('2023-09-11 21:00' as date),'Pink Haus','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'QTPC','Join us for an evening of productivity at the Pink Haus that''s set to take place this coming Monday, September 11th, from 7:00 PM to 10:00 PM. We invite you to immerse yourself in a calm and cozy atmosphere, perfect for focusing on your tasks and achieving your goals. There will be donuts, coffee, and hot chocolate from Dunkin'' Donuts!',null),
(9390691,'IGD Student Training',cast('2023-09-30 10:00' as date),cast('2023-09-30 15:00' as date),'ALANA MPR','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'ALANA',NULL||chr(10)||'The IGD Council and the ALANA Cultural Center present the second Student Inter-Group Dialogue Train-the-Trainer, Part I! If you are interested in learning how to facilitate difficult conversations and to build interpersonal or structural awareness in your own student groups or other community contexts, please join us!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Intergroup Dialogue is a research-based approach to face-to-face facilitated conversation between members of two or more social identity groups that strives to create new levels of understanding, relating, and action" (Zuniga 2003). Upon completion of the two-day training, students will receive an IGD Experience Training Certificate, Part I. Part I will equip you with a foundational set of tools for dialogue and includes ten training hours; students must commit to both sessions to be accepted to the Training.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'This training is open to all Hudson students and those who are (or plan to be) student leaders on and/-or outside the campus. There are limited seats so please sign up early. Part II of the training will begin in mid-October. At the end of Part I and Part II, students will be equipped, under continued supervision and mentorship, to plan and facilitate Intergroup Dialogue events in their student groups.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Note: Meals will be provided. But please bring your water bottle to the training. ',null),
(954527,'Brown Bag sponsored by SACC',cast('2016-09-13 12:00' as date),cast('2016-09-13 12:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Cultural',NULL,'SACC','In the past, the SACC has organized brown bags to spread awareness of the cultural diversity of the countries in South Asia. Particular topics in the past have been about the importance of International  Mother Language Day. The brown bag planned for this coming semester will be continuing on the same trend to attract more interest from the Hudson population.',null),
(9566419,'Dunkins and Bricks',cast('2023-10-27 14:00' as date),cast('2023-10-27 15:00' as date),'McGregory Hall','Social',NULL,'HTT','Join us for a delightful afternoon at Hudson Technic Titans social event - grab a donut, play around with Lego bricks, and/or get to know some people who share the same passion for engineering and robotics! This event serves to be a warm-up for the upcoming workshops; by putting some bricks and blocks together creatively in a relaxed setting, we want to make people more comfortable with engineering and more prepared with the more challenging parts of engineering.',null),
(9880348,'Midnight Philosophy Society Meeting',cast('2024-02-10 22:00' as date),cast('2024-02-11 01:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social',NULL,'MPS','Midnight Philosophy is a vibrant community of inquisitive and curious students who are excited to explore diverse and relevant philosophical topics! We host welcoming student-to-student conversations about morality, society, religion, metaphysics, and epistemology. Our members are diverse in their beliefs, and we are open to absolutely anyone, with no philosophical experience or major declaration necessary. ',null),
(9880351,'Midnight Philosophy Society Meeting',cast('2024-03-02 22:00' as date),cast('2024-03-03 01:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social',NULL,'MPS','Midnight Philosophy is a vibrant community of inquisitive and curious students who are excited to explore diverse and relevant philosophical topics! We host welcoming student-to-student conversations about morality, society, religion, metaphysics, and epistemology. Our members are diverse in their beliefs, and we are open to absolutely anyone, with no philosophical experience or major declaration necessary. ',null),
(9880354,'Midnight Philosophy Society Meeting',cast('2024-04-06 22:00' as date),cast('2024-04-07 00:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social',NULL,'MPS','Midnight Philosophy is a vibrant community of inquisitive and curious students who are excited to explore diverse and relevant philosophical topics! We host welcoming student-to-student conversations about morality, society, religion, metaphysics, and epistemology. Our members are diverse in their beliefs, and we are open to absolutely anyone, with no philosophical experience or major declaration necessary. ',null),
(9893788,'On Campus Hike (with Hot Cocoa!)',cast('2024-02-10 13:00' as date),cast('2024-02-10 14:00' as date),'Frank Dining Hall','Athletics','Outdoor Education','HIKE','Join Hiking Club for a stroll on the XC trails on Saturday, February 10th. We''ll meet outside of Frank at 1pm. Enjoy some hot cocoa and snacks! The hike should be approximately 2 miles long. Please RSVP by filling out this form so we know how much food/drinks to buy: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdq6y-9AF0jbOuRxK2wzULWWBmLwGW5SjqOCBCFoACLYoAIMA/viewform?usp=sf_link',null),
(9923506,'KCA Ya-Sik Event!',cast('2024-02-23 20:00' as date),cast('2024-02-23 22:00' as date),'The Mat','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','In Korea, contemporary social culture amongst students has become increasingly intertwined with cuisine. Ya-sik, or late-night snack is a quintessential part of the Korean student life experience. Yasik often includes foods such as tteokbokki (spicy rice cakes), ramen, and Bibimbap (mixed rice) and serves as a space where people can come together to catch up with friends, talk about the days work, or share the comfort of eating a core childhood snack (children begin to eat ya-sik from a young age, often elementary school). '||chr(10)||'In this event, we hope to introduce contemporary Korean evening cultures and routines shared by Korean students of all age groups. We will introduce tteokbokki, a spicy rice cake dish and introduce its tradition as an after-school evening snack through its presence at bun-sik-jip (snack restaurant) all around school districts. In addition, we will serve home-made Korean bibimbap and explain the historical origins of bibimbap and discuss how rice dishes vary from cuisine to cuisine depending on the local produce and diverse food traditions unique to each geographical region. ',null),
(9934543,'Taughannock Falls Hike (CIC Collab)',cast('2024-02-17 12:30' as date),cast('2024-02-17 19:00' as date),'Taughannock Falls State Park','Athletics','Outdoor Education','HIC','Hiking Club will be collaborating with Hudson International Community for a hike to Taughannock Falls in Ithaca. Taughannock Falls is the TALLEST (single drop) WATERFALL EAST OF THE MISSISSIPPI RIVER!! We expect the hiking itself to be moderate, lasting around 2 hours. There are always some trails open, while others may close due to ice, thus, we cannot be sure of the exact length of the hike. While traveling to and from Ithaca, enjoy foods from many different cultures, including kulfi (Persian Ice Cream) and other international snacks. We can take this as an opportunity to learn about the diverse backgrounds of fellow students. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'To sign up for this event, please fill out this form. However, please be aware that spots are being filled very fast! https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdhMqcrpmorOrg8NAtUXJLFcZdWIOw_GdN8fAUCpcB6HPNdjQ/viewform',null),
(9953063,'Pronoun Pin Making',cast('2024-02-16 18:00' as date),cast('2024-02-16 20:00' as date),'Women''s Studies Center','Arts',NULL,'TAG','Join us in WMST to make pronouns pins!',null),
(9983641,'Baby Tate After Party',cast('2024-03-01 23:00' as date),cast('2024-03-02 01:30' as date),'The MAT','Social','Dance','QTPC','Join us for the after-party to Baby Tate''s concert! All are welcome!',null),
(5225765,'Last Fall 2019 Open Mic',cast('2019-12-11 20:00' as date),cast('2019-12-11 21:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts',NULL,'HSU','Come down to Donovan''s Pub for the last Hudson Stand Up Open Mic of the semester! Hosted by Patrick Toohey',null),
(735265,'Ballet Classes',cast('2015-09-17 19:30' as date),cast('2015-09-17 20:00' as date),'Huntington 303','Arts',NULL,'BALLET','The Hudson Ballet Company provides classes taught by Paris Wilcox, a former principal dancer with the Kansas City Ballet, for students of all levels of experience. The classes help develop students'' technique, flexibility, strength, and artistic expression. Classes take place Tuesdays and Thursdays.',null),
(7516527,'The Nutcracker',cast('2021-11-12 19:30' as date),cast('2021-11-12 21:00' as date),'Arts at the Palace','Arts','Dance','BALLET','This November, the Hudson Ballet Company will be performing the Nutcracker. The story centers around a young girl named Clara who befriends her Uncle Drosselmeyer''s nephew at a Christmas Eve party. Later that night the Nutcracker she receives as a present from her Drosselmeyer comes to life, battling the evil Mouse, and saving her. The victorious Nutcracker transforms into the nephew, who then walks with her through the Land of Snow and introduces her to the Land of Sweets, where the Sugar Plum Fairy and her court celebrate by performing a series of dances for them.',null),
(756670,'Classics Society Movie Night',cast('2015-12-03 19:00' as date),cast('2015-12-03 21:00' as date),'Persson 27','Cultural',NULL,'HCS','Join Hudson Classics Society in watching one of our favorite films inspired by the history and culture of ancient Greece and Rome!  See how these ancient civilizations still influence our world today.  Refreshments provided!',null),
(10003190,'Charred Goosebeak Imrpov Show',cast('2024-03-06 19:00' as date),cast('2024-03-06 20:30' as date),'The MAT','Arts',NULL,'CG','Charred Goosebeak will host an Improv show to bring together campus community through laughter and fun. ',null),
(594031,'Art as Resistance: Faviana Rodriguez Workshop',cast('2015-03-03 19:00' as date),cast('2015-03-03 20:30' as date),'ALANA','Arts',NULL,'SRT','This event is a part of Sisters of the Round Table''s Africana Women''s Week(s). Favianna Rodriguez is an Afro-Peruvian American artist from Oakland, California. She uses her perspective as a child of migrant workers growing up  in a high crime area to forge her identity as a feminist and activist. Growing  up she did not witness positive images of women of color in the media which inspired her to work around issues of equality, race, interdependence, youth activism, and sexuality. During this workshop, Rodriguez will be sharing her artistic process with the Hudson community. All are welcome. ',null),
(7396249,'Mat Series: Quinton Brock',cast('2021-09-17 21:30' as date),cast('2021-09-18 00:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Arts',NULL,'SAA','Rescheduled 9/17 HDBeenDope in Mat to Quinton Brock in HOP.',null),
(10015030,'Zine Making',cast('2024-03-26 18:00' as date),cast('2024-03-26 19:00' as date),'Women''s Studies Center (Lounge)','Arts',NULL,'LAMBDA','Come join QTPOC, TAG, and Hudson LAMBDA for a night of fun, community, and creativity through zine making! All zine ideas are welcome <3',null),
(1025789,'Native American Culture Festival',cast('2016-10-22 08:00' as date),cast('2016-10-22 19:00' as date),'Sanford Field House','Cultural',NULL,'NAIS','The Native American Arts and Culture Festival is a public event that is a precursor to Native American Heritage Month (November). The festival is NASAs biggest event of the year and has been very successful in the past. '||chr(10)||'NASA would like to invite two music and dance groups to perform at the Native American Arts and Culture Festival on Saturday, October 22nd.  One group, the Haudenosaunee Singers and Dancers, represents Indigenous peoples of North America and specifically our local region, while the other group, Ayazamana, represents the Indigenous cultures of South America.  Both groups perform traditional social dances that educate the audience through explanatory narrative and participation.',null),
(1062653,'Korean Culture Association presents: Make Your Own Kimbap!',cast('2016-10-11 11:30' as date),cast('2016-10-11 12:00' as date),'COOP','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','Kimbap is one of the most popular foods in Korean culture to make with friends and family. It is a Korean dish made from steamed white rice and various other ingredients, rolled in gim (edible seaweed) and served in bite-size slices. Kimbap is often eaten during picnics or outdoor events, or as a light lunch. So come learn how to make this simple dish with KCA so you can prepare it for your next picnic or when you''re craving some Korean food!',null),
(1076998,'OASIS Speaker - Helen Zia',cast('2016-12-06 11:30' as date),cast('2016-12-06 13:00' as date),'Women''s Studies Center','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'OASIS','OASIS Brown Bag series invites Helen Zia, who is an award-winning journalist and renowned activist who has been involved in Asian American racial justice movements as well as social justice work on the intersectionality of race, gender, and sexuality. She has been instrumental in fighting for justice on the racially-charged murder of Vincent Chin. She is also involved in activist work against date rape and in supporting Asian American survivors of domestic violence. Helen Zia has written a well-known book on Asian identity and serves on White House Initiative on Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders, among many other involvements. We are hoping to bring her to campus to share about her valuable work and insights on Asian American identity, activism, representation and feminism. Helen Zia  ',null),
(1128321,'St. Nikolaus Day',cast('2016-12-05 08:30' as date),cast('2016-12-05 15:00' as date),'Lawrence Hall','Cultural',NULL,'GC','To celebrate St. Nikolaus Day like German children do, we are planning an event during which we will ask students with classes in Lawrence Hall to leave their shoes outside the classroom and during class, we will fill the shoes with candy. This event will be a fun way to educate students about a common holiday tradition in Germany. Students love candy so this event has been a big hit in the past!',null),
(1246693,'House Party Part III',cast('2017-02-11 22:00' as date),cast('2017-02-12 02:00' as date),'Creative Arts House','Arts',NULL,'HDJ','Social event at Creative Arts House. Food and refreshments will be served to those in attendance. ',null),
(1248467,'University Church Board Game Night',cast('2017-02-23 21:00' as date),cast('2017-02-24 00:00' as date),'Interfaith House','Social',NULL,'UC','Enjoy a night of fellowship and fun with board games and dessert every Thursday, 9pm until midnight, at Interfaith House (104 Broad Street). Typical favorites include games like Avalon, Settlers of Catan, Blokus, Scrabble, and more! Feel free to bring your own games, as well. ',null),
(3294448,'Crawfish Boil',cast('2019-04-19 14:00' as date),cast('2019-04-19 19:00' as date),'Theta Chi Backyard','Fundraising','Concert/Music','TC','We are hoping to host our annual Crawfish Boil a week after SPW on Friday, April 19. The proceeds for the event will go towards the Hamilton Fire Department, and we intend on fundraising by both tabling in the week prior and asking for donations at the door. The event will take place in the Theta Chi backyard. We plan on hiring a band, ordering a dunk tank, and hopefully acquiring permission to have alcohol for anyone 21+. We would also be very appreciative if BandG could drop off tables and chairs that we could set up in the backyard. '||chr(10)||'It is important that we lock down a date well in advance so that we can begin our preparations. I (Jesse) am meeting with Kayla later this afternoon to review our budget plan and receive any advice she may have for setting up the event. If you have any questions about the event, please let me know, but at the very least we would love to get the date of 4/19 set in stone. ',null),
(3349600,'One Love Foundation - Fundraising Event at Beta Theta Pi',cast('2019-04-26 17:00' as date),cast('2019-04-26 18:30' as date),'88 Broad Street (Beta Theta Pi Fraternity)','Fundraising',NULL,'BTP','The brothers of Beta Theta Pi invite all students to help support Team One Love at Hudson University and raise awareness for domestic violence. We will be hosting an event in our back yard with the One Love team here on Hudson''s campus. Those who wish to come and support the cause are welcome to participate in fun activities such as volleyball, basketball, spike-ball and more. We will also be presenting some tasty barbecue options that will be open to all students along with a variety of beverages. Our chapter is happy to be partnering with such a meaningful group at Hudson and promoting a very important cause on college campuses. We look forward to this event and hope for warm weather and a great turnout!  ',null),
(4878616,'Panhellenic Ice Cream Social',cast('2019-09-16 17:00' as date),cast('2019-09-16 18:00' as date),'Gamma Phi Beta Lawn','Social',NULL,'CPC','The Panhellenic Council will be hosting an Ice Cream Social for all affiliated women. Members can come to meet others and enjoy free Gilligan''s Ice Cream.',null),
(4885035,'Stretching for Success One Bowl at a Time',cast('2019-09-07 18:00' as date),cast('2019-09-07 19:00' as date),'Curtis Lawn','Community Service',NULL,'SAA','De-stress with some partner yoga and yummy acai bowls! '||chr(10)||'If you don''t have a mat or a partner, we have them for you! Come meet new people and excerise in a healthy, relaxing way. '||chr(10)||'Sponsored by Hudson Activities Board. ',null),
