(517173,'The 7th Annual Guy Fawkes Masquerade Ball',cast('2014-11-14 21:00' as date),cast('2014-11-15 00:00' as date),'Clark Room, Second Floor HOP','Arts','Dance','HBD','You are cordially invited to the 7th Annual Guy Fawkes Masquerade Ball! Friday November 14th, 9pm-midnight in the Clark Room, 2nd floor of the HOP.'||chr(10)||'Hosted by Hudson Ballroom Dancers, the Masquerade is a ballroom tradition every fall semester around the 5th of November, representing the day of an uprising led by Guy Fawkes, a masked anarchist who became a pop culture symbol after the movie V for Vendetta. The Masquerade is a formal dance party with multiple styles of ballroom dance music (as well as popular music).  Formal attire is requested, masks will be provided, and refreshments will be served.    ',null),
(518041,'Final''s Study Break',cast('2015-05-03 16:00' as date),cast('2015-05-03 18:00' as date),'Academic Quad','Social',NULL,'SAA','Hudson Activities Board will be hosting a final''s study break and celebration of the end of year by hosting a field day on the academic quad, ending with a BBQ from Holy Smokes. There will be a wide variety of team games that participants can come and play when they have a convenient break from studying. The games will begin around 4 PM and the BBQ will come around 5 or 6 PM',null),
(538290,'Study Break: Bowling and Basketball',cast('2014-12-10 17:00' as date),cast('2014-12-10 20:30' as date),'Reid Center Bowling Alley','Athletics','Club Sports','RDR','Hudson Athletics and Recreation would like to invite you to join us for a Study Break on Wed 12\10.Free Bowling and Pizza in Reid Center from 5 - 7 p.m. followed by a Hudson Women''s Basketball game at 7 p.m. ',null),
(5574262,'Teddies and Treats Valentine''s Day Celebration',cast('2020-02-13 18:00' as date),cast('2020-02-13 20:00' as date),'Case-Geyer Library, Batza Room','Social',NULL,'SAA','Make Valentine''s Day extra sweet this year! Create a cute stuffed animal for someone special (or yourself) while enjoying our DIY candy bar, fresh-made cotton candy, and gourmet chocolate samplings from Hamilton''s own Maxwells Chocolates.  '||chr(10)||'Hosted by the Hudson Activities Board.',null),
(623084,'Interfaith Dinners',cast('2015-11-12 18:00' as date),cast('2015-11-12 19:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. Each dinner has a theme and there are discussions or presentations that are related to that theme for students to participate in during the dinner. These dinners have been extremely successful in the past.',null),
