(9897151,'February LGBTQ+ Book Club',cast('2024-02-29 18:00' as date),cast('2024-02-29 19:00' as date),'The Rainbow Room (Bryan Complex Basement)','Arts',NULL,'LAMBDA','Join us in reading the anthology, Common Bonds, for LGBTQ+ Initatives February Book Club (in celebration of ASAW) on the 29th at 6pm in the Rainbow Room! '||chr(10)||'Common Bonds is an anthology of speculative short stories and poetry featuring aromantic characters. At the heart of this collection are the bonds that impact our lives from beginning to end: platonic relationships. Within this anthology, a cursed seamstress finds comfort in the presence of a witch, teams of demon hunters work with their rival to save one of their own, a peculiar scholar gets attached to those he was meant to study, and queerplatonic shopkeepers guide their pupil as they explore their relationship needs and desires. Through nineteen stories and poems, Common Bonds explores the ways platonic relationships enrich our lives.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'We only have so many copies, so it is first come, first served (if you want to purchase your own copy or get one from a library, you can still join us in the discussion! Just email R at rhunsicker@hudson.edu and let em know!).',null),
(502771,'Midterm Study Break',cast('2014-10-19 18:00' as date),cast('2014-10-19 20:00' as date),'Coop TV room','Arts',NULL,'SAA','Come enjoy a relaxing break from your studies in the Coop TV room, with entertainment provided by the Hudson Activties Board!',null),
(593455,'Cabaret',cast('2015-02-27 19:00' as date),cast('2015-02-27 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theater','Arts',NULL,'MAT',' The theme for this year''s musical theatre Cabaret is "Come Together Cabaret," which celebrates the Hudson community coming together to appreciate some feel-good songs despite the tension of last semester. So come join us in enjoying some great songs performed by lots of talented Hudson students at this year''s Cabaret!',null),
(735263,'Nutcracker',cast('2015-11-19 19:00' as date),cast('2015-11-19 21:00' as date),'Brehmer Theatre','Arts',NULL,'BALLET','Please join the Hudson Ballet Company for their annual production of the Nutcracker! This holiday favorite is student-directed, student-choreographed, and student-performed, with guest appearances by children from the Hamilton community. ',null),
