(1227640,'Summer in Winter with CVS (Summer Roll Creation)',cast('2017-02-25 13:00' as date),cast('2017-02-25 14:30' as date),'Alana Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'HVS','Have a taste of summer in winter with Hudson Vietnamese Society'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Summer in Winter with HVS is our organizations second public event in the 2016-2017 school year. The members of HVS hope to not only fulfil desires for a taste of summer amidst the cold snowy winter, but also introduce the Vietnamese Summer Roll to the Hudson family as it is as much a part of the Vietnamese cultural identity as Pho. This event will not only serve as an introduction to Vietnamese cuisine but also as a bonding activity and an opportunity for everyone to learn how to make a refreshing and healthy dish.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Summer in Winter with HVS welcomes all member of the public. HVS will send an event announcement to those who are currently on our mailing list as well as add it to the Events Calendar on Get Involved at Hudson. As of now the event is scheduled to take place on February 25th in the ALANA kitchen.  ',null),
(1241484,'Holi 2017',cast('2017-04-15 12:00' as date),cast('2017-04-15 13:00' as date),'Whitnall Field','Cultural','Religious/Spiritual','HINDU','The Hindu Student''s Association will be holding the yearly Holi celebration in honor of the festival of colors. The celebration will involve gathering students on Whitnall field with colors and refreshments. '||chr(10)||'The Royal India Grill will be catering for the event. Holi has traditionally gathered around 400 attendees from the Hudson campus and Hamilton. We wish to work on the success of previous Holi celebrations to engage in conversations around Hinduism and the importance of community.'||chr(10)||' ',null),
(1241488,'HSA Brown Bag Series Spring 2017',cast('2017-03-10 12:00' as date),cast('2017-03-10 13:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Spirituality',NULL,'HINDU','The Hindu Students'' Association regroups students who identify culturally and spiritually as Hindus. The HSA has been organizing Brown Bags involving Professors and student members around different themes such as Hindus and the Indian Diaspora. This year we are planning to continuing this trend.',null),
