(4906898,'The 13th Hour',cast('2019-09-13 16:00' as date),cast('2019-09-13 17:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social',NULL,'SAA','Celebrate Hudson Day with the Hudson Activities Board! It''s mocktail happy hour at the pub featuring themed Hudson mocktails like the "Cab Driver" and pub snacks. Stay and play darts, pool, and shuffle board to win Hudson themed prizes or just enter our raffle! ',null),
(5015539,'Ron Baker Memorial Fundraiser',cast('2019-10-05 19:30' as date),cast('2019-10-05 20:30' as date),'Class of 1965 Arena','Fundraising',NULL,'BTP','Come join the mens hockey team at the home opening game of the 2019-20 season on October 5th against RIT at 7:30 PM. The game will be in memory of long-time supporter and community member, Ron Baker. To honor Rons remarkable impact over the past 30+ years at Hudson, the brothers of Beta Theta Pi will be hosting a fundraiser with men''s hockey during their home opener, and all proceeds will directly benefit the Baker Family. There will be plenty of ways to donate during the game such as a 50/50 raffle, Chuck a Puck (after the 1st period), raffle giveaways and more. You can also donate directly to the Baker family with credit/debit/HUES Cards through the online link provided. Hope to see everyone there! ',null),
(5599194,'Open Mic',cast('2020-02-21 20:00' as date),cast('2020-02-21 21:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts','Theater','HSU','Come down and enjoy the first Hudson Stand Up Open Mic of the semester! ',null),
(593954,'The Thickness: Aja Monet',cast('2015-02-27 21:00' as date),cast('2015-02-28 00:00' as date),'CAH (100 Broad St.)','Arts',NULL,'SRT','Sisters of the Round Table in collaboration with Lounge and Broad Street Association, present The Thickness: Aja Monet. The Thickness is a traditional part of SORT''s Africana Women''s Week(s). Hudson students will have the opportunity to listen to and engage with an award-winning spoken word artist, whose words will be sure to inspire, spread love, encourage, and most of all heal. Not only that, they will be able to share a meal with her and ask questions in the name of pursuing their own poetry, activism, art and love. There will be an open mic afterwards. All are welcome!',null),
(598040,'Classics Coffee Hour',cast('2015-02-13 15:00' as date),cast('2015-02-13 16:00' as date),'Lawrence 112/114','Cultural',NULL,'HCS','If you have a passion for the classics, explore it further by coming to the Classics Coffee Hours in the Classics Lounge (Law 112/114)!',null),
(621693,'Gent Treadly Concert',cast('2015-03-27 20:00' as date),cast('2015-03-27 21:00' as date),'Donovans Pub','Arts',NULL,'BROS','Following the Whoopi Goldberg Lecture!!Join BSA, Brothers, CAC, and Phi Delta Theta in welcoming Gent Treadly this Friday at 8:00 PM in Donovan''s Pub!Gent Treadly was founded by Hudson alum Greg Koerner ''88. Friday''s show will also feature New Orleans jazz royalty Charles Neville!FREE FOOD FROM DONOVANS PUB',null),
(623083,'Interfaith Dinners',cast('2015-10-08 18:00' as date),cast('2015-10-08 18:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. Each dinner has a theme and there are discussions or presentations that are related to that theme for students to participate in during the dinner. These dinners have been extremely successful in the past.',null),
