(6632656,'Fall 2020 Dancefest',cast('2020-12-05 19:00' as date),cast('2020-12-05 19:30' as date),'Online','Arts','Dance','GDT','It''s your favorite high-energy Hudson tradition, but with a virtual twist!'||chr(10)||'Although this isn''t a traditional Dancefest, this small virtual showcase features many of Hudson''s talented dance student groups. Tune in Saturday night to watch. '||chr(10)||'https://youtu.be/AsJXpAAWW4s',null),
(7083837,'Earth Day Reusable Utensils Event',cast('2021-04-24 14:00' as date),cast('2021-04-24 15:00' as date),'Academic Quad','Social','Sustainability','SEA','On Saturday the 24th, we will be hosting an event from 2 pm - 4 pm on the Academic Quad to celebrate Earth Day. We will have a tent set up with some small activities as well as lawn games provided by Shaw Wellness. The activities on the table will consist of educational material that we have put together as a club in order to help educate our peers on the proper ways to use reusable utensils and why they are beneficial to individual health and the environment. After doing some of the activities we have at the tables, including the table set up by Shaw Wellness who will be collaborating with us on this event, the students will receive a reusable utensils pouch. We will then ask them to take a picture next to the inflatable Earthball (which we will be setting up on the quad) with their utensils and post it on Instagram, tagging both SEA and Shaw Wellness. This event will help Hudson move towards its goal of becoming a Zero-Waste campus by providing students with items they need to help them reduce their own waste when dining out. Additionally, our educational component will incentivize students to share their newly acquired knowledge with their peers and will increase the likelihood that they take more sustainability positive steps in other aspects of their lives.',null),
(715015,'SGA Ice Cream Social',cast('2015-09-10 11:20' as date),cast('2015-09-10 12:20' as date),'Chapel','Social',NULL,'SGA',NULL||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'Come learn about the different ways to get involved in SGA, meet your current representatives, and socialize with new and returning students!! Ice cream from Gilligan''s will be provided!! (Yes, that means Raider Passion!!!'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'',null),
(722312,'MSA Brown Bags',cast('2015-09-04 12:30' as date),cast('2015-09-04 12:30' as date),'Chapel Basement','Cultural',NULL,'HMSA','The MSA has been holding Brown Bags to raise awareness in the Hudson community'||chr(10)||'about contemporary issues in the Islamic world. Professors at Hudson from different departments'||chr(10)||'and with a wide range of expertise will share their insights on Islamic society, culture,'||chr(10)||'spirituality or politics. Students will have the opportunity to engage in discussions on these'||chr(10)||'important topics, while they enjoy delicious halal South Asian dishes.',null),
(722320,'Eid Banquet',cast('2015-10-16 18:00' as date),cast('2015-10-16 19:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Arts',NULL,'HMSA','The Muslim Student Association would like to hold this banquet to celebrate an important Islamic holiday and to share it with the Hudson campus. We are hiring an 8 part ethnic band, which specializes in qawwali music, a form of Muslim devotional music. We will also provide an entire repast of halal South Asian food, and teach interested students about the importance of this holiday, known as Eid al-Adha, in the Muslim faith and culture.',null),
(7312155,'Bubble Tea Cultural Social',cast('2021-10-01 14:00' as date),cast('2021-10-01 15:00' as date),'McGregory/Wynn quad','Cultural',NULL,'HIC','Welcome / Welcome back event co-hosted by Hudson International Community (CIC) and Office of International Student Service (OISS), where international and local students are all welcome to participate! We serve Asian snacks and just-made bubble tea of various kinds. Don''t hesitate to come over if you want to have some afternoon bubble tea and chill out with your fellow peers! This event would be an excellent opportunity for you to make connections with each other at the beginning of the semester! :)',null),
(7407060,'Midnight Movies: Hamilton Movie Theater',cast('2021-10-22 23:45' as date),cast('2021-10-23 01:00' as date),'Hamilton Movie Theater','Arts','Movie/Film','SAA','Midnight Movies are back at the Hamilton Theater!! Movies are first come, first serve. '||chr(10)||'Free entry with your HUES Card and free pizza from Slices.'||chr(10)||'Movie Screenings'||chr(10)||'Friday, September 3rd - Shang Chi and the Legend fo the Ten Rings'||chr(10)||'Friday, October 1st - Addams Family 2'||chr(10)||'Saturday, October 2nd - Venom 2'||chr(10)||'Friday, October 22nd - Dune'||chr(10)||'Friday, November 12th - Eternals',null),
