(800498,'Hudson Women in Business Coffee Hour Series',cast('2016-03-08 20:00' as date),cast('2016-03-08 21:00' as date),'Hudson University','Group Business',NULL,'HWIB','This series involves monthly coffee hours to educate members on different aspects of the business industry. ',null),
(821030,'Interfaith Dinners',cast('2015-04-09 18:00' as date),cast('2015-04-09 18:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. Each dinner has a theme and there are discussions or presentations that are related to that theme for students to participate in during the dinner. These dinners have been extremely successful in the past.',null),
(8373336,'Boston University Travel Conference- BARMUN XIV',cast('2022-10-06 08:00' as date),cast('2022-10-09 12:00' as date),'Boston University','Thoughtful Learning','Sustainability','MUN','Hudson attending Boston University model UN conference Oct 6-9, the long fall break weekend. This is a great conference to meet other students from other schools with similar interests, practice public speaking and debate, and explore Boston. All are welcome to tryout and attend. Come to the first meeting, Monday, Sept 12 at 7pm if interested, HO 101.',null),
(8447624,'Standup Comedy Show',cast('2022-10-01 19:00' as date),cast('2022-10-01 19:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts',NULL,'HSU','A 3045-minute standup comedy show at Donovan''s pub by members of our club',null),
(8542245,'CSA Vibe Session',cast('2022-10-27 18:00' as date),cast('2022-10-27 18:30' as date),'Harlem Renaissance Center (Basement of Crawshaw Hall in Bryan Complex)','Cultural',NULL,'CSA','The Caribbean Students Association in collaboration with the HRC will be hosting a Vibe Session on October 27th at 6 pm in the Harlem Renaissance Center, this is an event based around "vibing to"/ enjoying good music, along with some of our favorite cultural foods, and providing people with a safe space to unwind and get to know each other.'||chr(10)||'This event is sponsored by Hancock Commons.',null),
(8590418,'Grill Club Taqueria',cast('2022-11-12 13:00' as date),cast('2022-11-12 15:00' as date),'Parker Commons','Social',NULL,'HGC','Our third meating of the semester, featuring pulled pork, chicken, steak, and veggie tacos! Sides include: chips and guac/salsa, refreshments.',null),
(8883088,'Ramentine',cast('2023-02-11 17:00' as date),cast('2023-02-11 19:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','Asian Cultural Club (SACC), Hudson International Club (CIC), Korean Culture Association (KCA), and Hudson Vietnamese Society (HVS), Hudson Japanese Cultural Community (CJCC) wishes to cultivate a cross-cultural understanding of Asian culture through Ramentine, an event where participants can gather, share their stories, and enjoy a common dish in Asia: instant ramen noodles. Through this annual event, we hope Hudson students are reminded of their connection with the Asian culture through the familiar taste of ramen, while cultivating an understanding of our shared culture, thereby creating a community for all and strengthening the bond among members of the Hudson community. Besides having the opportunity to try out noodles of different Asian cultures, Hudson students will also get the chance to make noodles to their own liking. Besides understanding the Asian culture of gathering and food-sharing, we believe this event will be meaningful to Hudson members because they can also learn about various ramen noodle customs, as well as relax, chat with friends, and enjoy a hot meal amidst a cold winter day; thus, this event will bring people together and strengthen interconnections among participants through the common language of cuisine and cross-cultural holidays. Events will be in three different rooms where students can choose different activities including card writing and ramen-enjoying. This event is inclusive to all campus members who are interested in Japanese or Asian culture!',null),
(9041548,'13 Days of Green Kickoff Event',cast('2023-04-10 16:00' as date),cast('2023-04-10 17:00' as date),'Academic Quad','Social','Outdoor Education','GEG','Kick-off the Office of Sustainabilitys 13 Days of Green series on the Academic Quad with a celebration of sustainability at Hudson. Enjoy the warmth of spring while meeting members of Hudson organizations focused on sustainability and environmental issues. Tabling organizations and topics include:'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'Outdoor Education'||chr(10)||'Sustainability Graduation Pledge'||chr(10)||'Beekeeping Club'||chr(10)||'STEM/Sustainability Career Advisors'||chr(10)||'Sustainability Representatives (S-Reps)'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||'After you visit tables from campus partners to learn how to get involved, you can listen to live music, play lawn games and grab a Maxwells ice cream cone for a low-waste treat! Vegan and gluten-free options available.'||chr(10)||'We cant wait to see you there!'||chr(10)||'Rain Location: Coop Media RoomThis event is part of the Office of Sustainabilitys 13 Days of Green series leading up to Earth Day.',null),
(9056875,'Be the Match Donor Registry',cast('2023-04-25 10:00' as date),cast('2023-04-25 14:00' as date),'Frank Dining Hall and Library Patio','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','COVE','Volunteer to help table with the Hudson Football Team and Public Health Initiatives on April 25 and 26 or stop by to join the Be The Match donor registry. The national Be The Match registry pairs volunteer blood stem cell donors with thousands of patients diagnosed with life-threatening blood cancers. By giving 1-hour of your time as a volunteer or signing-up as a potential donor, you are increasing the chance to save a life. Visit the tables outside Frank Dining Hall and the Library Patio between 10am - 3pm for free giveaways, more information on Be The Match, and to join the registry. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Sign-up here to volunteer!',null),
(954488,'Burritos con los Santitos',cast('2016-10-27 18:00' as date),cast('2016-10-27 19:00' as date),'COOP TV room','Social',NULL,'NC','Come celebrate All Saints Day with the Newman Community! We will be learning about the saints, learning about what it means to be a saint, and eating great burritos!',null),
(9880349,'Midnight Philosophy Society Meeting',cast('2024-02-17 22:00' as date),cast('2024-02-18 01:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social',NULL,'MPS','Midnight Philosophy is a vibrant community of inquisitive and curious students who are excited to explore diverse and relevant philosophical topics! We host welcoming student-to-student conversations about morality, society, religion, metaphysics, and epistemology. Our members are diverse in their beliefs, and we are open to absolutely anyone, with no philosophical experience or major declaration necessary. ',null),
(9880350,'Midnight Philosophy Society Meeting',cast('2024-02-24 22:00' as date),cast('2024-02-25 01:00' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Social',NULL,'MPS','Midnight Philosophy is a vibrant community of inquisitive and curious students who are excited to explore diverse and relevant philosophical topics! We host welcoming student-to-student conversations about morality, society, religion, metaphysics, and epistemology. Our members are diverse in their beliefs, and we are open to absolutely anyone, with no philosophical experience or major declaration necessary. ',null),
(735200,'French Club Coffee Hour',cast('2015-10-21 16:15' as date),cast('2015-10-21 16:00' as date),'Lawrence Hall 2nd floor','Cultural',NULL,'FC','Come enjoy a presentation on a Francophone topic with snacks included such as croissants every month with a Francophone film screening to follow that weekend.',null),
(1227633,'Ballet Class',cast('2017-02-16 19:30' as date),cast('2017-02-16 21:00' as date),'Huntington 303','Arts',NULL,'BALLET','The Hudson Ballet Company provides classes taught by Paris Wilcox, a former principal dancer with the Kansas City Ballet, for students of all levels of experience. The classes help develop students'' technique, flexibility, strength, and artistic expression. Classes take place Tuesdays and Thursdays.',null),
(621158,'The Red Shirts Concert',cast('2015-04-18 20:30' as date),cast('2015-04-18 20:30' as date),'Donovan''s Pub','Arts',NULL,'SAA','Come to Donovan''s Pub to enjoy a concert by The Red Shirts, one of Hudson''s own student bands!',null),
(623162,'Here and Now Theater Company Presents "But All My Friends Are..."',cast('2015-04-09 19:00' as date),cast('2015-04-09 19:30' as date),'Golden Auditorium, Little Hall','Arts',NULL,'BROS','Brothers in collaboration with the Theater Depaartment are bringing Here and Now Theater Company to perform a 90-minute show of 10 short acts, each act concerning an aspect of being a minority in America through comedy, song, and acting. ',null),
(702781,'DDT Auditions',cast('2015-09-05 16:30' as date),cast('2015-09-05 17:00' as date),'Ryan Studio 212','Arts',NULL,'DDT','We are looking for new members for DDT, a high energy, fierce, and talented dance group! We perform at DanceFest every semester, and additionally perform at other Hudson events throughout the year. Nothing is needed in preparation. For further information, please contact Kristen Weymouth at kweymouth@hudson.edu',null),
(7516528,'The Nutcracker',cast('2021-11-13 14:00' as date),cast('2021-11-13 15:30' as date),'Arts at the Palace','Arts','Dance','BALLET','This November, the Hudson Ballet Company will be performing the Nutcracker. The story centers around a young girl named Clara who befriends her Uncle Drosselmeyer''s nephew at a Christmas Eve party. Later that night the Nutcracker she receives as a present from her Drosselmeyer comes to life, battling the evil Mouse, and saving her. The victorious Nutcracker transforms into the nephew, who then walks with her through the Land of Snow and introduces her to the Land of Sweets, where the Sugar Plum Fairy and her court celebrate by performing a series of dances for them.',null),
(9584434,'The Nutcracker',cast('2023-11-10 19:30' as date),cast('2023-11-10 21:00' as date),'Arts at the Palace','Arts','Dance','BALLET','The Nutcracker is a widely-known holiday performance and tradition for people all across the world, enjoyed by both the audiences and the performers. This ballet shares the story of a young girl who is gifted a Nutcracker that transforms into a prince and together they travel to a land of fantasy and sweets. The production is performed by Hudson students and dancers from the Hamilton community. Tickets are free and available through this link: https://www.hamiltoncreates.com/registration ',null),
(1109945,'Cabaret Fall 2016',cast('2016-11-10 19:00' as date),cast('2016-11-10 21:00' as date),'The Palace Theater','Arts',NULL,'MAT','Cabaret is a bi-yearly event that brings a musical theater showcase to the Hudson and Hamilton Community. Performed downtown at the Palace Theater, Cabaret puts on a show that includes great renditions by students of pop music and musical theater alike.',null),
(513835,'Dancefest',cast('2014-12-05 18:00' as date),cast('2014-12-05 20:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts',NULL,'GDT','Come watch your peers perform in the student organized and choreographed event, Dancefest!The doors will open at 5:30, and the show begins at 6!',null),
(5196030,'Dancefest Fall 2019',cast('2019-12-07 18:30' as date),cast('2019-12-07 21:00' as date),'Hudson Memorial Chapel','Arts','Dance','GDT','It''s your favorite high-energy Hudson tradition! Now in our 22nd year, Groove Dance Troupe invites you to get ready for celebrating a "higher love" through dance. '||chr(10)||'Doors open at 6pm, show starts at 6:30pm.'||chr(10)||'Warning: Some songs in the show may contain explicit language that may be perceived as inappropriate or offensive. Dancefests mission is to create a space for dancers to express themselves freely and exercise creative freedom in their choice of music. If you have any other further questions, please contact Groove Dance Troupe at groove@hudson.edu.',null),
(623116,'Newman Retreat',cast('2015-10-30 15:30' as date),cast('2015-11-01 13:00' as date),'Good News Center, Utica, NY','Spirituality',NULL,'NC','The Newman Community provides this retreat as a way for Catholics and non-Catholics alike to grow in their awareness of the Catholic faith through a weekend of prayer and activities.',null),
(708409,'Island Touch: Introduction to Latin American Dance',cast('2015-09-17 19:00' as date),cast('2015-09-17 20:00' as date),'Huntington Gym','Arts',NULL,'LASO','The Latin American Student Organization (LASO) and the Latin American Dance Company (LAD) have invited the Island Touch Dance Academy and its founders, Jorge Burgos and Tanja Kensinger, to perform and lead a dance workshop in honor of Hispanic Heritage Month (HHM) tentatively on Thursday September 17. Internationally renowned Latin dancers, Jorge and Tanja have performed and taught at Salsa Congresses and Bachata Festivals in over 25 different countries, and shared the stage with top Latin dancers, including Eddie Torres, Griselle Ponce, Yamulee, and Victor and Burju. They have choreographed for noted bachata artists such as Toby Love, Prince Royce, Xtreme, Dominic Marte, and Carlos y Alejandra. In 2011, Jorge and Tanja founded the Island Touch Dance Academy in Rockville, Maryland to instruct students in salsa, bachata, merengue, and cha cha dance styles; the academy now has competitive bachata teams in 14 U.S. cities and 16 around the world performing the directors choreographies.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'The event, which aims to both celebrate Latin American styles of dance in honor of Hispanic Heritage Month and encourage a greater appreciation for dance on campus, will feature a bachata performance by the New York Touch dance team and a salsa routine by its directors, Jorge and Tanja. Jorge and Tanja will follow these performances with a two hour-long, beginner-level workshop that will introduce event participants to the bachata style of dance. The directors will instruct participants in the footwork, partnerwork, styling, and technique to a segment of their own bachata choreography. Island Touchs workshops have been commonly characterized as high-energy, dynamic, and easy to follow. This event will expose participants to two widely popular styles of Latin dance and provide them with the fundamentals of dancing bachata. The performances and workshop will be open to the entire Hudson community, members of the Hamilton community, and interested members of surrounding schools. Dancers of all skills levels will be encouraged to attend.',null),
(772310,'Public Health in Rural Uganda Immersion Trip',cast('2016-01-01 06:00' as date),cast('2016-01-16 18:00' as date),'Indigo Foundation and Bwindi Community Hospital','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HGHC','Global Health Initiative is hosting an immersion trip that will focus on the local health complexities of rural Uganda, where students would spend the first week volunteering at Indigo Foundation and then spend a second week at the Bwindi Community Hospital. The goal of the trip is to engage and educate students on public health, as well as expose students to a future career in health and related fields.',null),
(902759,'Stone a Heathen',cast('2016-04-18 16:00' as date),cast('2016-04-18 17:00' as date),'Academic Quad','Community Service',NULL,'SASS','For this event anyone can volunteer to be pelted with water balloons as penance for heinous acts such as eating shellfish and wearing a cotton-polyester blend t-shirt. The purpose of this event is to raise awareness of religious persecution while bringing our thriving religious community together for an afternoon of fun in the lovely spring weather (or whatever it is we have here in Hamilton).'||chr(10)||'Anyone can come over and purchase water balloons to throw at your heathen friends. Proceeds will go to the Interfaith Alliance. Their website is: http://interfaithalliance.org.',null),
(9901196,'In the Mood for Love Screening',cast('2024-02-09 16:30' as date),cast('2024-02-16 17:30' as date),'Golden Auditorium','Arts',NULL,'HFS','Watching In the Mood for Love in Little 114',null),
(1119426,'Death Proof',cast('2016-11-12 17:00' as date),cast('2016-11-12 19:00' as date),'Golden Auditorium, Little Hall','Arts',NULL,'HFS','Join Hudson Film Society to watch Tarantino''s 2007 action horror film starring Kurt Russell and Rosario Dawson!',null),
(1136044,'Interfaith Dinner',cast('2017-02-09 18:00' as date),cast('2017-02-09 19:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. Each dinner has a theme and discussion of this theme is co-led by members from two different Chaplaincy groups. This discussion-based style allows students who attend to participate during the dinner. These dinners have been extremely successful in the past.',null),
(1248474,'University Church Board Game Night',cast('2017-04-20 21:00' as date),cast('2017-04-20 23:00' as date),'Interfaith House','Social','Religious/Spiritual','UC','Enjoy a night of fellowship and fun with board games and dessert every Thursday, 9pm until midnight, at Interfaith House (104 Broad Street). Typical favorites include games like Avalon, Settlers of Catan, Blokus, Scrabble, and more! Feel free to bring your own games, as well. ',null),
(1248475,'University Church Board Game Night',cast('2017-04-27 21:00' as date),cast('2017-04-27 23:00' as date),'Interfaith House','Social','Religious/Spiritual','UC','Enjoy a night of fellowship and fun with board games and dessert every Thursday, 9pm until midnight, at Interfaith House (104 Broad Street). Typical favorites include games like Avalon, Settlers of Catan, Blokus, Scrabble, and more! Feel free to bring your own games, as well. ',null),
(1283525,'Keynote Speaker: Ebony Mcgee',cast('2017-04-07 15:00' as date),cast('2017-04-07 15:30' as date),'Love Auditorium','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HMAPS','The proposed event is a keynote speaker who will be discussing mental health disparities faced by underrepresented and marginalized groups on college campuses. The MAPS Executive Board recently attended the Steve Fund Conference at Washington University at St. Louis where we spent the entire day interacting with professionals and voicing our ideas about the steps universities must take when addressing mental health. As agents of change and students inspired by these meaningful discussions, we prioritized reaching out to this speaker and bringing her to Hudson, in hopes of promoting cultural competency and awareness in the realm of mental health. This panel discussion would benefit all marginalized communities pursuing a career in the medical/health care delivery field, and would equip students with the tools necessary to receive support. Promoting awareness about the importance of mental health destigmatization would directly reinforce MAPS mission on this campus.This discussion will assist students in their educational pursuits and focus on fostering an environment where students can achieve academic excellence and personal fulfillment.',null),
(4881677,'Women''s Club Soccer Game',cast('2019-09-08 14:00' as date),cast('2019-09-08 15:00' as date),'Cortland State University','Athletics','Club Sports','SCQW','Women''s Club Soccer Game',null),
