(564212,'Democracy Matters Brown Bag',cast('2015-02-05 11:30' as date),cast('2015-02-05 13:30' as date),'O''Connor Campus Center Television Room','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'DM','Lunchtime brownbag presentations by university professors on topics relevent to Democracy Matters. Provides catering and an environment for disucssion on these topics. '||chr(10)||'Feb 5th -- Professor Jay Mandle, Department of Economics - "Economic Inequality/Political Inequality: Where Are We Heading?"'||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' March 5, Professor Michael Johnston "The Deeper Corruption: Political Money, Inequality, and the Credibility of Democracy" '||chr(10)||''||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' March 26th - Professor Joan Mandle - Associate Professor of Sociology and Anthropology, Emerita; Former Director of Women''s Studies -  "Who Owns Democracy: Women in Politics, Why So Few? ',null),
