(8060808,'Redistricting, Gerrymandering, and the 2022 Elections',cast('2022-04-13 16:15' as date),cast('2022-04-13 16:15' as date),'Persson Auditorium (027)','Thoughtful Learning','Volunteer and Community Service ','HVP','Join the Hudson Vote Project and the Hudson Professional Network in a discussion on redistricting and gerrymandering, focusing on redistricting in New York State and state- and nation-wide implications on the upcoming 2022 Midterm Elections. Panelists include Political Science Professors Sam Rosenfeld and Dominika Koter, and the Director of the Max. A. Shacknai Center for Outreach, Volunteerism, and Education (COVE) Jeremey Wattles.'||chr(10)||'We will also have good from Royal Indian Grill (RIG).'||chr(10)||'https://hudson.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_GAseVQY4R4Kiukn8ApKXtw',null),
