(3308897,'Anime Cosplay Formal',cast('2019-04-13 19:00' as date),cast('2019-04-13 21:00' as date),'Edge Cafe','Social','Dance','HAS','For SPW, Anime Society, Cosplay Photography, and Internet Gamers (League of Legends Club) invite you to a night of anime cosplay at the Edge Cafe. '||chr(10)||'Come dressed as your favorite anime character, in costume, or in formal wear. '||chr(10)||'Food, photo booth, and dancing! ',null),
(4905905,'Milk and Cookies',cast('2019-09-13 19:00' as date),cast('2019-09-13 18:30' as date),'Beta Theta Pi Chapter House','Social',NULL,'BTP','Please join the brothers of Beta Theta Pi down at 88 Broad Street for some homemade cookies baked by our chef, Liz King and some good conversation. Nothing quite gets the conversation going like a tall glass of milk and a fresh chocolate chip cookie!',null),
(5038555,'Senior Cider Study Break',cast('2019-10-20 16:15' as date),cast('2019-10-20 16:45' as date),'Batza Room','Fundraising',NULL,'SCGC','The Senior Class Giving Committee invites you to take a break from studying to enjoy apple cider and cider donuts from the Clinton Cider Mill.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'If you would like to make your senior class gift of any amount, you may do so at the event or by following this link.',null),
(521094,'Polynesian Awareness Week',cast('2014-11-10 11:00' as date),cast('2014-11-14 19:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'ALANA','Do you know where Samoa is? What about Tonga, Aotearoa, or Tahiti? And what, if anything, do these places have to do with Hawaii? If you didnt know: they are all located in the Polynesian Triangle, and their specific peoples are known as Polynesians. The ALANA Cultural Center, Native American Studies Department, Office of Residential Life, and Hawaii Club have joined together to host the first-ever Polynesian Awareness Week! From Monday, November 10 through Friday, November 14, please join in on the fun and culturally immersive activities planned, and while youre at it learn about a new culture or two!Monday 11/10 (11a-1p): Polynesian Awareness Week Kick-Off in the Coop.Tuesday 11/11 (5p-7p): Tongan Cooking Demo facilitated by Salote Tenisi in the ALANA kitchen.Wednesday 11/12 (5p-7p): Hula/Tahitian Dance Workshop taught by Lokelani Cummings in the ALANA Cultural Center. Yummy snacks will be provided!Thursday 11/13 (7p-9p): "Hawaiian as a Culture" Dinner Discussion. Come join in on the conversation revolving around cultural appropriation and how it affects people of Native Hawaiian descent. This event will be catered by Oliveri''s, featuring assorted apps and pasta dishes.Friday 11/14 (5p-7p): Aloha Friday Paina! Join us in the MPR room of ALANA to celebrate a successful week of cultural education! Music, dancing, food, and friendships will be plentiful!',null),
(564181,'Tea Club Study Break',cast('2015-05-05 19:30' as date),cast('2015-05-05 20:30' as date),'Coop Main Lounge/Fireplace','Cultural',NULL,'TTC','Take a break from finals to enjoy a well-needed break from the clamor of final exams, as well as some of the best East-Asian tea Hudson has to offer (for free!). Drop by the Coop fireplace room anytime between 7:30 and 9:30 PM to enjoy this event. Highly recommended for those who are planning to stay up late!',null),
(619702,'Beyond Ebola',cast('2015-04-02 11:30' as date),cast('2015-04-02 11:30' as date),'Lawrence 205, Hudson University','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'HGHC','Beyond Ebola: Emerging Infectious Diseases and the Future of U.S. Public HealthFears of Ebola in the U.S. have faded, but does that mean Americans can stop worrying about infectious disease? In this brown bag lecture, Prof. Geoff Holm will discuss other emerging diseases, and what the (near) future may hold for the U.S. public health system.',null),
(623085,'Interfaith Dinners',cast('2015-12-03 18:00' as date),cast('2015-12-03 19:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. Each dinner has a theme and there are discussions or presentations that are related to that theme for students to participate in during the dinner. These dinners have been extremely successful in the past.',null),
(623115,'Burritos con los Santitos',cast('2015-11-05 18:00' as date),cast('2015-11-05 20:00' as date),'COOP TV Room','Spirituality',NULL,'NC','Come celebrate All Saints Day with the Newman Community! We will be learning about the saints, learning about what it means to be a saint, and eating great burritos! ',null),
(7021105,'Tea Club X Korean Culture Association',cast('2021-03-26 15:00' as date),cast('2021-03-26 15:30' as date),'Alana Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','Tea Club will be distributing pre-packaged Korean Snacks to a group of students who sign up. The Pre-packaged tea and snacks will be distributed at ALANA via the tea club and KCA core. All items will be pre-packaged and officers will be distributing the items while wearing gloves and masks. People will come in during their assigned time and will collect their items and then attend the cultural event, where KCA will present about Korean tea, on Zoom. ',null),
(7389921,'Mat Series: Olivia Lunny ft. Lisa Heller',cast('2021-09-24 21:00' as date),cast('2021-09-24 22:00' as date),'Academic Quad','Arts','Concert/Music','SAA','Lisa Heller, a Hudson alum, will open with her band for Olivia Lunny! Concert starts at 9pm under the quad tent. Food trucks will be present!! ',null),
(7407058,'Midnight Movies: Hamilton Movie Theater',cast('2021-10-01 23:45' as date),cast('2021-10-02 01:00' as date),'Hamilton Movie Theater','Arts','Movie/Film','SAA','Midnight Movies are back at the Hamilton Theater!! Movies are first come, first serve. '||chr(10)||'Free entry with your HUES Card and free pizza from Slices.'||chr(10)||'Movie Screenings'||chr(10)||'Friday, September 3rd - Shang Chi and the Legend fo the Ten Rings'||chr(10)||'Friday, October 1st - Addams Family 2'||chr(10)||'Saturday, October 2nd - Venom 2'||chr(10)||'Friday, October 22nd - Dune'||chr(10)||'Friday, November 12th - Eternals',null),
