(376249,'CAB Take Two: Hunger Games Marathon',cast('2014-02-15 19:00' as date),cast('2014-02-15 23:45' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','CAB Take Two presents Hunger Games Marathon on Saturday night starting at 7pm.'||chr(10)||'Re-visit the exciting adventures of Katniss Everdeen!'||chr(10)||'Hunger Games Sat 7 pm'||chr(10)||'Katniss Everdeen voluntarily takes her younger sister''s place in the Hunger Games, a televised fight to the death in which two teenagers from each of the twelve Districts of Panem are chosen at random to compete.'||chr(10)||'Catching Fire Sat 9:30pm'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Katniss Everdeen and Peeta Mellark become targets of the Capitol after their victory in the 74th Hunger Games sparks a rebellion in the Districts of Panem.',null),
(403629,'"Sons of Lwala" Film Screening',cast('2014-04-02 19:00' as date),cast('2014-04-02 19:00' as date),'Persson Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','HGHC','Dr. Fred Ochieng and his brother, Dr. Milton Ochieng, started a community health clinic in their village of Lwala, Kenya after losing both of their parents to AIDS. This 45 minute documentary depicts their journey as they open their clinic and documents some of the amazing work that they have done to improve health outcomes in their village. Dr. Fred Ochieng was the keynote speaker at the Wolk Medical Conference this semester. Pizza will be served.',null),
(467873,'The Departed',cast('2014-10-18 17:00' as date),cast('2014-10-18 18:00' as date),'Golden Auditorium, Little Hall','Arts','Movie/Film','HFS','Looking for a grueling crime thriller? Look no further! Come down to Golden Auditorium to watch Martin Scorcese''s The Departed.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Description from IMDB: An undercover state cop who has infiltrated an Irish gang and a mole in the police force working for the same mob race to track down and identify each other before being exposed to the enemy, after both sides realize their outfit has a rat.',null),
(521886,'Global health Initiative Film Screening: "The Human Experiment"',cast('2014-11-18 18:30' as date),cast('2014-11-18 20:30' as date),'Persson Auditorium','Thoughtful Learning','Movie/Film','HGHC','"The Human Experiment lifts the veil on the shocking reality that thousands of untested chemicals are in our everyday products, our homes and inside of us. Simultaneously, the prevalence of many diseases continues to rise. From Oscar winner Sean Penn and Emmy winning journalists Dana Nachman and Don Hardy, The Human Experiment tells the personal stories of people who believe their lives have been affected by chemicals and takes viewers to the front lines as activists go head-to-head with the powerful and well-funded chemical industry. These activists bring to light a corrupt system thats been hidden from consumers... until now"'||chr(10)||'Global Health Initiative will screen this film in Persson Auditorium at 6:30 and there will be pizza and garlic knots from VJs!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' ',null),
(742633,'Screening of Sundance Film Festival Hit: Dope',cast('2015-09-25 22:00' as date),cast('2015-09-25 22:45' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','Come watch the screening of the Sundance Film Festival hit, Dope! Showings are this weekend on Friday at 10PM and Saturday at 7PM in Love Auditorium!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Synopsis:Life changes for Malcolm, a geek who''s surviving life in a tough neighborhood, after a chance invitation to an underground party leads him and his friends into a Los Angeles adventure.'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||' ',null),
(7887161,'Charade Screening',cast('2022-02-26 13:00' as date),cast('2022-02-26 15:30' as date),'020 Lawrence Auditorium','Cultural','Movie/Film','HFS','Come on down to Hudson Film Society''s first screening of the semester for a showing of Stanley Donen''s 1963 classic, Charade, starring Cary Grant and Audrey Hepburn!',null),
(9044999,'13 Days of Green - Hamilton Movie Theatre Film Screening: "To The End"',cast('2023-04-17 19:00' as date),cast('2023-04-17 19:00' as date),'Hamilton Movie Theatre','Arts','Movie/Film','DM','The Hamilton Movie Theatre, The Vis Lab, the Democracy Matters Club, and the Office of Sustainability have joined forces to offer a screening of an award-winning environmental film, To The End. Tickets are free, so mark your calendars! Watch the trailer here.'||chr(10)||'Filmed over four years of hope and crisis, To the End captures the emergence of a new generation of leaders and the movement behind the most sweeping climate change legislation in U.S. history. The award-winning team behind Knock Down the House follows four exceptional young women  Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez, activist Varshini Prakash, climate policy writer Rhiana Gunn-Wright, and political strategist Alexandra Rojas as they grapple with new challenges of leadership and power and work together to defend their generations right to a future. From street protests to the halls of Congress, these bold leaders fight to shift the narrative around climate, revealing the crisis as an opportunity to build a better society. Including up-to-the-minute footage that culminates in 2022s landmark climate bill. To the End lifts the veil on the battle for the future of our world, and gives audiences a front seat view of history in the making.'||chr(10)||'This screening is part of the Office of Sustainabilitys 13 Days of Green series leading up to Earth Day. ',null),
(1227655,'Africana Women''s Week(s) 2017',cast('2017-02-28 12:00' as date),cast('2017-03-08 20:00' as date),'Hudson University','Cultural',NULL,'SRT','Sisters of the Round Table (SORT) is a feminist organization whose mission is to provide a safe space for women of color to talk about issues that pertain to us locally and globally. Every Spring during the last week of February and the first week of March to celebrate the journey from Black history month to Women''s History month, we hold an event series entitled Africana Womens Week(s). SORT takes pride in strong sisterhood by providing outlets that foster bonding and support for women of color. A central component is to educate the community about the issues that women face. AWW will not only cover issues facing women but also issues surrounding inequality, identity, and inclusivity, thus attracting a diverse audience. SORT allows people from different backgrounds to discuss and bring awareness to these issues. These events will be a catalyst for greater and more meaningful discussions on campus. This year''s theme is Moving Past Survival; Healing as a Catalyst for Growth. Our feature keynote is: Diane Guerrero: known for her roles as inmate Maritza Ramos on the Netflix series Orange Is the New Black and Lina on Jane the Virgin. She is a strong and vocal advocate for immigration reform. Her role on Orange Is the New Black has twice contributed to wins for the Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by an Ensemble in a Comedy Series.',null),
(1248472,'University Church Board Game Night',cast('2017-04-06 21:00' as date),cast('2017-04-06 23:00' as date),'Interfaith House','Social','Religious/Spiritual','UC','Enjoy a night of fellowship and fun with board games and dessert every Thursday, 9pm until midnight, at Interfaith House (104 Broad Street). Typical favorites include games like Avalon, Settlers of Catan, Blokus, Scrabble, and more! Feel free to bring your own games, as well. ',null),
