(2887153,'Black Student Union Party',cast('2018-11-02 22:00' as date),cast('2018-11-03 01:00' as date),'Creative Arts House','Social','Dance','BSU','This event will serve as the annual social fall semester event for the Black Student Union. Traditionally, this party has been a mainstay of the Hudson community as it is highly attended and well reviewed. The Black Student Union plans on opening this event to the entire Hudson community, regardless of race, gender, class year, or affiliations to other campus groups. Music will be provided by DJ Highclass, one of NYCs and Upstate New Yorks up and coming DJs. He is known for his diverse sound and is very involved in the Black Student Union and Caribbean Student Association of his own university. ',null),
(3310501,'SPW Pool Party',cast('2019-04-13 16:00' as date),cast('2019-04-13 17:00' as date),'Lineberry Natatorium','Social',NULL,'SRT','Join us for an SPW pool party!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Games, food, and a live dj at Lineberry Natatorium (the Hudson Pool).',null),
(4884966,'Coffee Connections',cast('2019-09-11 16:00' as date),cast('2019-09-11 17:00' as date),'Coop Patio','Social',NULL,'SAA','Connect with new and old friends over a cup of Fojo Beans'' coffee and pasteries! We will have opportunities for coffee stain art and a raffle featuring prizes from Fojo Beans. Sponsored by The Hudson Activities Board!  ',null),
(533650,'Ski and Snowboard Club Meeting',cast('2014-12-03 16:30' as date),cast('2014-12-03 17:30' as date),'Lawrence 105','Social',NULL,'HSSC','Hudson Ski and Snowboard Club is meeting in preparation for our trips in the spring semester. All Hudson students are welcome. ',null),
(582662,'International Mother Language Day',cast('2015-01-12 12:00' as date),cast('2015-01-12 13:00' as date),'Keck Center','Cultural',NULL,'SACC','International Mother language day is celebrated annually on 21st February, to celebrate the linguistic diversities and cultures of the world. It was declared an international observance by The United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization in 1999. This observance has it''s roots and history in Bangladesh, and it''s language movement. Professor Murshid from the political science department will be speaking about this history and the background of this observance which is of great significance to South Asian people. We will cater traditional Bangladeshi foods and also have some simple and traditional South Asian decorations for our venue.  '||chr(10)||' ',null),
(597089,'Dean Obeidullah Comedy Show',cast('2015-04-16 18:00' as date),cast('2015-04-16 19:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Cultural',NULL,'HMSA','Dean Obeidullah is a renowned Arab-American comedian who has preformed comedy acts in USA, Jordan, Palestine, Saudi Arabia, Egypt, Lebanon, Oman, Israel, Qatar, and Dubai. He raises awareness about Arab and Muslim cultures, which rids of the prejudices about Muslims. Students will have the opportunity to learn more about Islamic culture and politics in a comical manner. ',null),
(598041,'Classics Coffee Hour',cast('2015-03-27 13:20' as date),cast('2015-03-27 13:45' as date),'Lawrence 112/114','Cultural',NULL,'HCS','If you have a passion for the classics, explore it further by coming to the Classics Coffee Hours in the Classics Lounge (Law 112/114)! Meet wth Classics students and professors!',null),
(623082,'Interfaith Dinner',cast('2015-09-10 18:00' as date),cast('2015-09-10 18:00' as date),'Chapel Basement','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'NC','The Interfaith Dinners are an opportunity for students to come together, talk about their different beliefs and share a meal. For this meal in particular, the Hudson Jewish Union will be hosting and leading discussion on Rosh Hashanah. ',null),
(6924586,'Women''s Water Polo Practice',cast('2021-02-13 11:15' as date),cast('2021-02-13 13:00' as date),'Pool','Athletics','Club Sports','WPCW','Practice. Please do not show up without contacting the primary contact due to limited space.',null),
(6969651,'Saraswati Puja',cast('2021-03-20 12:00' as date),cast('2021-03-20 13:00' as date),'Edge Cafe','Cultural','Concert/Music','HINDU','Saraswati Puja is a Hindu festival that celebrates the arrival of Spring and the Goddess Saraswati, who is the Goddess of wisdom, knowledge, music, and art. To commemorate this festival, the Hindu Students Association will be hosting a small celebration where we explain the significance of the festival followed by a prayer. This celebration will be accompanied by a musical performance on the sitar and tabla as well as food from RIG!',null),
(7026462,'Open Art-Making with the Senior Honor Society',cast('2021-03-30 20:00' as date),cast('2021-03-30 21:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Arts','Volunteer and Community Service ','THS','Join the Senior Honor Society Class of 2021 and 2022 to make some original artwork! Follow a guided lesson from a Hudson art professor in one side of the room or hang out and listen to music and work on independent pieces on the other side of the room. There will be Senior Honor Society members floating around to help guide you on technique, help you come up with ideas, and make art alongside you.',null),
(7127607,'Student Organization Involvement and Campus Resource Fair',cast('2021-09-02 17:00' as date),cast('2021-09-02 18:00' as date),'Academic Quad, Residential Quad, Burke Pinchin Quad','Social',NULL,'COVE','Stop by the Academic, Residential, and Burke/Pinchin Quads for the Student Organization Involvement Fair and the Campus Resource Fair! to find different ways to get involved on campus. Rain location is Huntington Gym.'||chr(10)||'Download the Corq app to find campus events, free food, free stuff, and more!',null),
(7512826,'Euphoria Party',cast('2021-10-15 18:00' as date),cast('2021-10-15 20:30' as date),'Rainbow Room','Social','Dance','QTPC','Come dressed in what helps you celebrate your gender/sexuality euphoria. Inspired by the show celebrating queer and POC identities. We will have a wall painting booth for our queer students to add their hands to our wall celebrating queer students, a polaroid photo-booth, pride flags, and temporary tattoos. ',null),
(7616930,'KCA x Hancock commons - Squid Game Takeover: Rice Balls and Ramen',cast('2021-12-05 12:00' as date),cast('2021-12-05 14:00' as date),'Bryan Complex Kitchen','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','Cooking ramen and rice balls, introduction of Korean casual cuisine.',null),
(7893592,'Lunar New Year Festival',cast('2022-02-26 12:30' as date),cast('2022-02-26 19:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'KCA','This year is the year of Tiger. Come learn about how different cultures celebrate Lunar New Year at ALANA on Feb. 26! Featuring clubs: OASIS+, CIC, HVS, CJCC, KCA, Tea Club, and SACC. During the day, we have various games from different countries, cultural food, and many other activities. Authentic Chinese food will be offered as dinner!!!'||chr(10)||'The detailed event schedule is as follows:'||chr(10)||'12:30 pm - 2:30 pm: CIC, Tea Club, KCA'||chr(10)||'3:00 pm - 5:00: OASIS+, HVS, SACC'||chr(10)||'5:30 pm - 7:00 pm: dinner (first come first serve)'||chr(10)||'*CJCC will be filming a Japanese-culture-related movie on Mar. 1; please contact CJCC for more information.',null),
(8010127,'Dinner and Discussion With Dr. J: Diversity and Equity in Medicine',cast('2022-03-23 18:30' as date),cast('2022-03-23 18:30' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'ALANA','Join Hudson MAPS for a chance to meet Hudson''s pre-health sciences advisor Dr. Julie Chanatry (Dr.J) for a guided conversation around the topics of the pre-med path, what it means for an institution to promote diversity and equity in the lens of medicine, and boundaries to the pursuit of DEI in healthcare. '||chr(10)||'This event is catered by Royal India Grill! Free food, but RSVP Required, so please register to get a seat and a plate! RSVP: bit.ly/dinnerdrj'||chr(10)||'Contact hudsonmaps@hudson.edu (or DM @hudsonmaps on instagram) for more information!',null),
(8583207,'Course Registration 102',cast('2022-11-10 18:30' as date),cast('2022-11-10 19:45' as date),'Alana Cultural Center','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'BROS','Brothers and Black Student Union are hosting the second part of our course registration series to help first years and transfer students register for Spring 2023 courses! We will have upperclassmen on standby to help anyone who runs into any issues during their time slot. We will also be making s''mores!',null),
(8594123,'CIC Global Kitchen',cast('2022-11-16 16:00' as date),cast('2022-11-16 19:00' as date),'ALANA Cultural Center','Cultural',NULL,'HIC','This event will gather student chefs and language interns from different national and cultural backgrounds to cook the food of their culture. After cooking, student chefs and language interns will share them with Hudson Community as a dinner. Before eating, the chefs will introduce the dishes to the participants regarding where the food originated, the cultural meaning and history of the food, how the food is made, or even the eating habits of people from that culture.'||chr(10)||'Don''t hesitate to sign up for the Global Kitchen if you want to have dinner made by students and language interns from different cultures!'||chr(10)||'Sign-up link: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/191DoD4dyNm9vCOAG-2yJZuMNzXbrWj_hdDDDXI6Cvjo/edit?usp=sharing',null),
(873644,'Hudson Buddhist Community Lunch: "Are You Happy?"',cast('2016-02-02 12:15' as date),cast('2016-02-02 13:15' as date),'Chapel Basement Lounge','Spirituality',NULL,'HBC','CBC is excited for a new semester of introducing Buddhist philosophy and offer a space for inspiring discussions and meditations!'||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Take a moment to reflect on whether you are happy, and well talk and look at some of it from a Buddhist perspective. Food will be catered from the delicious Hamilton Whole Foods  stop by and enjoy the great food and company, and feel free to invite those who you feel might be interested.'||chr(10)||' ',null),
(8823648,'Tri Delta COB',cast('2023-02-13 18:00' as date),cast('2023-02-13 20:00' as date),'Tri Delta House','Group Business',NULL,'DDD','COB, or continuous open bidding, is a more relaxed, informal recruitment process open to sophomores and juniors who want to explore the possibility of joining Tri Delta without the stresses of formal recruitment. This semester, our COB event will be a meet the sisters cookie decorating event in our house on 2/13 from 6-8 pm.',null),
(8935709,'Interest Meeting: Positive Post-Its, Hot Chocolate, and Doughnuts!!!',cast('2023-03-03 15:00' as date),cast('2023-03-03 16:00' as date),'COVE Lounge (109 Lathrop Hall)','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','RAK','We will be hosting an interest meeting to discuss what Do Random Acts of Kindness Club is about! We will be doing one of our favorite activities: Positive Post-Its, and will share hot chocolate and doughnuts!!! Everyone is welcome- regardless of whether or not you have attended a previous event this semester!',null),
(9056886,'Be the Match Donor Registry',cast('2023-04-26 10:00' as date),cast('2023-04-26 14:00' as date),'Frank Dining Hall and Library Patio','Community Service','Volunteer and Community Service ','COVE','Volunteer to help table with the Hudson Football Team and Public Health Initiatives on April 25 and 26 or stop by to join the Be The Match donor registry. The national Be The Match registry pairs volunteer blood stem cell donors with thousands of patients diagnosed with life-threatening blood cancers. By giving 1-hour of your time as a volunteer or signing-up as a potential donor, you are increasing the chance to save a life. Visit the tables outside Frank Dining Hall and the Library Patio between 10am - 3pm for free giveaways, more information on Be The Match, and to join the registry. '||chr(10)||' '||chr(10)||'Sign-up here to volunteer!',null),
(9058700,'Values Week: Study Break',cast('2023-04-17 16:15' as date),cast('2023-04-17 17:00' as date),'Coop Conference Room','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'CPC','Take a break with the members of Hudson''s Panhellenic and IFC community. Enjoy some delicious Eatery snacks in the Coop Conference Room starting at 4:15pm. ',null),
(954491,'Diwali''16',cast('2016-11-05 18:00' as date),cast('2016-11-05 20:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Spirituality',NULL,'HINDU','Diwali is the Hindu festival of lights and has been celebrated annually at Hudson in the fall semester. It is one of the most important Hindu festivals, marks the New Year for some and has been widely attended in recent years.',null),
(9587036,'Grill Club X Tri Delta',cast('2023-11-04 12:00' as date),cast('2023-11-04 13:00' as date),'Delta Delta Delta','Social',NULL,'DDD','Join us this Saturday for some delicious pulled pork, BBQ burnt ends, burgers, hot dogs, vegan meat options, and seasonal veggies. All. For. Free.',null),
(9835110,'Winterfest 2024',cast('2024-02-03 17:00' as date),cast('2024-02-03 19:00' as date),'Hall of Presidents','Social',NULL,'SAA','Winterfest Extravaganza  Join us this Saturday, February 3rd, 2024, at the Hall of Presidents from 5 to 7 PM for a winter wonderland of fun!  Embrace the chilly vibes with activities like mini golf, artsy adventures, and more. Bundle up and let the festivities begin! See you there! ',null),
(168719,'Take Two: The Avengers',cast('2012-09-08 22:00' as date),cast('2012-09-08 23:00' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','Nick Fury of S.H.I.E.L.D. brings together a team of super humans to form The Avengers to help save the Earth from Loki and his army.'||chr(10)||'Robert Downey Jr., Chris Evans, and Scarlett Johansson; PG 13; 143 min.; 2012.',null),
(186973,'Midnight Movie: ARGO',cast('2012-10-12 23:45' as date),cast('2012-10-13 00:45' as date),'Hamilton Movie Theater',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','CAB Take Two and the Muslim Students Association present a Midnight Movie - ARGO, Friday 11:59PM at the Hamilton Movie Theater. Tickets are ***FREE*** to all Hudson students (*theater capacity is 240*). Start out Homecoming Weekend right! Description from imdb: "As the Iranian revolution reaches a boiling point, a CIA ''exfiltration'' specialist concocts a risky plan to free six Americans who have found shelter at the home of the Canadian ambassador." Stars: Ben Affleck, Bryan Cranston and John Goodman. Rated R, 120 minutes. Trailer: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JW3WfSFgrVY',null),
(194089,'Take Two: Madagascar 3',cast('2012-10-26 19:00' as date),cast('2012-10-26 20:00' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','Madagascar 3: Europe''s Most Wanted'||chr(10)||'Alex, Marty, Gloria and Melman are still fighting to get home to their beloved Big Apple. Their journey takes them through Europe where they find the perfect cover: a traveling circus, which they reinvent - Madagascar style.'||chr(10)||'Ben Stiller, Jada Pinkett Smith and Chris Rock; Rated PG; 93 min.; 2012.',null),
(194094,'Midnight Movie: ROCKY HORROR PICTURE SHOW',cast('2012-10-26 23:45' as date),cast('2012-10-27 01:00' as date),'Hamilton Movie Theater',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','A Take Two tradition of sorts, come to the Hamilton Movie Theater at 11:59PM this Friday to enjoy this cult classic in time for Halloween! It will also be a great source of fun for the entire family this Family Weekend. **FREE ADMISSION WITH HUES Card** "A newly engaged couple have a breakdown in an isolated area and must pay a call to the bizarre residence of Dr. Frank-N-Furter." (from IMDB) Stars Tim Curry, Susan Sarandon and Barry Bostwick; Rated R; 100 min.; 1975.',null),
(200465,'Take Two: The Amazing Spider-Man',cast('2012-11-10 19:00' as date),cast('2012-11-10 21:00' as date),'Golden Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','Peter Parker finds a clue that might help him understand why his parents disappeared when he was young. His path puts him on a collision course with Dr. Curt Connors, his father''s former partner.'||chr(10)||'Andrew Garfield, Emma Stone and Rhys Ifans; PG-13; 136 min.'||chr(10)||'from imdb.com',null),
(233081,'CAB Take Two: Skyfall',cast('2013-03-01 19:00' as date),cast('2013-03-01 21:30' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','CAB Take Two presents Skyfall:'||chr(10)||'Bond''s loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. Whilst MI6 comes under attack, 007 must track down and destroy the threat, no matter how personal the cost.'||chr(10)||'from imdb.com',null),
(249615,'CAB Take Two: Argo',cast('2013-04-06 19:00' as date),cast('2013-04-06 20:15' as date),'Love Auditorium',NULL,'Movie/Film','SAA','CAB Take Two Movies presents Oscar Winning Movies:'||chr(10)||'Django Unchained at 7:00PM and Argo at 10:00PM in Love Auditorium on Friday, April 5th, and again at opposite times on Saturday, April 6th.'||chr(10)||'Django Unchained:'||chr(10)||'With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.'||chr(10)||'Argo:'||chr(10)||'A dramatization of the 1980 joint CIA-Canadian secret operation to extract six fugitive American diplomatic personnel out of revolutionary Iran.'||chr(10)||' ',null),
