(892902,'Take Two presents Oscars Week: The Danish Girl (2015)',cast('2016-02-19 19:00' as date),cast('2016-02-19 21:00' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','Showings are 7PM on Friday (2/19) and 10PM on Saturday (2/20) in Love Auditorium!'||chr(10)||'A fictitious love story loosely inspired by the lives of Danish artists Lili Elbe and Gerda Wegener. Lili and Gerda''s marriage and work evolve as they navigate Lili''s groundbreaking journey as a transgender pioneer.',null),
(892903,'Take Two presents Oscars Week: The Danish Girl (2015)',cast('2016-02-20 22:00' as date),cast('2016-02-20 23:45' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','Showings are 7PM on Friday (2/19) and 10PM on Saturday (2/20) in Love Auditorium!'||chr(10)||'A fictitious love story loosely inspired by the lives of Danish artists Lili Elbe and Gerda Wegener. Lili and Gerda''s marriage and work evolve as they navigate Lili''s groundbreaking journey as a transgender pioneer.',null),
(270374,'Dance Team Uniforms- request for BAC Funding',cast('2013-08-02 12:15' as date),cast('2013-08-02 12:15' as date),'Hudson University',NULL,'Dance','HDT','The Hudson Dance Team is expanding immensely, and we have already planned various performances through the Athletic Department, such as a Homecoming performance. In order to professionally represent Hudson at these events the entire team needs official Hudson uniforms. These uniforms include a maroon jersey top, of which we have very few. In order to accomodate the current team and also incoming freshmen and other students who will audition to join our team, it is crucial that we purchase more of these jersey tops. Dance Team funds are quite limited, so it is essential that we request and hopefully receive funding from the BAC so that we can proudly represent our school in front of students, alumni, parents, and visitors.      ',null),
(708414,'Bachata Heightz Homecoming Concert',cast('2015-09-18 22:00' as date),cast('2015-09-19 01:00' as date),'Parker Commons','Social',NULL,'LASO','The Latin American Student Organization (LASO) and other sponsors have invited Bachata Heightz to perform and headline a Bachata concert in honor of Hispanic Heritage Month (HHM) on Friday September 18, the beginning of Homecoming weekend, at 10pm at the Parker Commons.  '||chr(10)||'Bachata Heightz is a group composed of five talented young persons born and raised in Washington Heights in New York City. They became a group eight years ago as a hobby to keep them off the streets and to explore their musical passion, yet theyve become one of the most influential groups in the Hispanic market. The group has been one of the early pioneers of what is now known as ''urban style'' in the genre of bachata, with influences like hip hop, r and b and rock, as well as major influences of the environment where they lived. Their experiences in the streets of New York and the influences of their Latin upbringing compliment their tropical and sentimental sound to create a unique, vibrant musical sensation that will surely captivate the audience at Hudson.'||chr(10)||' ',null),
(747200,'Open Improv workshop with Tim Stoltenberg',cast('2015-10-03 12:00' as date),cast('2015-10-03 13:00' as date),'Ryan 212','Thoughtful Learning',NULL,'CG','Veteran comedian and improvsiational actor, member of the Improvised Shakespeare Company, and alum of the Second City touring company Tim Stoltenberg comes to campus to give a 2-hour workshop on improv comedy. He''ll shell out the secrets that make him a legend in Chicago improv.',null),
(791411,'Take Two: DIVERGENT (2014)',cast('2015-11-06 19:00' as date),cast('2015-11-06 20:00' as date),'Love Auditorium','Social',NULL,'SAA','In a world divided by factions based on virtues, Tris learns she''s Divergent and won''t fit in. When she discovers a plot to destroy Divergents, Tris and the mysterious Four must find out what makes Divergents dangerous before it''s too late.'||chr(10)||'Screenings are Friday 11/6 @ 7PM, and 11/7 @10PM in Love Auditorium, Free Admission!',null),
